      "skillMarkdown": "# Add Shortcut to New Tab Page\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill to add a website shortcut tile to the Chrome or Chromium New Tab page. The reusable workflow is text-first: open the New Tab shortcut editor, enter the current task's requested shortcut label and URL, save the dialog, and verify that the new tile appears in the shortcut grid.\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task asks to add a website shortcut to the Chrome or Chromium New Tab page.\n- The task provides, or clearly implies, the shortcut label and destination URL to enter.\n- Chrome can open a New Tab page with the shortcut grid below the search box.\n\nDo not use this skill for startup-page settings, bookmarks, pinned tabs, browsing history, profile setup, or theme changes unless the current task also requires adding a New Tab shortcut tile.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nUse `runtime_state_cards.json` for runtime branch loading and matching. Use `state_cards.json` only for audit, debugging, and the fuller image-level rationale. The runtime should load only the card whose `when_to_use` condition matches the current screenshot, not every image in the package.\n\n- `Images/new_tab_add_shortcut_button.png`: New Tab shortcut grid with the plus tile labeled Add shortcut.\n- `Images/add_shortcut_dialog_fields.png`: Add shortcut dialog with editable Name and URL fields.\n- `Images/url_field_corrected.png`: URL field focused or selected for correction and verification.\n- `Images/click_done_button.png`: ready-to-save dialog with fields filled and Done enabled.\n\nRed boxes mark interaction cues such as fields or buttons. Green boxes mark state or verification cues such as the active dialog. Treat both as visual guidance only, never as fixed coordinates.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Open a Chrome New Tab page.\n2. In the shortcut grid below the search box, find the circular plus tile labeled Add shortcut. Use the matching runtime card for `Images/new_tab_add_shortcut_button.png` only if the current screenshot is this New Tab grid state.\n3. Click Add shortcut to open the editor dialog.\n4. In the Add shortcut dialog, enter the current task's requested shortcut label in the Name field and the requested destination address in the URL field. Use the matching runtime card for `Images/add_shortcut_dialog_fields.png` only when the dialog with both fields is visible.\n5. If the URL was typed into the wrong field, contains a typo, or is selected for replacement, focus the URL field, select the existing URL text if needed, and type the correct address. Use the matching runtime card for `Images/url_field_corrected.png` only for this focused URL-field state.\n6. Verify that the Name and URL fields match the current task request and that Done is enabled.\n7. Click Done. Use the matching runtime card for `Images/click_done_button.png` only when it matches the ready-to-save dialog state.\n8. After the dialog closes, verify that a shortcut tile for the requested label or site appears in the New Tab shortcut grid.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy example shortcut names, URLs, existing tile labels, browser profile details, launcher icons, or window layout from the images.\n- Do not assume the Add shortcut tile, dialog fields, or Done button appear at the same screen coordinates.\n- Do not treat the filled dialog image as task completion. Completion requires the saved shortcut tile to appear on the New Tab page.\n- If the active Chrome surface is not the New Tab page or the Add shortcut dialog, navigate to the matching text state before using an image card.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The Add shortcut dialog closes after clicking Done.\n- The New Tab page shortcut grid is visible again.\n- A new tile matching the requested shortcut label or destination site is present in the grid.\n- If the tile is not visible, refresh or reopen the New Tab page and inspect the shortcut grid before declaring completion.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- The URL is incomplete, misspelled, or malformed, leaving Done disabled.\n- The shortcut label is entered into the URL field, or the URL is entered into the Name field.\n- A visible example value from an image is copied instead of the current task's requested value.\n- The task is mistaken for Chrome startup-page settings, bookmarks, pinned tabs, or profile customization.",
