      "skillMarkdown": "# Check Finance And Copy Or Share Stock Links\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task is about a stock or company quote in Chrome and the required work can be completed from Google Finance: opening the requested quote page, checking visible finance news titles or links, copying or sharing the quote link, or following the stock page.\n\nThe task must identify the target company or ticker. Prefer another skill when the instruction names a different finance site, requires account-specific portfolio management, asks for market analysis beyond visible page content, or needs an external sharing app workflow that is not part of the browser or OS share surface.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome or Chromium can reach Google Finance.\n- The target company name or ticker is known from the current task.\n- Any requested clipboard or sharing handoff is supported by the surrounding environment.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Open Google Finance in Chrome, or use the address bar or Google Finance search field to search for the requested company or ticker.\n2. If Google Finance shows quote suggestions, choose the result whose company name, ticker, and exchange match the current task. Do not rely on row order from an image card.\n3. Verify that the opened quote page header matches the requested stock before reading news, sharing, copying, or following.\n4. If the task asks for article context, scroll to the news section and read the requested current titles or links from the live page.\n5. If the task asks to share or copy the stock link, use the quote page Share control or the browser URL/share surface, then complete the requested copy or share handoff.\n6. If the task asks to follow the stock, use the Follow control and verify the resulting visible state on the same quote page.\n7. Finish only after the visible page and final state match the current task, not the example screenshot content.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nUse this as a text-first skill. Load visual cards only when the current screenshot plausibly matches the described state. The audit-quality image cards live in `state_cards.json`; the compact cards for Agent branch matching live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\nRuntime should load only the matching card or cards for the current state, not every image in the package:\n\n- `Images/google_finance_quote_page.png` marks the Google Finance search/suggestion entry state for selecting the requested quote.\n- `Images/finance_news_context.png` marks the quote-page news/context list for reading visible article titles or links.\n- `Images/finance_share_dialog.png` marks the pre-click Share control on the quote page.\n- `Images/finance_follow_or_share_state.png` marks the quote-page follow/share verification area after the relevant action.\n\nRed boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues. Use the labeled visual relationship and surrounding page context, not the screenshot coordinates.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\nThe screenshots are examples of Google Finance surfaces, not reusable task content. Do not transfer the example company, ticker, exchange, price, percentage change, chart tooltip, news headline, publisher, article order, thumbnail, browser profile, or scroll position unless the current live page independently shows the same required content.\n\nGoogle Finance layouts can shift by viewport, account state, locale, and time. If the Share or Follow control moves, locate the equivalent labeled control on the current quote page. If suggestions differ, choose the result that matches the task's company or ticker rather than the screenshot's row position.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nFor quote-page entry, the header should show the requested company or ticker and the page should include the Google Finance quote chart or quote details.\n\nFor news inspection, the required number of current article titles or links should be visible or already captured from the quote page news section.\n\nFor sharing or copying, verify the share/copy surface opened or the requested link handoff is complete. The Share button card only shows where to act before completion.\n\nFor following, verify the Follow control reflects the requested final state on the requested quote page. Use `Images/finance_follow_or_share_state.png` as a visual verification cue for the current stock, not as proof for the screenshot's example stock.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Selecting the wrong security from suggestions because it has a similar company name or ticker.\n- Treating a red or green box as a fixed coordinate after the layout changes.\n- Stopping after locating the Share button without opening the share/copy surface or completing the requested handoff.\n- Copying screenshot article titles or market values instead of reading the current page.\n- Finishing on a generic Google results page, a news article page, or the wrong Google Finance quote page.",
