      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Appearance Reading Mode and Toolbar\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when Chrome or Chromium must show a visible appearance result, especially:\n\n- opening the Reading mode side panel\n- changing Reading mode font family\n- changing Reading mode background or theme\n- confirming that a toolbar or bookmarks-bar visibility change is actually visible\n- reverting `Chrome Refresh 2023`-style UI changes through `chrome://flags` when the task explicitly asks for the older desktop UI\n\nThis skill is only complete when the requested visual state is present in the live browser UI.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome or Chromium is open and can reach the needed menu, side panel, Appearance control, or `chrome://flags` surface.\n- If the task depends on Reading mode content, be ready to switch to a readable page if the current page only shows the Reading mode empty state.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nUse `runtime_state_cards.json` as the compact card source for runtime branch loading. Load only the card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screenshot and current subgoal. Do not preload every image card just because the task mentions Chrome.\n\nUse `state_cards.json` as the full detailed version. It contains the same one-card-per-image coverage with fuller transfer limits, verification notes, and evidence metadata.\n\nKey image references:\n\n- `Images/reading_mode_surface.png`: entry cue for the menu path that exposes Reading mode\n- `Images/reading_mode_font_menu.png`: operation cue for the Reading mode font dropdown\n- `Images/reading_mode_color_choice.png`: operation cue for the Reading mode color or theme control\n- `Images/reading_mode_verification_state.png`: verification cue for a persisted Reading mode result\n- `Images/chrome_refresh_flags_surface.png`: filtered `chrome://flags` entry cue for Chrome Refresh rollback work\n- `Images/chrome_refresh_primary_dropdown.png`: operation cue for the main `Chrome Refresh 2023` row dropdown\n- `Images/chrome_refresh_relaunch_ready.png`: pending-apply cue for the `Relaunch` button after refresh-row changes\n\nAt runtime, only load the matching image card rather than the whole image set.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues and green boxes are state or verification cues. Neither one gives reusable coordinates.\n- Example font labels, background colors, flag-row ordering, page content, and account details in the screenshots are not target values unless the live task independently requests them.\n- Window size, zoom, menu placement, and panel dimensions can change across runs.\n- `chrome://flags` work is build-sensitive. Compare the live row names and visible pending `Relaunch` state instead of assuming the screenshot's exact row inventory.\n- Prefer the live Chrome UI when the same control or result state is visible in a slightly different layout.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Identify the required visible outcome: open Reading mode, change font, change background or theme, confirm a toolbar or bookmarks-bar state, or revert the Chrome Refresh UI.\n2. Reach the correct Chrome surface.\n   - For Reading mode, use the menu flow shown in `Images/reading_mode_surface.png` only when the live UI matches that menu state.\n   - For Chrome Refresh rollback, open `chrome://flags`, filter for `Chrome Refresh 2023`, and inspect the visible refresh rows before changing any dropdown.\n3. Change the requested control.\n   - Use the font card only when the Reading mode font dropdown is visible.\n   - Use the color or theme card only when the Reading mode toolbar shows that control.\n   - Use the refresh dropdown card only when the visible row name matches the live task and the row still needs a value change.\n4. If the task also requires page navigation, complete that navigation while preserving or reopening the needed appearance state.\n5. Verify the final visible result before stopping.\n   - For refresh-flag tasks, the stored screenshot only proves the pre-relaunch pending state. Click `Relaunch`, then verify the restarted browser reflects the requested older UI before marking success.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- For Reading mode tasks, verify that the side panel is still open on the right and that the visible font, background or theme, and page context match the instruction.\n- For toolbar or bookmarks-bar tasks, verify the persistent visible state in the browser window rather than relying only on a menu toggle.\n- For Chrome Refresh rollback tasks, verify both the relevant changed rows and the pending `Relaunch` state before applying changes, then confirm the restarted browser matches the requested UI.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening Reading mode but leaving the requested font or color unchanged.\n- Copying the example screenshot's font or tint instead of the live task's requested value.\n- Treating a red or green box as a stable click position after layout changes.\n- Disabling only one refresh row when nearby companion rows still obviously match the same `Chrome Refresh 2023` family.\n- Marking success from the pre-relaunch flags page without verifying the restarted browser UI.",
