      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Startup Downloads And System Behavior\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is to change a persistent Chrome setting rather than interact with page content. Typical cases:\n\n- change the default download folder\n- turn `Ask where to save each file before downloading` on or off\n- change `On startup` behavior or the startup page list\n- adjust a named control under `Performance` or `System`\n\nDo not use this skill for ordinary web browsing, downloading a page, website form entry, or OS-level file management outside the Chrome settings flow.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Reach the correct settings page.\n   - Prefer direct URLs when reliable: `chrome://settings/downloads`, `chrome://settings/onStartup`, `chrome://settings/performance`, or `chrome://settings/system`.\n   - Otherwise open Settings and use the left sidebar or settings search.\n\n2. Apply only the requested change.\n   - Downloads location: click `Change`, choose the requested folder in the system chooser, then confirm with `Select`.\n   - Ask-where-to-save: inspect the current toggle state first, then change it only if needed.\n   - On startup: select the requested option or edit the page list only as asked.\n   - Performance or System: change only the named control and leave nearby settings alone.\n\n3. Verify the persistent result before stopping.\n   - Downloads location is complete only when the Location row shows the requested destination.\n   - Ask-where-to-save is complete only when the visible toggle state matches the request.\n   - Startup, Performance, and System work is complete only when the named option is visibly in the requested state.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis package keeps two image-card files:\n\n- `state_cards.json`: full detailed cards with detailed rationale.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json`: compact cards for runtime branch loading.\n\nLoad only the card or cards whose `when_to_use` matches the live screenshot. Do not load every image as a fixed sequence.\n\n- `Images/downloads_settings_surface.png`: navigation card for reaching the Downloads page.\n- `Images/ask_where_to_save_toggle.png`: direct action card for the ask-where-to-save toggle on the Downloads page.\n- `Images/download_location_picker.png`: action card for the open system `Location` chooser after pressing `Change`.\n- `Images/download_location_updated.png`: verification card for the persistent `Location` row on the Downloads page.\n\nWhen the runtime already has the needed live state in view, prefer the matching compact runtime card and the visible UI text over any stored screenshot.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues. Neither is a reusable coordinate.\n- Do not copy example folder names, path text, table rows, or window geometry from the images.\n- Do not infer completion from a nearby sidebar item; verify the target page or control itself.\n- If the live screenshot conflicts with a stored card, trust the live UI labels and the current task.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Downloads location: the Downloads page is open and the Location row text matches the requested destination.\n- Ask-where-to-save: the named toggle is visible and its state matches the requested on or off value.\n- On startup: the requested radio choice or startup-page list is visibly selected.\n- Performance or System: the named control is visible and clearly in the requested state.\n- After using a chooser dialog, return focus to Chrome and verify the persistent setting row instead of stopping on the dialog itself.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- confusing the highlighted `Downloads` sidebar entry with the Downloads page already being loaded\n- flipping a toggle without first checking whether it already matches the task\n- selecting the example folder from a reference image instead of the folder named by the current task\n- stopping while the chooser is still open without verifying the saved Location row\n- carrying unrelated example goals from the source trajectory into the reusable settings workflow",
