      "skillMarkdown": "# Filter And Sort Commerce Results\n\n## Overview\n\nUse shopping-site result lists and shopping-specific filter or sorting controls to apply requested price, category, size, color, or rating constraints and verify that the shopping result list reflects the requested constraint.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Filtering or sorting a shopping results page\n- Applying price, category, size, color, rating, or deal constraints on shopping sites\n- Verifying that the shopping results page reflects the requested filter or sort state\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- A shopping results list is already open.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark action targets.\n- Green boxes mark verification or recovery signals.\n\n## Procedures\n\n### commerce_filters\n\n#### open_results_surface\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to filter or sort a shopping result list.\n- Visual grounding: A shopping results page with visible filter or sorting controls\n- Action: Reach the shopping results surface that contains the items to filter or sort.\n\n#### open_filter_or_sort_controls\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to apply requested filters or sorting on arbitrary commerce or travel sites\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on shopping or travel result lists with filters and sorting controls\n- Action: Advance Chrome through the `open_filter_or_sort_controls` subgoal until the result list shows the requested filter chips, ranges, or sorting label.\n- Image: `Images/shopping_filter_control.png`\n\n#### Expected Result: verify_commerce_filter_or_sort_state\n\n- Trigger: The requested shopping filter or sort should already be active.\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on shopping or travel result lists with filters and sorting controls\n- Action: Verify that the shopping results page reflects the requested filter or sort state.\n- Image: `Images/shopping_filter_applied.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Treating a travel results surface as if it were a shopping filter panel.\n- Stopping when a dropdown opens instead of verifying that the selected shopping constraint persists on the results page.\n- Confusing a product detail or cart page with the results page where filtering must happen.\n\n## Runtime Assets\n\n- `state_cards.json` carries the richer multiview authoring bundle.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` carries the slimmer runtime-facing card set.",
