      "skillMarkdown": "# Interact With YouTube And Video Page Controls\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is inside YouTube in Chrome and requires any of the following:\n\n- opening the requested creator channel or watch page\n- using the channel Videos tab and its sort chips\n- opening a target video from the current channel surface\n- using watch-page controls such as Like, Subscribe, Share, or Copy link\n- verifying that a YouTube engagement state is visibly active\n\nDo not use it for YouTube Studio, account settings, playlist management, comment authoring, uploads, or non-YouTube websites.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome can open YouTube.\n- The task already tells you which creator, video, sort order, or engagement result matters.\n- Sign-in state may gate Like or Subscribe. If YouTube blocks the action with a sign-in prompt, handle that prompt before claiming success.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Reach the requested YouTube surface. Use YouTube search, a direct URL, or visible navigation already on the page.\n2. If search results show a channel-style result row for the requested creator, confirm the live creator identity before opening it.\n3. If the task depends on channel ordering, open the Videos tab and select the requested sort chip before choosing a video.\n4. Open the intended video only after the creator surface and sort state match the task.\n5. On the watch page, act on the specific live control needed for the task: Like, Subscribe, Share, Copy link, or another visible control in the engagement row.\n6. Verify the exact requested result in the live UI before stopping. A generic watch page is not enough.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n`state_cards.json` is the full audit record. `runtime_state_cards.json` is the compact runtime version for the agent branch. Load only the card whose `image_path`, `when_to_use`, and visible cues match the current screenshot.\n\n- `Images/youtube_channel_surface.png`: use only when the live page is YouTube search results and a creator channel row is visible.\n- `Images/youtube_sort_oldest.png`: use only when the live page is a channel Videos tab with sort chips.\n- `Images/youtube_engagement_controls.png`: use only when the live page is a watch page with the engagement toolbar visible.\n- `Images/youtube_share_dialog.png`: despite the filename, use only when verifying a persistent subscribed-state cue on the watch page.\n\nIf no card matches the current screenshot, continue with the text procedure instead of forcing an image match.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues. Neither is a reusable coordinate.\n- Do not copy example creator names, queries, titles, counts, thumbnails, recommendation order, or desktop artifacts from the screenshots.\n- Do not assume the same button order, spacing, or overflow behavior across YouTube layouts.\n- Treat the screenshots as examples of page state, not as proof that a different requested action has completed.\n- The `youtube_share_dialog.png` filename is misleading; rely on the visible UI, not the name.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Channel selection: the visible creator identity matches the requested creator.\n- Sorting: the requested sort chip appears active or the video list refreshes into the intended order.\n- Like: the Like control is visibly selected for the current video.\n- Subscribe: the channel action button changes into a persistent subscribed state.\n- Share or copy link: a share dialog, link-copy confirmation, or another share-specific confirmation is visible.\n\nCompletion requires the exact result requested by the task, not merely any engagement state from the same page.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening an unrelated or sponsored result instead of the requested creator.\n- Picking the first visible video before applying the requested sort.\n- Clicking from the screenshot cue instead of locating the specific live button.\n- Stopping after Subscribe when the task also requires Like or link copying.\n- Treating the subscribed-state image as evidence that sharing or copying already succeeded.",
