      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Passwords and Autofill\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is about Chrome Password Manager rather than general browsing:\n\n- Open the password-management surface from Chrome Settings.\n- Add a password manually or review saved password entries.\n- Confirm that a requested saved credential row or password-manager state is visible.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome is available.\n- Chrome Settings can open the `Autofill and passwords` area.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit detail lives in `state_cards.json`.\n- The compact runtime set for the Agent branch lives in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime should load only the image cards whose `when_to_use` and `visible_cues` match the current screenshot. Do not load every image just because it belongs to this skill.\n- Treat red boxes as action cues and green boxes as state or verification cues.\n- Cards are for recognizing state and checking results, not for reusing coordinates.\n- Some asset filenames are legacy names. Match on the visible UI, not the filename alone.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy example site names, usernames, passwords, notes, or saved-row contents from the screenshots.\n- Do not assume the same row order, search contents, or window geometry across tasks.\n- Transfer only the Chrome surface identity, the relevant controls, and the verification relationship between steps.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Reach `Settings > Autofill and passwords` if Password Manager is not already open. Use `Images/password_manager_surface.png` only as the cue that the broader settings surface is open and the `Password Manager` row is available to enter.\n2. After opening Password Manager, use `Images/add_new_password_dialog.png` only when the live screenshot matches the password list page with the search bar, `Add` button, and saved-password rows.\n3. If the task requires manual entry, open the add-password flow and fill the requested site, username, and password fields. Use `Images/saved_password_entry_visible.png` only as the cue that the dialog fields are populated before submission.\n4. Use `Images/save_password_button.png` only when the live screenshot matches the open `Add new password` dialog and the next step is to commit the entry with `Save`.\n5. After saving, re-check the live Password Manager page and verify the requested credential row or requested password-manager state is actually present.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Final completion is the live Password Manager surface showing the requested saved credential row or other requested password-manager state.\n- A populated add-password dialog is not final success. It only confirms that the form is ready to submit.\n- The broader `Autofill and passwords` settings page is also not final success. It only means the path into Password Manager is available.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Stopping on the `Autofill and passwords` settings page instead of opening Password Manager.\n- Treating a sample saved-password row from the reference image as proof that the current target credential was saved.\n- Clicking `Save` before the live dialog fields contain the intended values.\n- Assuming the credential was stored even though the modal is still open or the live Password Manager list never refreshes to the requested state.",
