      "id": "CHROME_Manage_Web_Store_Extension_Install_And_Permissions",
      "name": "Manage Web Store Extension Install And Permissions",
      "description": "Use chrome://extensions, Chrome Web Store pages, and extension settings surfaces to install an extension from the store or load an unpacked local extension, then verify that the extension or permission state matches the task.",
      "domain": "chrome",
      "domainLabel": "Chrome",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/chrome/CHROME_Manage_Web_Store_Extension_Install_And_Permissions",
      "imageCount": 9,
      "stateCardCount": 4,
      "runtimeCardCount": 4,
      "planStepCount": 9,
      "tags": [
        "web"
      ],
      "overview": "",
      "applicability": [
        "Reach the Chrome Web Store from `chrome://extensions`.",
        "Search for a requested extension and open the correct detail page.",
        "Install an extension with `Add to Chrome`."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Mistaking the `chrome://extensions` page for the Chrome Web Store itself.",
        "Opening the Web Store even though the task clearly requires `Load unpacked` from a local folder.",
        "Selecting the wrong folder for `Load unpacked` instead of the folder that directly contains `manifest.json`."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Web Store Extension Install And Permissions\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task involves installing a Chrome Web Store extension, loading an unpacked local extension, opening the extension's management or permission surface, or verifying a permission value after installation.\n\nTypical fits:\n\n- Reach the Chrome Web Store from `chrome://extensions`.\n- Search for a requested extension and open the correct detail page.\n- Install an extension with `Add to Chrome`.\n- Load an unpacked extension from a local folder that already contains `manifest.json`.\n- Open extension-specific settings or site details and change a requested permission.\n- Verify the final permission value, such as `Block`, `Allow`, or `Ask`.\n\nDo not use this skill for unrelated Chrome settings work, toolbar-only extension usage, or extension tasks that only require clicking the extension icon after it is already installed.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\ndetailed image cards live in `state_cards.json`. The compact runtime set for the Agent branch lives in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\nLoad only the card whose screenshot matches the current Chrome surface. Do not load all image cards by default. The image references below are workflow examples, and the runtime should only use the matching card at the moment it is needed:\n\n- `Images/web_store_search_surface.png`\n- `Images/add_to_chrome_button.png`\n- `Images/extension_install_dialog.png`\n- `Images/extension_permission_state.png`\n\nRed annotations indicate likely interaction targets. Green annotations indicate state or verification cues. Neither should be treated as reusable coordinates.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Start by identifying whether the task is a Web Store install flow or a local unpacked-extension flow.\n2. If the task mentions a local folder, `manifest.json`, or `Load unpacked`, stay on `chrome://extensions`, enable Developer mode if needed, and use the local-extension path instead of going to the Web Store.\n3. For unpacked flows, choose the folder that directly contains `manifest.json`; do not select a parent folder that only contains the extracted project directory.\n4. For Web Store flows, move from `chrome://extensions` into the Web Store, search for the requested extension, and open the matching detail page.\n5. On the store detail page, use `Add to Chrome` only for the requested extension.\n6. If Chrome opens an installation confirmation dialog, review the permission request and confirm only when it matches the task.\n7. After installation, open the extension's details, settings, or site-permission page through `chrome://extensions` or Chrome settings when the task asks for a permission change.\n8. Change only the permission requested by the task.\n9. End only after either the extension tile is visibly installed on `chrome://extensions` or the extension-specific permission surface shows the requested final value.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The extension is installed, not merely visible in Web Store search results.\n- For unpacked flows, the extension appears as a real extension tile on `chrome://extensions`.\n- The browser is on an extension-specific management or settings surface, not a temporary menu.\n- The relevant permission row is visible on the page.\n- The permission control itself shows the requested final value.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Extension names, publishers, ratings, IDs, user counts, and search queries in the screenshots are examples only.\n- Chromium and Chrome may differ in spacing, button placement, or sidebar layout.\n- Some filenames are legacy identifiers and do not literally describe the screenshot contents. Match cards by visible UI state, not by the filename text.\n- Use image cards to recognize the kind of surface and the relevant control or verification cue. Do not reuse coordinates, crops, or copied page text.\n- If the local extension folder is already prepared by the task setup, do not reopen Terminal just to re-check files unless Chrome cannot find the folder.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Mistaking the `chrome://extensions` page for the Chrome Web Store itself.\n- Opening the Web Store even though the task clearly requires `Load unpacked` from a local folder.\n- Selecting the wrong folder for `Load unpacked` instead of the folder that directly contains `manifest.json`.\n- Selecting the first result in the Web Store without checking that it matches the requested extension.\n- Treating the store detail page as proof of installation before Chrome confirms the install.\n- Changing a generic site setting instead of the installed extension's own permission state.\n- Ending on the settings page without checking that the visible dropdown value matches the task request.",
