      "skillMarkdown": "# Navigate Arbitrary Website and Find Target Section\n\n## Overview\n\nUse official-site results, site-specific navigation shortcuts, and in-site section or item links to reach the requested page on an arbitrary website and verify that the final section or destination page is visibly open.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Browsing from a website home page to a target section\n- Opening a target item or subsection through site navigation\n- Verifying that the requested site section is visibly open\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target site or page is known.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark action targets.\n- Green boxes mark verification or recovery signals.\n\n## Procedures\n\n### website_nav\n\n#### reach_target_site\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to reach an arbitrary website and land on the requested section or page\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on the target website and its internal navigation controls\n- Action: Advance Chrome through the `reach_target_site` subgoal until the requested section, article, FAQ entry, or product page is visibly open.\n- Image: `Images/official_site_result.png`\n\n#### open_local_navigation\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to reach an arbitrary website and land on the requested section or page\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on the target website and its internal navigation controls\n- Action: Advance Chrome through the `open_local_navigation` subgoal until the requested section, article, FAQ entry, or product page is visibly open.\n- Image: `Images/site_books_navigation.png`\n\n#### choose_target_section\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to reach an arbitrary website and land on the requested section or page\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on the target website and its internal navigation controls\n- Action: Advance Chrome through the `choose_target_section` subgoal until the requested section, article, FAQ entry, or product page is visibly open.\n\n#### Expected Result: verify_target_section\n\n- Trigger: The workflow still needs to reach an arbitrary website and land on the requested section or page\n- Visual grounding: Relevant controls on the target website and its internal navigation controls\n- Action: Advance Chrome through the `verify_target_section` subgoal until the requested section, article, FAQ entry, or product page is visibly open.\n- Image: `Images/target_book_page_visible.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Stopping on a search engine shortcut instead of verifying the final in-site page.\n- Choosing an official site correctly but then drifting into the wrong subsection.\n- Treating a list or discovery page as the final destination when the requested item page is still unopened.\n\n## Runtime Assets\n\n- `state_cards.json` carries the richer multiview authoring bundle.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` carries the slimmer runtime-facing card set.",
