      "skillMarkdown": "# Navigate Google News and Search Topics\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is to reach Google News in Chrome, browse a category, search for a news topic, open an article from the Google News feed, or confirm that the correct Google News or article surface is visible.\n\nTypical fits:\n- Start from a Google homepage or Chromium new tab and open Google News.\n- Switch from the Google apps launcher into the News service.\n- Search for a topic or browse Google News categories.\n- Open a specific article from the results or feed.\n- Confirm that bookmarking or another follow-on action is happening on the intended article page.\n\nDo not use this skill for general web search outside Google News, for article interactions that do not begin from the News surface, or for browser settings flows unrelated to news navigation.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chromium or Chrome is available.\n- Google pages can load in the current browser session.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. If the browser is on a Google homepage or new tab, use the Google apps launcher to reach Google News.\n   - Matching image card: `Images/google_apps_menu_open.png`\n2. If the Google apps launcher is already open, click the News tile.\n   - Matching image card: `Images/click_news_icon.png`\n3. When Google News loads, either:\n   - type the requested topic into the search field and submit, or\n   - choose the requested category tab from the News surface.\n   - Matching image card: `Images/search_query_entered.png`\n4. From the feed or search results, click the requested article headline.\n   - Matching image card: `Images/click_article_headline.png`\n5. If the task continues inside the article, perform the requested follow-on action there, such as confirming a bookmark destination.\n   - Matching image card: `Images/bookmark_dialog_folder_selection.png`\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill stays text-first. Treat the image cards as optional grounding aids for the current screenshot, not as the primary instruction source.\n\n- detailed version: `state_cards.json`\n- Runtime version for the Agent branch: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nLoad only the image card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screen. If no screenshot matches, continue from the text procedure instead of forcing a visual match.\n\nRed boxes indicate interaction targets. Green boxes indicate state or verification cues. They are not reusable coordinates.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy literal search terms, article headlines, dates, weather details, folder names, account labels, or feed ordering from the screenshots unless the current task explicitly asks for them.\n- Do not assume the same theme, bookmark bar, signed-in state, or launcher tile arrangement.\n- Use each image to recognize a UI state transition, not to memorize pixel positions.\n- `search_query_entered.png` is a Google News ready-state image even though its filename suggests a completed query.\n- `google_apps_menu_open.png` is a pre-click launcher image even though its filename suggests the menu is already open.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nUse the task as complete only when the relevant visible result is present:\n\n- Google News opened successfully: the News header, search field, and populated article sections are visible.\n- Topic or category navigation is ready: the News surface is loaded and the requested search or browsing control is available.\n- Article opened successfully: the browser leaves the feed view and loads the article page.\n- Bookmarking verification: the bookmark confirmation bubble is visible and the selected folder matches the requested destination.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Clicking the apps launcher from a non-Google page where the expected Google controls are absent.\n- Confusing the pre-click launcher icon image with the launcher-open panel image.\n- Treating the Google News home surface as proof that a requested topic search already ran.\n- Clicking a headline preview from the wrong card or publisher because the feed refreshed.\n- Accepting the example bookmark folder or article title instead of the current task's requested target.\n\n## Notes For Runtime Loading\n\nThe runtime should load only the matching entries from `runtime_state_cards.json`. `state_cards.json` remains the fuller detailed reference file for reviewing image-specific cues, transfer limits, evidence lineage, and review rationale.",
