      "skillMarkdown": "# Open Google Maps and Inspect Place Details\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is to find a place inside Google Maps and stop once the place profile is visibly open.\n\n- Search for a place by name in Google Maps.\n- Open the place detail panel, review surface, or place profile from search.\n- Confirm that the requested place has loaded before taking follow-up actions such as reading reviews or copying a link.\n\nDo not use this skill for route planning, category browsing without a named place, or generic Chrome web search outside Google Maps.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome can load Google Maps.\n- The target place name or identifying text is already known.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill is text-first. Use the procedure below as the default workflow, and load image cards only when the current screenshot plausibly matches the state you need.\n\n- `state_cards.json` is the full detailed version with detailed transfer limits and evidence notes.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` is the compact version intended for runtime branch loading.\n- Load only the matching image card at runtime rather than all images at once.\n- Red boxes mark interaction cues. Green boxes mark verification cues. Neither is a reusable coordinate.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\nTransfer the UI state, not the example content.\n\n- The example place name, rating, review count, sponsored modules, map location, and suggestion ordering are not reusable instructions.\n- Google Maps layouts can vary by place type, signed-in state, language, and experiment flags.\n- Use the cards to recognize search-box state, suggestion-list state, and detail-panel state.\n- If the current screenshot disagrees with a card's visible cues, ignore that card and continue with text guidance or a different matching card.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### 1. Reach the Google Maps search state\n\n- Open Google Maps in Chrome.\n- If the page is idle and ready for input, the matching reference image is `Images/maps_search_box_ready.png`.\n- Focus the search field at the top left.\n\n### 2. Enter the requested place and select the correct suggestion\n\n- Type the requested place name into the Maps search field.\n- When the autocomplete list appears, identify the suggestion that matches the requested place.\n- The matching reference image for this operation state is `Images/maps_place_suggestion.png`.\n- Select the matching place suggestion row.\n\n### 3. Verify that the place detail panel is open\n\n- Wait for the left panel to switch from suggestions to a place profile.\n- The verification reference image is `Images/maps_place_detail_panel.png`.\n- Confirm that the panel shows the intended place with a stable place-detail layout such as a title, rating line, tabs, or action buttons.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nTreat the skill as complete only when the place-detail surface is visibly open.\n\n- The left panel shows a specific place profile rather than the search suggestions list.\n- The panel contains the requested place identity, not just the typed query.\n- Persistent place metadata is visible, such as a title, rating line, photo header, or place-level tabs.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Typing the place name but never selecting a suggestion.\n- Selecting a suggestion that matches only part of the requested place name.\n- Stopping on the raw map view before the place-detail panel loads.\n- Mistaking a temporary search list for the final place profile.",
