      "skillMarkdown": "# Perform Reverse Image Search Or Image Download\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task in Chrome is to:\n\n- start reverse image search from a Google or Google Lens surface\n- upload a local image or paste an image link into Lens\n- inspect visual matches, exact matches, products, or similar result cards\n- open a requested source from those matches and verify the correct surface is visible\n\nThis package is strongest on the reverse-image-search branch. If the task later moves into a native save dialog or another browser-download surface, keep following the text workflow, but do not expect image cards here to cover that native dialog.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Chrome is open.\n- The image file exists locally if the task requires upload.\n- The task allows using Google or Google Lens as the lookup surface.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit reference: `state_cards.json`\n- Agent branch prompt-budget reference: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nLoad only the image card whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot. Do not load every card just because the task mentions reverse image search.\n\n- `Images/visual_search_entry_surface.png` is the entry cue for a Google surface that still has an image-search trigger.\n- `Images/image_upload_dialog.png` is the in-browser Lens upload panel.\n- `Images/matching_visual_result.png` is only supplemental evidence that Chrome is in the Lens upload flow; it is not a completion image.\n- `Images/matching_source_page.png` is the strongest verification image in this package because it shows the visual-results surface with candidate matches.\n\nRed boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues. Neither color is a reusable coordinate.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Reach a Google surface that exposes image search.\n   - Look for the image-search trigger shown in `Images/visual_search_entry_surface.png`.\n   - If the current page has no image-search entry, navigate to a Google search surface that does.\n\n2. Open the Lens upload surface and submit the image.\n   - Match `Images/image_upload_dialog.png`.\n   - Use the upload option that fits the task: choose a local file or paste an image link.\n\n3. Wait for the reverse-image-search flow to advance.\n   - If the browser only shows a `lens.google.com` upload-style URL and no stable results yet, that matches the transitional evidence in `Images/matching_visual_result.png`.\n   - Do not stop there; continue until visible matches or the requested source page appears.\n\n4. Inspect visual matches and open the needed result.\n   - Use the loaded results surface in `Images/matching_source_page.png` as the primary verification cue that Lens has processed the image.\n   - Open the requested source, merchant, or exact match from that verified state.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not transfer the example product, seller names, prices, URLs, or result ordering.\n- Do not transfer the example wallpaper theme, browser shortcuts, or screenshot framing.\n- Do not treat boxed regions as fixed click coordinates.\n- The presence of a Google Lens surface transfers; the specific image subject in the example does not.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nTreat the task as verified only when the current screen shows the right level of completion for the user request:\n\n- For \"start reverse image search\" or \"show matches\" requests, verify the Google-hosted results surface with the submitted-image preview and visible candidate matches.\n- For \"open a source page\" requests, do not stop at the results grid; verify that the downstream page itself is open.\n- For upload steps, do not claim success while the Lens upload panel is still waiting for input.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- The current page is a generic tab or homepage with no usable image-search trigger.\n- The Lens upload panel is open, but the image has not been submitted yet.\n- Chrome is on a Lens upload URL, but the results surface has not rendered; this is only a transition state.\n- The results grid is visible, but the requested external source page has not been opened yet.\n\n## Notes For Runtime Use\n\n- Keep this skill text-first. Use images to disambiguate state, not to replace the procedure.\n- Runtime should load only the matching image card from `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- `state_cards.json` remains the fuller detailed reference file with transfer limits, evidence lineage, and review rationale.",
