      "skillMarkdown": "# Save Or Print Page To PDF With Exact Options\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the current goal is to produce a PDF from the page already open in Chrome and the task may require exact print or save settings such as destination, margins, layout, pages, or filename and location.\n\nTypical fits:\n\n- Save the current page as a PDF.\n- Open Chrome print preview and switch output to PDF.\n- Use a site-native `Download as PDF` action when the page provides one.\n- Confirm the PDF filename and destination before the final save.\n\nDo not use this skill for non-PDF downloads, screenshots, or workflows that have already moved out of Chrome into another app's export flow.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed image cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- The runtime should load only the card or cards whose visible cues match the live screenshot. Do not load every image card by default.\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are verification cues. Neither is a reusable coordinate map.\n- If no image matches well, continue from the text procedure and wait for a closer state instead of forcing an image match.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy example page titles, selected text, article subjects, filenames, folders, drive letters, or menu placement.\n- Treat site-native PDF export as optional and site-specific. If the current site does not expose a comparable export item, use the browser print route instead.\n- An open save dialog is only a readiness check. It does not prove the file has already been saved.\n- Use red and green boxes only to recognize the relevant control or verification signal in the live UI.\n\n## Matching Image Cards\n\n- `Images/browser_print_dialog.png`: page context menu with `Print...` available.\n- `Images/site_pdf_export_page.png`: site-native tools/export menu with `Download as PDF`.\n- `Images/pdf_save_dialog.png`: Chrome print preview ready to save as PDF.\n- `Images/pdf_save_state.png`: system save dialog showing a `.pdf` filename.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Reach a PDF-export surface.\n   - If the page or Chrome context menu exposes `Print...`, follow the browser print path shown by `Images/browser_print_dialog.png`.\n   - If the site exposes its own `Download as PDF` or comparable export action, use that path instead, as shown by `Images/site_pdf_export_page.png`.\n\n2. Confirm PDF output options before saving.\n   - In Chrome print preview, ensure the output is PDF and adjust any task-specific options before committing the save.\n   - Match `Images/pdf_save_dialog.png` only when the preview sidebar and PDF save action are both visible.\n\n3. Confirm the save target.\n   - In the system save dialog, set or verify the requested folder and filename, keeping the `.pdf` extension.\n   - Match `Images/pdf_save_state.png` only when the dialog is clearly a PDF save dialog.\n\n4. Finish the workflow.\n   - Use the final save action only after the visible filename, destination, and any requested print options match the current task.\n   - Completion is the correct ready-to-save state followed by the final save, or the dialog closing with the save committed.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Chrome print preview or the site export flow clearly targets PDF output.\n- The save dialog shows a `.pdf` filename and the intended destination.\n- Any user-requested print option is visibly set before the final save.\n- After the final save, the dialog closes or the saved file appears in the requested location.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Using the site-export card on a page that does not actually offer native PDF export.\n- Leaving print destination on a physical printer instead of PDF.\n- Clicking `Save` in print preview before checking requested margins or other print settings.\n- Reusing the example filename or folder from the screenshot instead of the task's requested values.\n- Treating the open file-save dialog as proof of completion before the final save is executed.",
