      "skillMarkdown": "# Select Product Offer Or Result And Complete Cart Or Wishlist Action\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill to move from a qualifying commerce result or product offer to a completed add-to-cart or save action in Chrome. The skill is complete only when the site shows a visible confirmation that the item was added or saved.\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\n- A commerce results page, product page, or offer card is already open in Chrome.\n- The item constraints are already known from the task or previous steps.\n- The next objective is to choose the correct result and trigger Add to Cart, Save, Add to List, or an equivalent merchant-specific control.\n- Success must be verified from the page state, not assumed from the click.\n\nDo not use this skill for checkout completion, account sign-in, or broad product discovery when the relevant commerce surface is not open yet.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- A commerce result list or product page is already open.\n- The qualifying product constraints are already known.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed image cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- The compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the card or cards whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot. Do not load every image by default.\n- Treat red boxes as interaction cues and green boxes as verification cues. They show what kind of UI element matters; they are not reusable coordinates.\n- If a card's `when_not_to_use` applies, fall back to the text procedure or another matching card.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the state pattern, not the example merchant details.\n- Product names, prices, filters, delivery text, ratings, subtotal values, and recommendation content are example-bound unless the live task explicitly asks for them.\n- The screenshots come from Amazon layouts, but the skill should transfer to other commerce sites that expose the same result-list, product-page, and post-action confirmation states.\n- Do not assume that the button position, wording, or page column layout will match the example image.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nLook for a durable success state tied to the selected item before ending the skill:\n\n- an `Added to cart` or equivalent success message\n- a saved or listed state indicator\n- a cart-count or cart-summary change that clearly follows the action\n- a confirmation panel or region that references the selected item\n\nTransient hover states, unchanged product pages, or generic upsell panels are not enough.\n\n## Procedures\n\n### commerce_selection\n\n#### State 1: open_candidate_offer\n\nWhen to use:\n- The correct results page is already filtered and the product still needs to be chosen.\n- Matching image reference: `Images/commerce_result_add_to_cart.png`\n\nAction:\n- Open the qualifying product card or use its visible inline add-to-cart control.\n\n#### State 2: trigger_cart_action\n\nWhen to use:\n- The qualifying product page or offer card is already open.\n- Matching image reference: `Images/commerce_product_add_to_cart_button.png`\n\nAction:\n- Click the primary add-to-cart or save control for the chosen product.\n\n#### State 3: verify_cart_confirmation\n\nWhen to use:\n- The cart or save action has already been triggered.\n- Matching image reference: `Images/commerce_cart_confirmation.png`\n\nAction:\n- Verify the visible add-to-cart or saved-state confirmation before continuing.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Acting on a result that no longer matches the requested constraints.\n- Clicking Buy Now, Proceed to checkout, or another adjacent purchase control instead of the requested add/save control.\n- Leaving the page before a durable success signal appears.\n- Treating merchant-specific example details as reusable instructions.",
