      "id": "GIMP_GIMP_Capture_Screenshots_and_Sample_Colors",
      "name": "GIMP_GIMP_Capture_Screenshots_and_Sample_Colors",
      "description": "Capture a screenshot as a new image in GIMP and sample a visible color into the foreground color slot when the task calls for it.",
      "domain": "gimp",
      "domainLabel": "GIMP",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/gimp/GIMP_GIMP_Capture_Screenshots_and_Sample_Colors",
      "imageCount": 7,
      "stateCardCount": 3,
      "runtimeCardCount": 3,
      "planStepCount": 7,
      "tags": [
        "images"
      ],
      "overview": "Use this skill when a task stays inside GIMP and needs one or both of these outcomes:",
      "applicability": [
        "GIMP is already running.",
        "The task explicitly wants GIMP to perform the screenshot capture, not an external screenshot utility.",
        "The screen or image region to capture is already visible or will be visible when the capture runs."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Confirming the wrong screenshot scope because the dialog settings were not checked before capture.",
        "Assuming capture succeeded while the Screenshot dialog is still open or before a new image appears.",
        "Sampling from the wrong nearby pixel and trusting the result without checking the foreground color swatch or picker readout."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_Capture_Screenshots_and_Sample_Colors\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when a task stays inside GIMP and needs one or both of these outcomes:\n\n- capture the current screen into a new GIMP image\n- sample a visible pixel so the foreground color and picker readout reflect that pixel\n\nThis is a text-first OSWorld skill. Use the procedure text first, and only load image cards whose visible cues match the current GIMP screen.\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\n- GIMP is already running.\n- The task explicitly wants GIMP to perform the screenshot capture, not an external screenshot utility.\n- The screen or image region to capture is already visible or will be visible when the capture runs.\n- A color must be sampled from visible pixels rather than typed in from a known value.\n\nDo not use this skill for generic file import, manual color entry, or screenshots taken outside GIMP.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Full detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime should load only the card or cards whose `when_to_use` and `visible_cues` match the current GIMP surface.\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues.\n- The boxes help identify equivalent UI parts; they are not reusable coordinates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/screenshot_dialog.png`\n- `Images/captured_screenshot_loaded.png`\n- `Images/theme_color_sampled.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy exact coordinates, box placement, or pixel positions from the example screenshots.\n- Do not copy example-only values such as the shown delay, document title, resolution, RGB numbers, or hex color.\n- Do not treat the captured desktop contents, wallpaper, dock icons, or time display as required outputs.\n- Reuse the UI relationship instead: dialog before capture, loaded screenshot after capture, picker readout plus updated foreground swatch after sampling.\n\n## Procedure 1: Capture The Current Screen\n\nWhen to use:\n\n- The task needs the current screen to become a new image inside GIMP.\n\nSteps:\n\n1. Open or focus GIMP's Screenshot dialog.\n2. Confirm the capture settings that fit the live task.\n3. Trigger the capture from the dialog.\n4. Verify that GIMP returns to the editor with a newly opened screenshot image in the canvas.\n\nMatching image cards:\n\n- Entry / action cue: `Images/screenshot_dialog.png`\n- Expected result: `Images/captured_screenshot_loaded.png`\n\n## Procedure 2: Sample A Visible Color\n\nWhen to use:\n\n- The task needs a visible pixel from the screenshot or another open image to become the active foreground color.\n\nSteps:\n\n1. Make sure the target image is visible in the canvas.\n2. Use color picking on the intended visible region.\n3. Check that GIMP reports the sampled color and updates the foreground color swatch.\n\nMatching image card:\n\n- Verification cue: `Images/theme_color_sampled.png`\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Screenshot capture is complete when a new image is open in GIMP and the captured screen is visible in the canvas.\n- Color sampling is complete when picker feedback is present and the live foreground color swatch reflects the sampled pixel.\n- If the current screen does not match any loaded runtime card, fall back to the text procedure and wait for a matching state before declaring success.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Confirming the wrong screenshot scope because the dialog settings were not checked before capture.\n- Assuming capture succeeded while the Screenshot dialog is still open or before a new image appears.\n- Sampling from the wrong nearby pixel and trusting the result without checking the foreground color swatch or picker readout.\n- Treating the example's displayed numbers or screenshot contents as values that must be reproduced in a different environment.",
