      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_GIMP_Configure_Shortcuts_and_Interface_Behavior\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this family when the task is about:\n\n- keyboard shortcut lookup or assignment;\n- minimum undo levels or closely related undo-history counts;\n- toolbox submenu behavior such as show-on-click vs show-on-hover;\n- enabling or disabling interface-behavior toggles such as editing on non-visible layers.\n\nDo not use it for theme selection or image precision/profile changes.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The correct Preferences or shortcut-editor surface is open for the requested behavior.\n- The requested toggle, undo count, dropdown choice, or binding is visibly set.\n- The change is confirmed before leaving the modal surface.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the top menu stays open but Preferences is not yet visible, reopen `Edit` -> `Preferences` and verify the left settings tree before typing into any field.\n- For undo-level tasks, ignore nearby cache and memory settings until the `Minimum number of undo levels` field itself is active.\n- After changing a numeric value or toggle, confirm the Preferences dialog instead of reopening menus and repeating the same edit.",
