      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_GIMP_Convert_Image_Modes_Palettes_and_Precision\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this family for indexed and palette conversion only:\n\n- switch to Indexed mode;\n- set maximum colors or palette choice;\n- enable or adjust dithering behavior.\n\nDo not use it for precision, gamma, or color-profile conversion. Those belong to `GIMP_GIMP_Manage_Image_Precision_Gamma_and_Color_Profiles`.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The active modal is `Indexed Color Conversion`, not a precision or profile surface.\n- The requested palette-size, colormap, and dithering choices are visible together before conversion is confirmed.\n- Once the dialog is configured, convert immediately instead of reopening `Image` menus and repeating the same mode-selection step.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the workflow lands on a precision, gamma, or profile surface, back out and return to the indexed conversion path rather than forcing palette logic onto the wrong dialog.\n- If the dialog closes without a visible indexed/palette confirmation step, reopen the indexed conversion dialog and verify the requested values before confirming again.",
