      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_Create_and_Style_Text_Layers\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use this skill when text must be added to an image or canvas with the GIMP Text tool.\n- Use it when the task includes entering text and adjusting visible text properties such as size, color, bold, italic, or similar font treatment.\n- Keep this skill focused on text-layer creation and styling. Use a different skill for movement-heavy layer repositioning, masking, or unrelated image edits.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- A target image or blank canvas is already open in GIMP.\n- The requested text content is known.\n- The intended appearance is known well enough to verify the result on the canvas.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed image cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the image card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screenshot. Do not load unrelated cards just because they belong to the same skill.\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues.\n- The cards are for recognition and verification, not for reusable coordinates.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the workflow, not the example text, portrait subject, placement, font family, size value, color swatch, layer name, or canvas geometry.\n- Treat boxed regions as cues for the equivalent control or result in the current screenshot.\n- If a task asks for additional effects beyond ordinary text entry and styling, verify whether another skill should handle that separate operation.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### 1. Create the text region\n\nUse this state when no editable text region exists yet.\n\nImage reference: `Images/text_region_drawn.png`\n\n- Activate the Text tool if needed.\n- Drag out a text region in the requested area of the image.\n- Continue only after an editable text box is visible on the canvas.\n\n### 2. Enter the text content\n\nUse this state when the text region is active and ready for typing.\n\nImage reference: `Images/text_content_entered.png`\n\n- Type the requested text into the active text region.\n- Keep the text layer active while entering content so later styling applies to the text layer instead of the image background.\n\n### 3. Style the active text layer\n\nUse this state when the text is already present and its appearance still needs adjustment.\n\nImage reference: `Images/styled_text_layer.png`\n\n- Adjust the active text layer's size, color, and requested font treatment.\n- Verify the visible text on the canvas, not only the numeric controls.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The requested text is visible on the canvas.\n- The text layer is clearly active or selected while styling is applied.\n- The visible result matches the requested appearance better than the default inserted text.\n- Use `runtime_state_cards.json` for lightweight runtime matching and `state_cards.json` when auditing, debugging, or revising the skill.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Typing before a text region exists.\n- Styling the background layer instead of the text layer.\n- Treating example text, placement, or color as defaults for unrelated tasks.\n- Folding separate layer movement or compositing work into this skill when the task has already moved beyond text entry and styling.",
