      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_GIMP_Move_Text_Or_Object_Layers_Without_Selecting_Background_Content\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task is to reposition text or object content without shifting the base image. It fits duplicate-layer moves, isolated object moves, and text-layer moves where the wrong active layer would move the background or another sibling layer instead.\n\nUse a different skill when the task is to move the whole image, scale or rotate content, or create the duplicate layer itself.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The content to move already exists on its own layer.\n- The layer stack is visible or can be opened.\n- GIMP can switch to the Move tool.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. In the Layers panel, make the intended text, duplicate, or object layer the active layer.\n2. Activate the Move tool.\n3. If Tool Options expose a movement target choice, keep the move scoped to the active layer rather than \"pick a layer or guide\".\n4. Drag on the canvas to reposition only that active layer.\n4. Stop when the layer reaches the requested location and the base image has not shifted.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the background moves instead of the text or object, undo immediately, reselect the intended layer row in the Layers dock, and only then retry the drag.\n- If clicking the canvas keeps re-targeting the wrong object, use the Layers dock as the source of truth for which layer is active before moving again.\n- If a different transform tool is active, switch back to Move before dragging. Do not continue from Scale, Rotate, or Unified Transform.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\ndetailed cards live in `state_cards.json`. Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\nLoad only the card whose screenshot plausibly matches the current GIMP state:\n\n- `Images/target_layer_prepared.png`: use when checking that the correct non-background layer is active before any move.\n- `Images/move_tool_selected.png`: use when checking that the Move tool is active and the selected layer is ready to drag.\n- `Images/active_layer_repositioned.png`: use when verifying that only the intended layer moved to its new position.\n\nIf the current screenshot does not resemble a card, continue from the text procedure rather than forcing an image match.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues from the example image, not reusable coordinates.\n- Green boxes are state or verification cues, not required screen geometry.\n- Do not copy example layer names, subject matter, dialog contents, or destination coordinates from the screenshots.\n- One screenshot includes an unrelated layer-mask dialog. For this skill, only transfer the fact that the intended non-background layer is selected in the Layers panel.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nTreat the move as complete only when both of these are true:\n\n- The intended text or object layer is the layer that moved.\n- The base image stayed fixed while the moved layer reached the task-requested location.\n- If the task is directional rather than absolute, verify the moved layer shifted in the requested direction instead of matching the example screenshot's destination.\n\n`Images/active_layer_repositioned.png` is the best reference for this final check. Runtime should load only its matching card, not all image cards at once.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Dragging before the correct layer is active, which moves the wrong layer or the background.\n- Using a transform tool other than Move, which changes size or orientation instead of position.\n- Verifying against the example screenshot's exact placement instead of the destination requested by the current task.\n\n## Image References In Procedure Context\n\n- Prepare target layer: `Images/target_layer_prepared.png`\n- Confirm Move tool state: `Images/move_tool_selected.png`\n- Verify moved-layer result: `Images/active_layer_repositioned.png`",
