      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_Open_GIMP_Help_and_Tutorials\n\n## Overview\n\nOpen the official GIMP documentation or tutorial page for a named topic. Use this skill when the requested outcome is learning material, not an edited image.\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\n- The user asks for help, documentation, an introduction, or a tutorial about a GIMP concept.\n- The task should end on a readable documentation page for the requested topic.\n- Opening a help surface or browser page is allowed.\n\nDo not use this skill when the user wants the edit performed directly inside GIMP.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- GIMP is available.\n- The topic to look up is known.\n- A browser or help surface can be opened.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### Open The Requested Tutorial Page\n\n1. Route from GIMP into its help or documentation flow instead of starting an image-editing operation.\n2. Confirm that the workflow has opened the official GIMP documentation surface in a browser or help window.\n3. Continue navigating until the page for the requested topic is open.\n4. Stop only when the visible page is the requested topic page, not just the generic documentation landing page.\n\nImage references used by this procedure:\n\n- `Images/help_menu_route.png`\n- `Images/named_tutorial_page.png`\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit-level image cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime should load only the card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screen. Do not preload unrelated cards just because they belong to the same skill.\n- Use `Images/help_menu_route.png` only to recognize the intermediate documentation landing state.\n- Use `Images/named_tutorial_page.png` only to verify that the requested topic page itself is open.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues and green boxes are state-verification cues.\n- Boxed regions are not reusable coordinates.\n- Browser theme, tab order, window geometry, zoom level, and scroll position are not transferable.\n- The example topic name visible in an image is sample-specific. Replace it with the current requested topic at runtime.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Intermediate verification: the official GIMP documentation site is open in a browser or help window.\n- Final verification: the page heading names the requested topic and the article body below it belongs to that same topic page.\n- If only the generic docs landing page is visible, the task is not complete.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Treating a learning request as an image-editing request.\n- Stopping after the docs site opens without opening the requested topic page.\n- Mistaking an index, search result, or unrelated web page for the final tutorial page.",
