      "skillMarkdown": "# GIMP_Print_Images_with_Page_Setup\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task is about printing the current image from GIMP and the important outcome is a correct paper-oriented setup, not file export.\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The user asks to print the current image from GIMP.\n- The task mentions paper size, orientation, copies, scaling, page setup, or print preview.\n- The correct end state is a ready-to-confirm Print dialog with the requested settings visible.\n\nDo not use this skill for export-only requests such as PNG, JPEG, PDF export, or Save As workflows.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- A target image is already open in GIMP.\n- The requested print settings are known or can be read from the task.\n- GIMP's own Print dialog is available in the current environment.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis package includes two card files:\n\n- `state_cards.json`: full detailed cards with detailed transfer limits and grounding notes.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json`: compact cards for runtime loading in the Agent branch.\n\nLoad only the card or cards whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot. The images are examples of reusable UI states, not a sequence that must always be loaded all at once.\n\n- `Images/print_dialog_open.png`: entry cue that the GIMP Print dialog is open.\n- `Images/page_setup_tab_active.png`: operation cue that Page Setup is active and paper controls are visible.\n- `Images/print_settings_ready.png`: verification cue that print settings are in place and the dialog is ready for preview or confirmation.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Treat red boxes as interaction cues and green boxes as state or verification cues only.\n- Never reuse boxed regions as fixed coordinates.\n- Do not copy example-specific paper sizes, orientation values, scale values, filenames, page counts, or printer defaults unless the live task asks for the same values.\n- Ignore incidental image content behind the dialog; the transferable part is the print UI state.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Confirm that the task is about printing, not exporting.\n2. Enter or continue in GIMP's Print dialog.\n3. If paper or layout settings are required, move to `Page Setup` and adjust the relevant controls for the current task.\n4. Re-check the visible selections and preview area before confirming with `Print Preview` or `Print`, depending on what the task requires.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The Print dialog is still open and no longer in the untouched entry state.\n- The relevant paper-oriented fields visible in the dialog match the current task request.\n- A confirmation affordance such as `Print Preview` or `Print` is available once setup is complete.\n- When using image cards at runtime, prefer the verification card only after the requested settings have already been applied.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening an export flow instead of GIMP's Print dialog.\n- Stopping on the `General` tab when the task requires paper size or orientation changes from `Page Setup`.\n- Accepting the example values shown in a screenshot instead of checking the live values requested by the task.\n- Treating a visible confirmation button as proof that setup is correct without reading the current paper and layout fields.",
