      "skillMarkdown": "# Apply Revenue Cost Discount Profit Formulas\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task explicitly names revenue, cost, profit, discount, unit price, gross profit, or another business-style derived metric.\n- Use when the main difficulty is choosing the right source columns and producing a filled output column, not merely typing a generic one-off formula.\n- This is the preferred main path for profit and revenue cases that later branch into reporting, pivot, or chart steps.\n\n## When Not To Use\n\n- Do not use as the main planner for pure keyed lookups or reference-table retrieval. Use `LIBREOFFICECALC_Lookup_Reference_and_Keyed_Fill_Formulas`.\n- Do not use for formatting-only tasks, page setup, or pure chart creation after the calculations already exist.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Confirm the requested output header or output column name before entering the first formula.\n2. Identify the exact source columns used by the business relation for the first row.\n3. Enter the first business-metric formula in the destination cell.\n4. Verify the first result:\n   - the formula is under the correct output header,\n   - the visible source columns match the task,\n   - the arithmetic relation is plausible for the row.\n5. Fill the formula only through the requested output range.\n6. Re-check the finished output column on the sheet before starting any later pivot, chart, highlight, or save step.\n\n## Verification Focus\n\n- Verify the target column header itself, not just the active formula cell.\n- Spot-check one filled cell lower in the column so relative references did not shift.\n- If a source value comes from another sheet but is still a direct arithmetic dependency, verify the sheet-qualified reference before fill-down.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the business relation is wrong on the first row, stop and repair that formula before filling the range.\n- If the result appears in the wrong column, move back to the requested output header and restart from the first destination cell.\n- If the task turns out to be a keyed table lookup rather than direct metric arithmetic, switch to the lookup skill.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Runtime cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Match only the card that fits the current live Calc surface.\n\nImage references in this package:\n\n- `Images/first_revenue_formula_entry.png`\n- `Images/first_revenue_formula_entry_focus_crop.png`\n- `Images/discount_rate_values_visible.png`\n- `Images/discount_rate_values_visible_focus_crop.png`\n- `Images/filled_revenue_output_column.png`\n- `Images/filled_revenue_output_column_focus_crop.png`",
