      "skillMarkdown": "# Build Merged Report Headers and Multi Row Layouts\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task asks to merge and center report headers, merge named cell spans, or handle hidden-cell content while merging.\n- Use when the merged result is part of a broader report layout that must remain visually intact afterward.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The exact range to merge is known from the task.\n- If non-empty cells are involved, the required hidden-cell behavior is known before clicking through the warning.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Use this card when the report header cells are selected and the next step is to merge the intended span.\n2. Use this card when Calc warns that some cells in the merge range are not empty and the task depends on keeping, moving, or clearing hidden contents correctly.\n3. Compare the visible merged span and header text against the current task, then confirm nearby report structure was not broken by the merge.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed review cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose screenshot actually matches the live Calc surface.\n- Image references in this package:\n  - `Images/merge_cells_hidden_content_option.png`\n  - `Images/merge_cells_hidden_content_option_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/merged_header_text_visible.png`\n  - `Images/merged_header_text_visible_before.png`\n  - `Images/merged_header_text_visible_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/selected_header_merge_span.png`\n  - `Images/selected_header_merge_span_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Merging the wrong span because the selection drifted before the command.\n- Clicking through the hidden-cell warning without checking whether contents should be cleared or preserved.\n- Assuming the merge succeeded without verifying the visible header span on the worksheet.",
