      "skillMarkdown": "# Conditional Formatting and Placeholder Handling\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task explicitly asks for conditional formatting, gradients, data bars, color scales, or placeholder handling such as #N/A.\n- Use when the workflow depends on dialog-level rule setup rather than only direct on-sheet styling.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target range and rule logic are known before opening the conditional-formatting surface.\n- The task specifies the comparison value, style family, or placeholder treatment that should be applied.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Use this card when conditional formatting is being authored and the first need is to confirm the right target range and comparison operator.\n2. Use this card when the conditional rule compares against a literal placeholder or token and the value field still needs to be filled correctly.\n3. Use this card when the conditional rule logic is already defined and the next branch is selecting the style family or visual treatment.\n4. Check that the rule-hit cells on the live sheet show the requested styling effect and that non-matching cells were not unintentionally changed.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed review cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose screenshot actually matches the live Calc surface.\n- Image references in this package:\n  - `Images/apply_style_dropdown_open.png`\n  - `Images/apply_style_dropdown_open_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/conditional_rule_equal_to_dialog.png`\n  - `Images/conditional_rule_equal_to_dialog_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/placeholder_value_hash_na.png`\n  - `Images/placeholder_value_hash_na_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/rule_match_highlight_result.png`\n  - `Images/rule_match_highlight_result_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Applying a direct fill instead of authoring a conditional rule.\n- Typing the comparison value incorrectly, especially placeholder text such as #N/A.\n- Stopping at the dialog without checking the visible styled result on the sheet.",
