      "skillMarkdown": "# Enable Data Validation Dropdowns and Allowed Values\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task asks for a dropdown list, validation rule, or allowed-values constraint on one or more cells.\n- Use when the actual completion gate is that the cell behaves like a dropdown after the dialog is confirmed.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target cell or range is selected before opening Data > Validity.\n- The exact allowed values or validation criteria are known.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Use this card when the destination cell is selected and the next step is to open Calc's validation dialog from the Data menu.\n2. Use this card when the Validity dialog is already open on the Criteria tab and the dropdown criteria still need to be configured.\n3. Check that the dropdown opens from the intended target cell and that its visible choices match the task's allowed values exactly.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed review cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose screenshot actually matches the live Calc surface.\n- Image references in this package:\n  - `Images/data_menu_validity_entry.png`\n  - `Images/data_menu_validity_entry_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/validated_dropdown_choices_visible.png`\n  - `Images/validated_dropdown_choices_visible_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/validity_dialog_list_entries.png`\n  - `Images/validity_dialog_list_entries_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening Validity for the wrong cell after losing the selection.\n- Leaving Allow on the wrong criteria type or typing list entries with the wrong separators.\n- Stopping after clicking OK without confirming the cell actually exposes the dropdown choices.",
