      "skillMarkdown": "# Fill Copy Paste and Split Calc Data\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task asks to fill blanks, copy and paste table content, duplicate rows, or split delimiter-based text into cells.\n- Use when the visible challenge is data movement across cells rather than formula logic or formatting only.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The source and destination ranges are visible or named in the task.\n- The task is clear about whether existing data should be preserved, overwritten, or only blank cells filled.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Use this card when a Calc cell with delimited text is already selected and the next step is to open LibreOffice Calc's built-in Text to Columns command from the menu bar. The current screen should plausibly match an open Data menu with the Text to Columns entry visible.\n2. Use this card when copied data needs to be pasted into a fresh worksheet and Calc is showing the sheet-tab strip at the bottom of the workbook. The current screen should plausibly match a normal worksheet view where the next action is to create a new sheet from the plus button.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed review cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose screenshot actually matches the live Calc surface.\n- Image references in this package:\n  - `Images/data_menu_text_to_columns.png`\n  - `Images/data_menu_text_to_columns_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/new_sheet_plus_button.png`\n  - `Images/new_sheet_plus_button_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Running fill or paste on the wrong range after a selection change.\n- Overwriting populated cells when the task only wanted blanks filled or split output appended.\n- Stopping after opening a split or fill surface without checking the resulting cells.",
