      "name": "Lookup Reference and Keyed Fill Formulas",
      "description": "Enter cross-sheet or keyed-reference formulas in the correct destination column, verify the sheet-qualified references, and confirm the visible filled results.",
      "domain": "libreoffice_calc",
      "domainLabel": "LibreOffice Calc",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/libreoffice_calc/LIBREOFFICECALC_Lookup_Reference_and_Keyed_Fill_Formulas",
      "imageCount": 4,
      "stateCardCount": 2,
      "runtimeCardCount": 2,
      "planStepCount": 6,
      "tags": [
        "formulas"
      ],
      "overview": "Use when the task explicitly involves VLOOKUP-style logic, cross-sheet references, matching by key, or filling values from a reference table. Use when the main risk is choosing the wrong source sheet, wrong key column, wrong lookup range, or wrong destination output column.",
      "applicability": [
        "Use when the task explicitly involves VLOOKUP-style logic, cross-sheet references, matching by key, or filling values from a reference table.",
        "Use when the main risk is choosing the wrong source sheet, wrong key column, wrong lookup range, or wrong destination output column.",
        "Use when the task explicitly involves VLOOKUP-style logic, cross-sheet references, matching by key, or filling values from a reference table."
      ],
      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Lookup Reference and Keyed Fill Formulas\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task explicitly involves VLOOKUP-style logic, cross-sheet references, matching by key, or filling values from a reference table.\n- Use when the main risk is choosing the wrong source sheet, wrong key column, wrong lookup range, or wrong destination output column.\n\n## When Not To Use\n\n- Do not use for plain arithmetic formulas that only happen to live on another sheet but are not keyed lookups.\n- Do not use for generic business-metric columns such as profit or revenue unless the hard part is the keyed reference itself.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Anchor the correct destination sheet and destination output header before entering the formula.\n2. Identify the key column in the destination table and the reference table or source sheet that will supply the result.\n3. Enter the first keyed formula and verify the sheet-qualified references before pressing Enter or filling downward.\n4. Check the first returned value against the live key for that row.\n5. Fill the verified formula through the requested range only.\n6. Re-check the destination result column on the sheet instead of trusting the formula bar alone.\n\n## Verification Focus\n\n- Confirm the active sheet tab is the destination sheet when entering the formula.\n- Confirm the formula points to the intended source sheet and reference range.\n- Confirm the destination output header matches the task, not just the selected cell address.\n- Spot-check at least one later filled row so the lookup range and key reference stayed correct.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the active sheet is wrong, switch back before editing formulas.\n- If the reference formula is actually a direct arithmetic relation rather than a keyed lookup, switch to the generic formula skill.\n- If the first returned value is wrong, fix the source sheet, key column, or lookup range before filling the rest of the column.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Runtime cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Match only the card that fits the current live Calc surface.\n\nImage references in this package:\n\n- `Images/cross_sheet_formula_bar_reference.png`\n- `Images/cross_sheet_formula_bar_reference_focus_crop.png`\n- `Images/filled_reference_results_visible.png`\n- `Images/filled_reference_results_visible_focus_crop.png`",
