      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Calc Worksheets and Cross Sheet Data\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use when the task is about creating, renaming, deleting, or switching worksheet tabs or placing data on another sheet.\n- Use when cross-sheet placement is part of the visible result.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target worksheet or sheet name is known.\n- The task is primarily about sheet/tab management rather than cell formulas or pivot configuration.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Verify that the intended destination tab remains active after the cross-sheet action, then separately confirm the task-required pasted data or downstream output is visible on that sheet if the current screenshot exposes it.\n2. Use this card when the sheet already exists and LibreOffice Calc is asking for the tab name in a Rename Sheet dialog. It matches a centered rename modal where the Name field is active and the current sheet label text is selected, ready to be replaced.\n3. Use this card when Calc is already open on a worksheet and the task needs a brand-new destination sheet before later paste, pivot, chart, or summary steps. It matches a screen where the bottom worksheet tab strip is visible and the small plus control for adding a sheet is available beside the existing tabs.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed review cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose screenshot actually matches the live Calc surface.\n- Image references in this package:\n  - `Images/destination_sheet_with_pasted_data.png`\n  - `Images/destination_sheet_with_pasted_data_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/rename_destination_sheet.png`\n  - `Images/rename_destination_sheet_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/sheet_tab_plus_button.png`\n  - `Images/sheet_tab_plus_button_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Renaming or editing the wrong sheet tab.\n- Pasting data onto the current sheet when the task required another tab.",
