      "overview": "Use this skill when the task names multiple slides or a slide range and applies the same text-formatting recipe to each target.",
      "applicability": [],
      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Apply Multi-Slide Title and Text Formatting\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task names multiple slides or a slide range and applies the same text-formatting recipe to each target.\n\nDo not use this skill for one-off title formatting, for paragraph bullet work, for single-slide tasks with several text boxes, or for cases where the main task is deleting slides, moving objects, changing notes, or changing backgrounds and the text edit is only incidental.\n\n## Loop Procedure\n\n1. Select the next target slide in the filmstrip.\n2. Select the exact text on that slide.\n3. Apply the repeated character-formatting recipe.\n4. Verify the visible result on the current slide.\n5. Advance to the next named slide and repeat the loop.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If one slide in the range has a different operation from the others, stop using this skill and switch to the more specific local skill for that slide.\n- If the current slide loses selection or the wrong text object becomes active, reselect the current slide and re-run the local verification before advancing.\n- Never treat success on the first slide as proof that the remaining slides are done.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Every target slide needs its own local verification.\n- The filmstrip selection must stay aligned with the current loop step.\n- Completion means the loop has been repeated for all named slides, not just the first one.\n- If the task mixes text formatting with object deletion, note editing, or table changes, this skill should not remain the primary workflow.",
