      "skillMarkdown": "# Apply Object Animations\n\n## Overview\n\nSelect the target object, open the LibreOffice Impress Animation controls, set the requested effect and timing values, and verify the final animation entry before leaving the sidebar.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for object-level animations on a selected slide object, text box, image, shape, or title.\n- Use it when the task names an animation effect, effect category, direction, trigger, duration, delay, or other object-animation parameter.\n- Do not use it for slide-wide transitions, master-slide edits, or general object formatting that does not create or modify an animation entry.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target presentation is open in LibreOffice Impress.\n- The intended slide can be reached and the target object can be selected on the slide canvas.\n- The task is about configuring an object animation, not changing the transition for the whole slide.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### Apply or Tune an Object Animation\n\n1. Navigate to the slide that contains the target object.\n2. Select the object that should receive or already has the animation. Verify that selection handles are visible on that object before changing animation controls.\n3. Open the right-side Animation controls. If another sidebar deck is open, switch to the Animation deck rather than using slide transition controls.\n4. Add the requested animation effect or select the existing animation entry that needs adjustment.\n5. Set the requested category, effect, direction, start trigger, duration, delay, and other timing controls. Only use values from the current task.\n6. Before leaving the surface, verify that the selected animation entry corresponds to the intended object and that visible timing or effect fields match the request.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`; the compact branch-loading cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime should load only the image card whose `when_to_use` state plausibly matches the current screenshot.\n- `Images/animation_sidebar_open.png` is an entry-state cue for a selected object and the right sidebar surface before continuing into animation controls.\n- `Images/animation_timing_controls.png` is an operation-state cue for a selected animation entry with editable effect, direction, duration, and delay controls.\n- `Images/animation_result_state.png` is a verification cue for a selected object that still has a selected animation entry and visible final settings.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes mark interaction targets, such as the sidebar or duration field; they are not reusable coordinates.\n- Green boxes mark state or verification cues, such as the selected object or selected animation entry; they are not instructions to reuse the example object.\n- Do not copy example slide text, picture subjects, slide numbers, object positions, effect names, directions, duration values, or delay values unless the current task explicitly requests them.\n- Ignore a visual card if the screenshot is a transition panel, a non-Impress surface, or an animation pane for the wrong selected object.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The intended object should be selected on the slide or otherwise clearly linked to the selected animation entry.\n- The Animation sidebar should contain the configured animation entry for that object.\n- Effect, direction, trigger, duration, and delay should match the current task wherever those fields are requested.\n- If the task only asks to add an effect, still verify that the animation entry remains present before finishing.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Applying the effect to the wrong object because the intended text box, image, or shape was not selected first.\n- Using slide transition controls instead of the object Animation sidebar.\n- Selecting the right effect but leaving the old duration, delay, direction, or trigger unchanged.\n- Treating a visually similar example card as completion even though the current task requested different values or a different object.",
