      "skillMarkdown": "# Apply Slide Transitions\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task is about how one slide advances to the next in LibreOffice Impress: choosing a slide transition effect, setting its sound, adjusting duration or automatic advance timing, or applying the same transition to all slides.\n\nDo not use this skill for per-object animation work on shapes, text boxes, or chart elements. Those actions belong to the animation pane, not the slide-transition sidebar.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The presentation is already open in LibreOffice Impress.\n- The target slide thumbnail is selected in the navigator.\n- The right sidebar can be switched to the Slide Transition panel.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Confirm the target slide is selected in the left thumbnail navigator.\n2. Open the Slide Transition sidebar if it is not already visible.\n3. Choose the requested transition effect for the selected slide.\n4. Set any requested transition options on the same sidebar, such as sound, duration, automatic advance timing, or apply-to-all scope.\n5. Verify that the sidebar still shows the requested transition settings before leaving the slide.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nUse `runtime_state_cards.json` as the compact runtime source for the Agent branch. Load only the card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screenshot; do not preload unrelated cards.\n\nUse `state_cards.json` as the fuller audit record. It preserves the same one-card-per-image mapping with richer transfer limits, review rationale, and grounded targets.\n\nImage references for this skill:\n\n- `Images/transition_sidebar_open.png` supports entry-state recognition when the selected slide and Slide Transition sidebar are both visible.\n- `Images/transition_scope_controls.png` supports the mid-procedure state where the transition effect is visible and scope controls such as apply-to-all can still be changed.\n- `Images/transition_result_state.png` supports final verification that the requested transition settings remain visible before moving away.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues only.\n- Green boxes are state or verification cues only.\n- Box locations are not reusable coordinates.\n- Slide content, thumbnail artwork, slide numbers, and example transition values in the screenshots are incidental unless the current task explicitly asks for those same details.\n- Do not copy effect names, sounds, or timings from example screenshots unless the user request matches them.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nTreat the skill as complete only when the Slide Transition sidebar still shows the requested settings on the selected slide. Depending on the task, that may include:\n\n- the chosen transition effect remaining selected\n- the requested sound remaining visible\n- the requested duration or automatic advance timing remaining visible\n- the correct scope decision, including apply-to-all only when requested\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- The wrong slide thumbnail is selected before editing the transition.\n- The agent opens the animation sidebar for objects instead of the Slide Transition sidebar.\n- The agent applies a transition to all slides when the task only asks for one slide.\n- The agent leaves the slide without checking whether the requested sound or timing is still shown in the sidebar.\n\n## Runtime Notes\n\nThe runtime branch should load `runtime_state_cards.json` for prompt-budget matching and return the matched `state_id` when a card fits the current screenshot. Use `state_cards.json` when auditing, reviewing transfer limits, or checking the grounded evidence behind a visual cue.",
