      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Impress Preferences, Print, and Slide Show Settings\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill for persistent application-level preferences such as view settings, print defaults, grids, compatibility options, or other lasting Impress or LibreOffice controls.\n\nDo not use it for one-off slide content edits. Do not use it if the task is really about slide-show mode or presenter console behavior; that belongs to the separate presenter skill.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Open `Tools -> Options`.\n2. Confirm the correct left-tree branch and page title.\n3. Change the requested control on that page.\n4. Verify the resulting value on the same page before closing the dialog.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The page title and left-tree selection must still match the requested preference family.\n- The final value or toggle state must be visible on the correct page.\n- Reaching the dialog is not enough without the value check.",
