      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Presenter Console and One-Monitor Slide Show\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task changes presentation mode, presenter console behavior, one-monitor playback, pointer-as-pen, or related slide-show settings.\n\nUse `Slide Show -> Slide Show Settings...` for run-local playback changes such as `In a window`, click-to-advance behavior, custom slide shows, or pointer-as-pen.\n\nUse `Tools -> Options -> LibreOffice Impress -> General` only when the task explicitly asks for a persistent presenter-console preference.\n\nDo not use this skill for generic application preferences that are unrelated to slideshow playback.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Choose the correct settings surface before changing any value.\n2. Keep the task on that surface until the requested checkbox, radio button, or dropdown value is visible.\n3. Verify the requested state before the dialog or menu closes.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The visible surface must match the task: `Slide Show Settings` for run-local playback, `LibreOffice Impress -> General` only for persistent presenter-console preferences.\n- The requested checkbox, dropdown, or radio state must remain visible before the surface closes.\n- Verify the specific presentation mode or presenter-related state, not just that a menu or window opened.",
