      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Slide Backgrounds and Fill Effects\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task changes the background of the slide itself: color, gradient, image, hatch, pattern, or transparency on the current slide surface.\n\nDo not use this skill for fills on shapes, text boxes, charts, or images that only look like a background. Do not use it for master-slide editing unless the task explicitly targets the master.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Confirm the target slide is selected in the filmstrip.\n2. Make sure the right sidebar is targeting the slide surface rather than a selected object.\n3. Open the slide background controls from `Properties > Slide` or `Slide Properties`.\n4. Choose the requested fill family or transparency value.\n5. Verify the preview in the dialog only as an intermediate check.\n6. Confirm the result on the slide canvas before leaving the surface.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThe entry card is a wrong-surface gate. It exists to prevent object-fill mistakes before any value is changed.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/background_fill_mode.png`: slide-level background entry cue in the normal editing workspace.\n- `Images/background_transparency_controls.png`: modal value controls plus the in-dialog preview region.\n- `Images/background_result_state.png`: final result check after the change is applied.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The slide thumbnail must still indicate the intended target slide.\n- The background row or dialog must belong to the slide surface, not to a selected object.\n- The canvas must visibly reflect the requested background state before the skill is considered complete.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening object fill controls instead of the slide background surface.\n- Losing the target slide selection during a multi-slide task.\n- Treating a preview-only match as completion without checking the canvas.",
