      "skillMarkdown": "# Edit Slide Number and Master Slide Elements\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task changes slide numbers, dates, footer text, or other elements that should persist through the master surface.\n\nDo not use it for edits that belong only to a single slide.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Enter `View -> Master Slide` or open the master-elements control that belongs to the persistent field.\n2. Confirm the canvas is the master surface rather than a single editable slide.\n3. Change the requested persistent element.\n4. Verify the persistent field or footer on the master canvas before leaving master editing.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The surface must clearly be master editing, not the normal slide canvas.\n- The requested persistent field or element must be visible on the master canvas before the skill is complete.\n- If the task continues with slide-specific edits afterward, leave master editing only after the persistent element is visibly present.",
