      "overview": "Use this skill when the task explicitly targets notes, notes view, or master notes.",
      "applicability": [],
      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Edit Speaker Notes and Notes Views\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task explicitly targets notes, notes view, or master notes.\n\nDo not use it for normal slide text boxes. The main risk in this workflow is typing into the wrong surface.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Switch into `View -> Notes` or `View -> Master Notes`.\n2. Confirm the lower notes region is the active text surface.\n3. Type or paste into the notes region, not into the main slide canvas.\n4. Verify the requested note text is visible in the notes surface before leaving it.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If typed text appears on the slide canvas instead of the notes area, undo that input, return to Notes view, and re-place focus in the lower notes surface.\n- If the view switches back to Normal while the note is still incomplete, re-open Notes view before typing again.\n- For mixed tasks that also change slide text formatting, finish each surface with its own verification: slide canvas for title/body edits, notes surface for note text.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The screen must clearly be the notes surface, not the normal slide canvas.\n- The note text must be visible in the lower notes region before the skill is complete.\n- If the main slide text box is still taking edits, the workflow is still on the wrong surface.",
