      "overview": "Use this skill for character-level formatting on existing slide text: font family, size, color, bold, italic, underline, highlight, outline, shadow, superscript, or similar effects.",
      "applicability": [],
      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Format Slide Text and Paragraphs\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill for character-level formatting on existing slide text: font family, size, color, bold, italic, underline, highlight, outline, shadow, superscript, or similar effects.\n\nDo not use this skill as the main workflow for bullets, numbering, indentation, or paragraph spacing. Do not use it when the task primarily changes several slides in sequence with the exact same recipe; use the batch-formatting skill for that case.\n\n## Entry Checks\n\n1. Confirm the correct slide in the filmstrip.\n2. Select the exact title or text run that must change.\n3. Confirm that the caret or selection is inside the intended text object, not in another text box or on the empty slide canvas.\n\n## Operation Procedure\n\n1. Open the Character controls while keeping the selected text visible.\n2. Apply only the requested character styling.\n3. If you type into a font-family or size field, verify keyboard focus is in that control before typing.\n\n## Result Verification\n\n1. Verify the changed text on the canvas before moving to another target.\n2. Re-check the active slide thumbnail when the task names a specific slide.\n3. For multiple text objects on the same slide, finish one object and verify it locally before selecting the next.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If typed characters appear inside the slide text box instead of the font field or size field, undo that text insertion immediately, reselect the intended text, and retry from the Character controls.\n- If the sidebar changed but the canvas result is not visible, do not advance to another object or slide yet.\n- If selection is lost after opening the sidebar, re-establish the exact text selection before applying any more formatting.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThe state cards are written around the selection state and the visible result, because the audit failures came from losing the target text or stopping after only looking at the sidebar.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/text_target_selected.png`: exact text selection plus filmstrip state.\n- `Images/text_character_controls.png`: Character controls while the selected text stays visible.\n- `Images/text_format_result.png`: final canvas-visible formatting result.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The active slide thumbnail must still match the requested slide.\n- The selected text object must stay visible while the Character controls are used.\n- The on-canvas text must visibly show the requested style before the skill is complete.\n- A changed sidebar control alone is not enough if the canvas text still looks unchanged or if the wrong text box is active.",
