      "id": "LIBREOFFICEIMPRESS_Insert_Shapes_Text_Boxes_and_Diagram_Objects",
      "name": "Insert Shapes, Text Boxes, and Diagram Objects",
      "description": "Insert a new shape, text box, or simple diagram object on the current slide, adjust its basic geometry when needed, and verify that it remains on the canvas.",
      "domain": "libreoffice_impress",
      "domainLabel": "LibreOffice Impress",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/libreoffice_impress/LIBREOFFICEIMPRESS_Insert_Shapes_Text_Boxes_and_Diagram_Objects",
      "imageCount": 6,
      "stateCardCount": 3,
      "runtimeCardCount": 3,
      "planStepCount": 8,
      "tags": [
        "slides",
        "text"
      ],
      "overview": "",
      "applicability": [
        "Inserting a shape such as a circle, rectangle, line-derived shape, or callout.",
        "Adding a new text box.",
        "Adding a simple diagram-style object that starts from the same insert workflow."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Opening the correct insert path on the wrong slide.",
        "Editing a pre-existing object instead of creating a new one.",
        "Changing geometry before the new object is actually selected."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert Shapes, Text Boxes, and Diagram Objects\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when LibreOffice Impress is already open on the target presentation and the task is to add a new drawable object to the current slide. Good matches include:\n\n- Inserting a shape such as a circle, rectangle, line-derived shape, or callout.\n- Adding a new text box.\n- Adding a simple diagram-style object that starts from the same insert workflow.\n\nDo not use this skill for editing an existing object that is already on the slide, changing only formatting on an existing object, or solving a task that begins from a different surface such as slide layout changes.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The correct slide is selected in the thumbnail strip.\n- The task is about creating a new object, not reusing one that already exists.\n- LibreOffice Impress is on the normal editing canvas.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill is text-first. Use the procedure below as the default workflow, and load image cards only when the current screenshot plausibly matches the state you are in.\n\n- Audit file: `state_cards.json`\n- Runtime file for the Agent branch: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nLoad only the card whose `when_to_use` matches the current screen. Do not load every image card at once. The images are for state recognition and verification, not for replaying coordinates.\n\nRed boxes mark interaction cues. Green boxes mark state or verification cues. Neither box color provides reusable coordinates.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\nThe screenshots contain example slide content, example object styles, and example numeric values. Transfer only the UI relationship:\n\n- menu open vs. menu closed\n- object selected vs. not selected\n- geometry controls visible vs. hidden\n- inserted object visibly present on the slide vs. not yet confirmed\n\nDo not copy example text, slide titles, object size, object position, fill color, or line style unless the current task explicitly asks for those details.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### 1. Open the insertion surface\n\nIf the object has not been created yet, open the Insert menu and choose the path for the needed object type.\n\n- Image reference: `Images/shape_insert_surface.png`\n- Matching card: `shape_insert_surface` in both `state_cards.json` and `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nUse this image only when the current screenshot already shows the Insert dropdown as the next decision point.\n\n### 2. Place the new object on the target slide\n\nInsert the requested shape, text box, or diagram object onto the selected slide. After placement, keep the new object selected if the task still requires size or geometry adjustment.\n\nIf the task only requires insertion and the object already matches the requested result, move directly to verification.\n\n### 3. Adjust geometry when needed\n\nWhen the inserted object is selected and the right sidebar exposes geometry controls, refine width, height, or position as required by the task.\n\n- Image reference: `Images/shape_geometry_controls.png`\n- Matching card: `shape_geometry_controls` in both `state_cards.json` and `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nUse this image only when the object is already on the slide and the visible controls are object-level geometry controls, not slide-level settings.\n\n### 4. Verify the result on the canvas\n\nBefore finishing, confirm that the requested object is visibly present on the intended slide as a persistent canvas element.\n\n- Image reference: `Images/shape_result_state.png`\n- Matching card: `shape_result_state` in both `state_cards.json` and `runtime_state_cards.json`\n\nThe verification image is an example of a completed inserted object on the slide. Treat the visible object presence as transferable; treat the exact example shape and styling as non-transferable unless the task asks for them.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nThe task is complete only when the current slide shows the newly inserted object in the slide canvas itself. Strong cues include:\n\n- the object is visible on the target slide\n- the object can be selected on the canvas\n- object-specific controls appear in the sidebar when selected\n- the requested text or shape type is present when the task requires it\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening the correct insert path on the wrong slide.\n- Editing a pre-existing object instead of creating a new one.\n- Changing geometry before the new object is actually selected.\n- Finishing after insertion without checking that the object remains visible on the slide.\n- Copying example screenshot details such as literal text, color, or size instead of following the current task request.",
