      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert and Edit Charts\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when a LibreOffice Impress task needs chart-specific work on the current slide:\n\n- insert a new chart from the slide editor\n- open the chart data table for an existing chart\n- change chart data and confirm the updated chart data state before finishing\n\nDo not use this skill for plain table insertion, generic shapes, or slide content edits that never enter chart-specific controls.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target slide is already selected.\n- The task is explicitly about a chart, chart data, or chart-type workflow.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. If a chart must be added, start from the slide editing surface and open `Insert` -> `Chart`.\n2. Once a chart exists and needs value edits, work inside the chart `Data Table` dialog rather than on the slide canvas.\n3. Keep chart editing active until the requested data state is visibly present.\n4. Verify the resulting chart data state before closing the dialog or leaving chart edit mode.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the card whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot; do not preload every image card just because the skill is active.\n- The image references used by this skill are:\n  - `Images/chart_type_controls.png`\n  - `Images/chart_data_table.png`\n  - `Images/chart_result_state.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are state or verification cues.\n- Boxes are not reusable coordinates.\n- Do not copy example slide text, chart subject matter, row labels, or numeric values unless the current task explicitly asks for them.\n- Match the UI state shown by the card, not the source task's literal content.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- If you are inserting a chart, verify that you reached chart-specific controls rather than inserting a generic object.\n- If you are editing values, verify that the `Data Table` dialog is the active surface before typing.\n- Before finishing, verify that the visible table state matches the current task's requested result, not merely that the dialog is open.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening the wrong insert path and creating a non-chart object.\n- Editing the slide or sidebar instead of the chart data table.\n- Treating the example row values in the screenshot as required output for a different task.\n- Closing the data table without confirming that the requested result is visibly present.",
