      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert and Format Tables\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill for table insertion and table-specific edits: row or column counts, header rows, cell text, merged cells, table geometry, or on-slide placement.\n\nDo not use it for chart insertion or for generic shape grids that only resemble tables.\n\n## Core Procedure\n\n1. Confirm the target slide.\n2. Insert the table if it does not exist yet.\n3. Keep the table active on the canvas while editing cells, headers, merges, or geometry.\n4. Verify the resulting table structure and placement on the slide before leaving the workflow.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The final table must be visible on the slide.\n- Header text, merged cells, or row and column structure must match the request.\n- A style preset alone is not enough without the visible table result.",
