      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Writer Preferences, User Data, Toolbar, and Dictionaries\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task changes persistent Writer options instead of formatting only the current document selection.\n- The matching surface is the Options dialog or a closely related settings dialog such as Customize or Extension Manager.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- LibreOffice Writer is already open on a document window.\n- If the task later requires saving the current document, finish the settings change first and then switch to the save or export skill.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Use this state when the Options dialog is already open on the User Data page and the task needs one of the persistent profile fields such as Company or Initials.\n2. Use this state when the task is about default Writer fonts and the Options dialog still shows a different page such as User Data.\n3. Use this state when the Basic Fonts (Western) page is already visible and the task needs the Default font or size controls changed.\n4. Confirm the requested row already shows the target family and size, then apply the setting and only then leave the Options dialog.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed authoring cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose `when_to_use` matches the current surface.\n- Generated images in this package:\n  - `Images/writer_options_basic_fonts_branch.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_basic_fonts_branch_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_default_font_control.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_default_font_control_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_default_font_result.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_default_font_result_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_user_data_company_field.png`\n  - `Images/writer_options_user_data_company_field_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Loading a visually similar surface that does not actually contain this skill's target control.\n- Assuming the operation is complete before the document or settings surface shows the requested result.",
