      "skillMarkdown": "# Format Paragraph Alignment and Spacing\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task changes paragraph-level alignment, line spacing, or paragraph spacing.\n- The requested result is visible as a block-level layout change on the document canvas.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The intended paragraph or paragraph range is already selected, or the cursor is inside the target paragraph.\n- If the task also changes font color or underlines, finish the paragraph edit first and then switch to the character-formatting skill.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Use this state when paragraph text is already selected and you need to open the paragraph formatting surface from a context-menu path.\n2. Use this state when the Paragraph dialog is open on Indents and Spacing and the task specifically names a line-spacing value such as Single, 1.5 Lines, or Double.\n3. Confirm the correct paragraph block shows the requested spacing or alignment change on the page before moving on to any character-level formatting.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed authoring cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose `when_to_use` matches the current surface.\n- Generated images in this package:\n  - `Images/paragraph_dialog_entry.png`\n  - `Images/paragraph_dialog_entry_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/paragraph_line_spacing_dropdown.png`\n  - `Images/paragraph_line_spacing_dropdown_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/paragraph_spacing_result.png`\n  - `Images/paragraph_spacing_result_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Loading a visually similar surface that does not actually contain this skill's target control.\n- Assuming the operation is complete before the document or settings surface shows the requested result.",
