      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert Bookmarks, Comments, Hyperlinks, and Notes\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task asks for a bookmark, comment, hyperlink, or similar annotation tied to the current cursor position or selection.\n- The goal is navigation, linking, or annotation inside the document, not bibliography or cross-reference numbering.\n- The current surface is a bookmark dialog, hyperlink dialog, comment/note affordance, or the document canvas showing the inserted result.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Writer is open on the target document.\n- The insertion point or selected text is already known.\n\n## Do Not Use\n\n- Do not use this skill for bibliography insertion or cross-reference numbering.\n- Do not treat the dialog closing by itself as proof that the insertion succeeded.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Place the caret or select the content that should receive the bookmark, comment, hyperlink, or note.\n\n2. Open the matching insert surface and fill the requested value.\nUse the bookmark dialog for anchor naming, the hyperlink dialog for a destination, and the comment/note route for annotation content.\n\n3. Verify the document-level result before leaving.\nCheck that the inserted anchor, link text, comment marker, or note marker is now visible in the document or attached to the intended content.\nIf the dialog closed but no visible marker or link result appeared, stay in this workflow and fix the insertion.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed authoring cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose `when_to_use` matches the current surface.\n- Generated images in this package:\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_bookmark_dialog.png`\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_bookmark_dialog_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_hyperlink_dialog.png`\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_hyperlink_dialog_focus_crop.png`\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_result.png`\n  - `Images/insert_bookmarks_result_focus_crop.png`\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Using this skill for reference-number workflows that belong to the cross-reference skill.\n- Confirming a dialog before the requested name, URL, or comment text is actually entered.\n- Leaving the flow before checking the document canvas for the inserted marker or link result.",
