      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert Page Numbers, Headers, Footers, and Blank Pages\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task changes page-level structure rather than ordinary paragraph formatting.\n- The task asks for footer or header content, page numbering, a numbering scheme, a blank page, or a manual page break.\n- The current surface is the Insert menu path, a Page Style dialog, or the document canvas showing the page-level result.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Writer is open on the target document.\n- The requested page-style behavior is known from the task wording.\n\n## Do Not Use\n\n- Do not use this skill for page margins, orientation, or other layout-only changes unless the task also includes header, footer, page-number, or blank-page behavior.\n- Do not assume that a page break succeeded until the extra page is visibly present.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Choose the page-structure route that matches the task.\nUse the header/footer path when the task is about page numbers or footer content.\nUse the blank-page or page-break route only when the task asks for an additional page.\n\n2. Verify the intermediate surface.\nFor numbering work, verify that the footer is active or that the page-number format control is open.\nFor blank-page work, verify that the command actually created an additional page rather than just moving the cursor.\n\n3. Verify the document-level result before leaving.\nFor footer tasks, check that the footer region is active and contains the requested content.\nFor blank-page tasks, check that the document now contains the added empty page.\nIf the page count or page canvas did not change, do not move on.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Detailed authoring cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime-facing cards live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the state whose `when_to_use` matches the current surface.\n- Use the blank-page result card only as a verification state after the insertion action has already run.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Choosing the wrong page style in the footer path.\n- Inserting a page break and assuming success without checking that the extra blank page exists.\n- Changing numbering controls in a dialog without verifying the visible result on the document canvas.",
