      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Add Or Adjust Recurring Timetable Slots In Calc\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when a weekly timetable is open in Calc and the task ends only after the requested class block is visibly present in the correct day-time slot. The reusable pattern is: anchor on the target slot, verify the full lecture span, then finish on the formatted block inside the timetable grid.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- OSWorld timetable trajectory\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task names a weekly timetable slot such as Wednesday at 12 PM.\n- The schedule is stored in LibreOffice Calc and the finish condition is a visible lecture or class block.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The timetable workbook can be opened in Calc.\n- The requested weekday column and time rows are visible or can be brought into view.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Anchor on the exact day-time slot before typing**: use the grid coordinates as the first check.\n- **Verify the final lecture block formatting**: finish on the completed schedule block, not on a transient toolbar action.\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the timetable uses multi-row class blocks`, verify the full block span before final formatting.\n- If `the task ends with a visible lecture block`, treat the finished block in the grid as the completion signal.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the formatting control that still needs action.\n- Green boxes mark the selected or completed timetable block that proves placement or success.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the timetable sheet, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the relevant grid region or toolbar control.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `calc_timetable_target_slot_osworld`: Target timetable slot is selected. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `calc_timetable_lecture_block_text_osworld`: Lecture text spans the intended time block. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `calc_timetable_formatting_control_osworld`: Formatting control for the timetable block is active. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `calc_timetable_formatted_result_osworld`: Recurring lecture block is visibly formatted in the timetable. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Insert or adjust a recurring timetable slot in Calc\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Target timetable slot is selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The requested day and time slot is already selected in the Calc grid.\n- Image reference: `Images/calc_timetable_target_slot_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The timetable is open and the target row and column are visible.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the exact slot before entering or dragging the class block.\n\n##### State 2: Lecture text spans the intended time block\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The lecture label already occupies the selected timetable region.\n- Image reference: `Images/calc_timetable_lecture_block_text_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The class label has just been entered or stretched across the intended duration.\n\nAction:\n- Verify that the label and its span match the requested slot.\n\n##### State 3: Formatting control for the timetable block is active\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The formatting tool is visible while the intended timetable block remains selected.\n- Image reference: `Images/calc_timetable_formatting_control_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The right lecture block is already selected.\n\nAction:\n- Apply timetable styling only while the intended block is still active.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The lecture block is visibly formatted in the schedule grid.\n- Image reference: `Images/calc_timetable_formatted_result_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The timetable update is complete.\n\nAction:\n- Finish on the visible block inside the timetable, not on the toolbar alone.",
