      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Capture Browser Downloads In A Target Folder\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the browser is only an intermediate surface and the real finish condition is a downloaded or saved output landing in the requested local folder. It now explicitly covers single-file saves, batch downloads into an opened folder, and browser-to-filesystem verification after the download step.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Download Browser Files Into A Working Folder\n- Save Web Pages Or Selections As Local Documents\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task asks for a browser file, screenshot, PDF, article, or local saved copy to be placed in a named local folder.\n- The browser may use either a dedicated download button or a save/export flow, but the real endpoint is still local storage.\n- The task may require more than one file; finish only after the requested count is present in the destination folder.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The browser can reach the requested page or output source.\n- The destination folder already exists or can be created during the task.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Identify the correct browser source output**: Stay anchored on the right browser file, article, or download card before starting any save or download action.\n- **Deliver the output to the requested folder**: Move, save, or redirect the output into the explicit destination folder instead of stopping at the default download location.\n- **Verify the final local endpoint**: Re-open the destination folder if needed and confirm the requested file names or file count before marking the task done.\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the browser already exposes a dedicated download control`, prefer that over manual reconstruction.\n- If `the task asks for multiple items`, finish the whole set before leaving the browser workflow.\n- If `the file lands in a temporary location first`, reopen the requested folder and verify the real endpoint there.\n- If `the browser still shows an active download spinner or unfinished tray item`, wait for completion before switching apps.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the download handoff and the final local folder result before marking completion.",
