      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Capture Terminal Output Into A Writer Report\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when terminal output is only intermediate evidence and the task ends when that output is preserved inside a saved Writer report.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Copy Terminal Output Into Writer\n- Save The Terminal-Backed Report As A Reusable output\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The terminal generates process output, command output, or other text that must be placed into Writer.\n- The result must remain in a saved Writer output rather than only in the terminal window.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The relevant terminal command can be run or its output is already visible.\n- Writer can be opened for the report destination.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Capture the required terminal output**: Stay on the right terminal output block before copying it.\n- Derived from: Copy Terminal Output Into Writer, Save The Terminal-Backed Report As A Reusable output\n- **Preserve the output in a saved Writer report**: Use the visible saved report output as the real endpoint.\n- Derived from: Copy Terminal Output Into Writer, Save The Terminal-Backed Report As A Reusable output\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the terminal already shows the requested output block`, choose `Capture the required terminal output`. Copy from the visible result instead of rerunning unrelated commands.\n- If `the task names a report file or document save`, choose `Preserve the output in a saved Writer report`. The saved document is the real completion state.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `terminal_writer_copy_control`: Terminal copy action is exposed. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `terminal_writer_pasted_output`: Writer already contains the pasted output. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `terminal_writer_saved_report`: Saved report output remains open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `terminal_writer_source_output`: Terminal output block is visible. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Move terminal output into a saved Writer report\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Terminal output block is visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal shows the exact output block that should be preserved in Writer.\n- Image reference: `Images/terminal_writer_source_output.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The command has already produced the requested terminal result.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the terminal result before copying it.\n\n##### State 2: Terminal copy action is exposed\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal context menu already exposes the copy action for the selected output.\n- Image reference: `Images/terminal_writer_copy_control.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested output block is selected in the terminal.\n\nAction:\n- Use the terminal copy action so the exact command output is transferred.\n\n##### State 3: Writer already contains the pasted output\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Writer is open and the terminal output is already visible in the document body.\n- Image reference: `Images/terminal_writer_pasted_output.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The workflow has switched from the terminal into Writer.\n\nAction:\n- Keep the output in the Writer document instead of leaving it only in the terminal.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The saved Writer report still shows the preserved terminal output after the save step.\n- Image reference: `Images/terminal_writer_saved_report.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The document has already been saved as the requested report output.",
