      "skillMarkdown": "# Commit And Push Project Changes From Terminal\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task is a Terminal-based git workflow that ends only after the remote branch update succeeds. The key reusable pattern is: verify the repository prompt, review the commit-and-push command, then finish on the remote success output rather than on the act of typing.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- OSWorld Git push trajectory\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task explicitly names a commit message and a branch or remote such as `origin main`.\n- The work already starts in Terminal and the result is a successful push, not a later browser or file-manager step.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Terminal can be focused on the target repository.\n- The repository is already initialized and the task expects normal git add, commit, and push behavior.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Confirm the repository prompt before sending git commands**: verify the shell is scoped to the correct repo.\n- **Verify that the remote accepted the push**: finish on the returned prompt plus the remote success line.\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the prompt already shows the target repo path`, confirm that scope before running a write command.\n- If `the task names a commit message and destination branch`, review the full command line and finish only on the remote success output.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the shell line that still needs deliberate execution or review.\n- Green boxes mark a state signal or durable success line that proves the workflow completed.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the terminal surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the repo prompt, command line, or success lines.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `git_push_repo_prompt_osworld`: Repository prompt is visible in Terminal. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `git_push_compound_command_osworld`: Combined git add commit and push command is ready to execute. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `git_push_remote_success_osworld`: Remote push succeeds in Terminal. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Stage changes, commit them, and push the requested branch from Terminal\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Repository prompt is visible in Terminal\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal title and prompt both show the intended repository path.\n- Image reference: `Images/git_push_repo_prompt_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- Terminal is open on the target project.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the repo path before sending any staging, commit, or push command.\n\n##### State 2: Combined git add commit and push command is ready to execute\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal line already contains the full command with the requested message and branch.\n- Image reference: `Images/git_push_compound_command_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The repository prompt has already been verified.\n\nAction:\n- Review the exact git command before executing it.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal output confirms the remote accepted the push and the prompt returned.\n- Image reference: `Images/git_push_remote_success_osworld.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The git command has already run.\n\nAction:\n- Finish only on the remote success lines, not on the act of typing the command.",
