      "skillMarkdown": "# Compare Files Statements Or Records And Write A Result\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task compares records or computed values across files and only ends after the result is written into the requested report output. It is a narrow compare-then-write workflow, not a generic fallback for other multi-app tasks.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Compare Records Across Files Or Statements\n- Write Comparison Findings Into A Result output\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The workflow compares rows, values, or rankings across one or more files or web sources.\n- The compared result must appear in a final chart, table, or numeric report output.\n- Do not use this skill for Git repository sync, timetable editing, citation-format cleanup, bulk paper metadata extraction, or subtitle export tasks.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The source files or comparison inputs can be opened.\n- A report destination such as Writer is available if the task requires one.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Inspect the comparison source data**: Stay on the cells, rows, or records that feed the comparison.\n- Derived from: Compare Records Across Files Or Statements, Write Comparison Findings Into A Result output\n- **Write the computed comparison result**: Use the final chart or result table as the endpoint rather than the raw source data.\n- Derived from: Compare Records Across Files Or Statements, Write Comparison Findings Into A Result output\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task compares spreadsheet values or ranked items`, choose `Inspect the comparison source data`. The comparison must stay grounded on the actual source rows or cells.\n- If `the task ends in a report table or chart`, choose `Write the computed comparison result`. The visible report output is the finish condition, not the intermediate math.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `compare_execution_surface`: Comparison logic is ready to execute. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `compare_final_artifact`: Final comparison output is visibly complete. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `compare_result_written`: Computed comparison result is written into the report. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `compare_source_data`: Comparison source data is visible. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Compare the source records and surface the final result\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Comparison source data is visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The spreadsheet already shows the source cells or rows that feed the comparison.\n- Image reference: `Images/compare_source_data.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The comparison inputs have been opened.\n\nAction:\n- Anchor on the source records before computing the result.\n\n##### State 2: Comparison logic is ready to execute\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The terminal or code surface is ready to run the comparison logic that computes the result.\n- Image reference: `Images/compare_execution_surface.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The source records have already been identified.\n\nAction:\n- Run the comparison logic only after the correct source data is known.\n\n##### State 3: Computed comparison result is written into the report\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The destination report already shows both the comparison label and the computed result value.\n- Image reference: `Images/compare_result_written.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The comparison computation has finished.\n\nAction:\n- Write the result into the report output instead of leaving it only in the terminal or source sheet.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The report output visibly combines the compared output and its labeled result.\n- Image reference: `Images/compare_final_artifact.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The comparison result has already been inserted into the report.",
