      "skillMarkdown": "# Convert A Local Office Document And Upload It To Drive\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task starts from a local office file, requires a format conversion or export, and only finishes once the uploaded output is visible in Google Drive.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Export Office Files To A Shareable Format\n- Upload A Prepared output To Google Drive\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A local Writer or Calc file must be converted or exported before uploading.\n- The task names a Drive folder and expects the uploaded output to be the endpoint.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The local office document can be opened in the relevant LibreOffice app.\n- Google Drive is available for the upload step.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Prepare the source office document for export**: Stay on the correct office file before choosing the requested export format.\n- Derived from: Export Office Files To A Shareable Format, Upload A Prepared output To Google Drive\n- **Verify the uploaded output in Drive**: Use the uploaded file row inside the target Drive folder as the finish state.\n- Derived from: Export Office Files To A Shareable Format, Upload A Prepared output To Google Drive\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task names a shareable format such as PDF or PNG`, choose `Prepare the source office document for export`. The conversion step matters before any upload can succeed.\n- If `the task names a specific Drive folder`, choose `Verify the uploaded output in Drive`. The cloud folder endpoint is the real completion state.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `office_drive_export_format`: Requested export format is selected. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `office_drive_source_document`: Source office document is open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `office_drive_target_folder`: Target Drive folder is open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `office_drive_uploaded_artifact`: Uploaded converted output is visible in Drive. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Export the office output and confirm it inside Drive\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Source office document is open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The local office document is already open in LibreOffice before export.\n- Image reference: `Images/office_drive_source_document.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The workflow is still operating on the local source file.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the right office document before exporting the wrong output.\n\n##### State 2: Requested export format is selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The export dialog already exposes the requested output format for the office output.\n- Image reference: `Images/office_drive_export_format.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The source office file is ready to be converted.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested export format before leaving the local office app.\n\n##### State 3: Target Drive folder is open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Google Drive is already open inside the requested destination folder.\n- Image reference: `Images/office_drive_target_folder.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The converted file is ready to be uploaded.\n\nAction:\n- Upload into the named Drive folder rather than leaving the output in a generic Drive location.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The uploaded office output is visible inside the requested Drive folder.\n- Image reference: `Images/office_drive_uploaded_artifact.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The upload has completed in the correct cloud location.",
