      "skillMarkdown": "# Convert Or Export Local Files And Verify Output\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the workflow begins from a local file or already-open document, performs a format conversion or export, and ends only after the produced output is visible in the expected local location or target app. This skill is the this release replacement for tasks that were previously forced into the Drive-upload skill even though the real endpoint stayed local.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A local office, media, image, text, or document output must be converted or exported into another format.\n- The workflow may run through a GUI export dialog or a command-line batch conversion, but the finish condition is still a local output output.\n- The task may also ask you to open or preview the result after export.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The source file or app surface can be opened.\n- The required export surface or terminal conversion path is available.\n\n## State-Action Mapping\n\n1. Confirm the correct source file or source app surface before transforming anything.\n2. Use the requested export format, conversion command, or batch transform control.\n3. Save into the requested location or open the requested preview target instead of accepting a default path blindly.\n4. Finish only after the converted output file or preview surface confirms the new output exists.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the first export dialog defaults to the wrong folder or wrong format, back out and correct it before saving.\n- If a batch conversion finishes silently, reopen the destination folder and verify that the expected filenames were actually created.\n- If the task asks for a preview in another app, verify the file exists locally first, then open it.",
