      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Extract Web Listings Into A Calc Table\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the browser is the source of structured listings and the real endpoint is a populated Calc table.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Enter Web Listings In A Calc Table\n- Paste Web Links Or References Into Calc Cells\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task asks for browser listing data such as names, addresses, phone numbers, or links to be entered into Calc.\n- Calc cells are the finish condition rather than the source page staying open in the browser.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The browser can reach the requested listing source.\n- Calc can be opened for the destination spreadsheet.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Read the correct browser listing block**: Anchor on the exact listing card or detail popup before transferring its values.\n- Derived from: Enter Web Listings In A Calc Table, Paste Web Links Or References Into Calc Cells\n- **Populate the destination Calc cells**: Carry the requested values into Calc and verify the completed spreadsheet rows.\n- Derived from: Enter Web Listings In A Calc Table, Paste Web Links Or References Into Calc Cells\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the browser shows a listing card or map detail popup`, choose `Read the correct browser listing block`. The listing card exposes the values that should be transferred into Calc.\n- If `the task names cells, rows, or headers`, choose `Populate the destination Calc cells`. The spreadsheet layout is the actual target, not the browser source.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `browser_calc_calc_switch`: Switch back to Calc is ready. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `browser_calc_destination_cells`: Destination Calc cells are open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `browser_calc_result_table`: Calc table shows the completed transferred rows. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `browser_calc_source_listing`: Source listing details are open in the browser. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Read browser listings and complete the Calc table\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Source listing details are open in the browser\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The browser displays the listing card whose fields should be transferred into Calc.\n- Image reference: `Images/browser_calc_source_listing.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The browser has reached the requested listing detail popup.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the source listing before moving to Calc.\n\n##### State 2: Switch back to Calc is ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The desktop already exposes the Calc entry point for continuing the structured handoff.\n- Image reference: `Images/browser_calc_calc_switch.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested browser details have been identified.\n\nAction:\n- Return to Calc so the listing values land in the spreadsheet.\n\n##### State 3: Destination Calc cells are open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Calc is already open on the target sheet where the browser values should be entered.\n- Image reference: `Images/browser_calc_destination_cells.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The workflow has switched back into Calc.\n\nAction:\n- Use the target cells as the insertion point for the listing values.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The destination Calc table visibly contains the browser-derived listing data.\n- Image reference: `Images/browser_calc_result_table.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The required values have been entered into Calc.",
