      "skillMarkdown": "# Insert VLC-Captured Media Into An Impress Slide\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when VLC provides the source frame or audio and the task only ends after the captured media is visible on the target Impress slide.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Insert VLC Audio Into An Impress Slide\n- Set A VLC Snapshot As An Impress Slide Background\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task captures a VLC frame or converts VLC audio for insertion into Impress.\n- The final verification happens in the slide deck rather than inside VLC.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The target media can be opened in VLC.\n- Impress can open the target presentation and slide.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Capture the required VLC media moment**: Stay on the right VLC frame or conversion setting before handing the media off.\n- Derived from: Insert VLC Audio Into An Impress Slide, Set A VLC Snapshot As An Impress Slide Background\n- **Verify the media on the target slide**: Use the visible media element on the target slide as the endpoint.\n- Derived from: Insert VLC Audio Into An Impress Slide, Set A VLC Snapshot As An Impress Slide Background\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task names a timecode or audio conversion profile`, choose `Capture the required VLC media moment`. The right VLC capture state matters before inserting anything into Impress.\n- If `the task names a slide number or slide background`, choose `Verify the media on the target slide`. The Impress slide is the real finish condition.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `vlc_impress_capture_control`: VLC capture or conversion control is selected. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `vlc_impress_insert_target`: Impress insertion target is open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `vlc_impress_result`: Target slide visibly shows the inserted media. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `vlc_impress_source_frame`: Source media moment is paused in VLC. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Capture VLC media and confirm it on the target Impress slide\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Source media moment is paused in VLC\n\nVisual grounding:\n- VLC already shows the exact frame or paused playback moment relevant to the task.\n- Image reference: `Images/vlc_impress_source_frame.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The media has been opened in VLC and the target moment has been reached.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the source moment before capture or conversion.\n\n##### State 2: VLC capture or conversion control is selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- VLC already exposes the capture or conversion setting that produces the reusable media.\n- Image reference: `Images/vlc_impress_capture_control.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The right playback source has already been identified.\n\nAction:\n- Use the capture or conversion control that creates the media for Impress.\n\n##### State 3: Impress insertion target is open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Impress is already open on the target slide with the media insertion action available.\n- Image reference: `Images/vlc_impress_insert_target.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The VLC media output is ready for handoff.\n\nAction:\n- Insert the media into the correct slide instead of leaving it only on disk or in VLC.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Impress slide visibly contains the VLC-derived media result.\n- Image reference: `Images/vlc_impress_result.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The capture has already been inserted into the presentation.",
