      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Install Add-on Or Extension Across Browser And Desktop App\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task installs a browser extension or desktop add-on and only ends after the target app returns in a ready post-install state. This skill covers both catalog installs and manual local-extension handoffs such as Chrome `Load unpacked`.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Install A Browser Extension From The Web Store\n- Install A Desktop Extension Or Add-on Package\n- Verify The Extension In The Target App\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The workflow installs an extension, plugin, theme, or add-on into Chrome, LibreOffice, or VS Code.\n- The task points to a local unpacked Chrome extension folder and the install must happen from `chrome://extensions`.\n- The task expects restart or post-install verification rather than stopping at the download page.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The catalog page, extension file, or extension manager can be opened.\n- The target application can be restarted or reopened if the install requires it.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Identify the requested add-on candidate**: Stay on the exact extension or add-on entry that should be installed.\n- Derived from: Install A Browser Extension From The Web Store, Install A Desktop Extension Or Add-on Package, Verify The Extension In The Target App\n- **Confirm the installed state in the target app**: Use the post-install manager row or reopened app window as the endpoint.\n- Derived from: Install A Browser Extension From The Web Store, Install A Desktop Extension Or Add-on Package, Verify The Extension In The Target App\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the install begins from a web store or extension catalog`, choose `Identify the requested add-on candidate`. The correct extension entry matters before installation.\n- If `the task names a local folder or unpacked extension`, stay on the Chrome manual-install branch and verify the folder-selection plus loaded-card states rather than using store-install cues.\n- If `the task explicitly requires restart or reopen`, choose `Confirm the installed state in the target app`. A visible ready-state after install is the real success condition.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `extension_install_candidate`: Extension candidate is identified. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `extension_install_confirm`: Install confirmation action is visible. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `extension_install_manual_directory_selected_osworld`: Select the unpacked Chrome extension directory from the Desktop. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `extension_install_chrome_loaded_osworld`: Verify that Chrome has loaded the unpacked extension card. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `extension_install_manager_row`: Installed add-on appears in the manager. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `extension_install_ready_state`: Target app is back in a ready state. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Install the requested add-on and verify the target app after install\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Extension candidate is identified\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The catalog or extension list already highlights the add-on that should be installed.\n- Image reference: `Images/extension_install_candidate.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The install flow is still on the source catalog page.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the add-on candidate before accepting the install.\n\n##### State 2: Install confirmation action is visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The browser or app confirmation surface already exposes the install action for the add-on.\n- Image reference: `Images/extension_install_confirm.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct extension has been chosen.\n\nAction:\n- Use the explicit add or install action to commit the add-on.\n\n##### State 3: Installed add-on appears in the manager\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target app's extension manager already shows the installed add-on row.\n- Image reference: `Images/extension_install_manager_row.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The installation has completed.\n\nAction:\n- Verify the add-on in the manager instead of stopping at the install prompt.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target application has returned after the installation or restart step.\n- Image reference: `Images/extension_install_ready_state.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The add-on is installed and the app has been reopened.",
