      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Transfer Browser Research Into Writer\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when browser research is only the source and the task truly ends when the requested note, citation, or reference block is visible inside Writer. The this revision emphasizes preserving the requested field order and matching any existing Writer entry pattern.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Record Browsed Details In A Writer Note\n- Copy Browser Citations Into Writer\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The task collects facts, citations, paper metadata, or reference text in the browser and writes the result in Writer.\n- The browser content must be transferred into an opened or saved Writer document instead of remaining in the source page.\n- The destination document may already contain example rows or example paragraphs that the new entry should follow.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The browser can open the requested source page or citation panel.\n- Writer can be opened for the destination document.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Collect the correct browser evidence**: Stay on the exact citation, metadata block, or source card that the task requests.\n- **Insert the browser evidence into Writer**: Paste or type the browser result into Writer at the correct insertion point.\n- **Verify structure after the handoff**: Check that Writer now shows the requested fields, in the requested order and format, before leaving the task.\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the source page exposes a citation dialog or structured details block`, copy only from that explicit source block instead of reconstructing it.\n- If `the destination Writer document already contains example entries`, match that entry pattern before considering the task complete.\n- If `the browser evidence spans multiple fields`, collect the full set before switching into Writer so the handoff does not lose context.\n- After pasting, verify the result in Writer rather than immediately returning to the browser.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.",
