      "skillMarkdown": "# Transfer Calc Results Into A Writer Report\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the task is not finished in Calc alone and the required endpoint is a Writer report that contains the copied chart, range, or result-table block. The this revision strengthens the header-plus-row case, the destination-section check inside Writer, and the final save verification.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Paste A Calc Chart Into Writer\n- Paste A Calc Range Into Writer\n- Transfer Calc Results Into A Writer Report\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A chart or cell range is prepared in Calc and must appear inside Writer.\n- The task asks for a named result row, table header, or small result table to move from Calc into a Writer report.\n- The task names a Writer section, merged cell, report table, or filename that determines where the copied result should land.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The relevant Calc chart or range already exists or can be created.\n- Writer can be opened for the destination report.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Select the exact Calc result**: Stay anchored on the chart, header-plus-row block, or range that should move into Writer.\n- **Place the result into the Writer report**: Use the correct Writer destination instead of pasting into an arbitrary blank area.\n- **Verify the saved Writer deliverable**: Confirm that the copied result is still present after the save step.\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task names a specific model row or says the header must be pasted too`, copy the full header-plus-row block before leaving Calc.\n- If `the Writer destination is an existing section or report table`, anchor on that section heading or table cell first.\n- If the first paste loses the table shape or formatting, undo and repeat with the correct Calc block selection instead of trying to patch the broken paste in Writer.\n- Finish only after the saved Writer document still shows the requested result.",
