      "skillMarkdown": "# Transfer Other App Content Into A Writer Output\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when the source material comes from another desktop app such as Impress, GIMP, a mail attachment flow, or a local viewer, but the real endpoint is a Writer document. The goal is to preserve the cross-app handoff and verify the result on the Writer side.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- The source app is not primarily a browser listing task and not a Calc-to-Writer table transfer.\n- The task asks you to move notes, slide text, extracted content, or another source output into a Writer document.\n- The destination Writer document may already have existing content or section structure that the inserted result should follow.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The source app can show the content that must be transferred.\n- Writer can open the destination document or a new output document.\n\n## State-Action Mapping\n\n1. Confirm the source content in the non-Writer app before switching away.\n2. Return to the correct insertion point in Writer.\n3. Use the Writer-side insert or edit control that applies the requested update.\n4. Finish only after Writer visibly shows the transferred content.\n\n## Failure Recovery\n\n- If the first Writer insertion lands in the wrong section, undo and relocate the insertion point before retrying.\n- If the source content spans several fields or notes, collect the full set before switching into Writer.\n- After the handoff, verify the result in Writer instead of bouncing back to the source app immediately.",
