      "overview": "Use this skill when Thunderbird is the source of a document attachment and the task only finishes after the attachment has been updated inside Writer.",
      "applicability": [
        "A Thunderbird email attachment must be opened in Writer and edited there.",
        "The finish condition is the updated Writer document rather than the email source."
      ],
      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Turn A Thunderbird Attachment Into A Writer Update\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when Thunderbird is the source of a document attachment and the task only finishes after the attachment has been updated inside Writer.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Download A Thunderbird Attachment For Writer Use\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A Thunderbird email attachment must be opened in Writer and edited there.\n- The finish condition is the updated Writer document rather than the email source.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird can open the relevant email with the attachment.\n- Writer can open the attachment for editing.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Locate and save the attachment from Thunderbird**: Stay on the right attachment card before opening it in Writer.\n- Derived from: Download A Thunderbird Attachment For Writer Use\n- **Apply the requested Writer update**: Use the Writer document as the actual endpoint for the handoff.\n- Derived from: Download A Thunderbird Attachment For Writer Use\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the attachment card is already visible in Thunderbird`, choose `Locate and save the attachment from Thunderbird`. The attachment source should be confirmed before editing starts.\n- If `the task asks for an inserted image or document change inside Writer`, choose `Apply the requested Writer update`. The edited Writer document is the real result.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `thunder_writer_attachment_source`: Attachment source is visible in Thunderbird. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `thunder_writer_insert_control`: Writer insertion control is available. Views: `full_frame`.\n- `thunder_writer_result`: Updated Writer document shows the attachment-driven result. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `thunder_writer_save_control`: Attachment save control is ready. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Save the Thunderbird attachment and complete the Writer edit\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Attachment source is visible in Thunderbird\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird already shows the attachment card for the document that should be edited.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_writer_attachment_source.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The relevant email has been opened in Thunderbird.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the attachment before saving or opening it.\n\n##### State 2: Attachment save control is ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird exposes the direct save action for the attachment.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_writer_save_control.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The attachment card is already confirmed.\n\nAction:\n- Save the attachment so the workflow can continue in Writer.\n\n##### State 3: Writer insertion control is available\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Writer is already open on the attachment document with the insert-image action available.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_writer_insert_control.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The saved attachment has been opened in Writer.\n\nAction:\n- Use the Writer edit controls to complete the requested document update.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Writer document visibly contains the requested update derived from the Thunderbird attachment workflow.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_writer_result.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The Writer edit has been completed and saved.",
