      "failureModes": [],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Upload Thunderbird Attachments Or Message Exports To Drive\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when Thunderbird provides the source attachment or exported message and the workflow only finishes once the file is visible inside the requested Drive folder.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Save A Thunderbird Message As An Archive File\n- Download An Email Attachment For Reuse\n- Upload Thunderbird Attachments Or Message Exports To Drive\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A Thunderbird attachment or saved message file must be uploaded into Google Drive.\n- The task expects Drive folder creation or upload confirmation after the mail-side save step.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird can open the relevant email or message list.\n- Google Drive is available for the upload step.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Save the Thunderbird-sourced file locally**: Anchor on the exact attachment or message export before starting the cloud handoff.\n- Derived from: Save A Thunderbird Message As An Archive File, Download An Email Attachment For Reuse, Upload Thunderbird Attachments Or Message Exports To Drive\n- **Verify the uploaded Drive result**: Use the visible uploaded file in the target Drive folder as the finish condition.\n- Derived from: Save A Thunderbird Message As An Archive File, Download An Email Attachment For Reuse, Upload Thunderbird Attachments Or Message Exports To Drive\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the Thunderbird message already shows the attachment or export menu`, choose `Save the Thunderbird-sourced file locally`. The cloud handoff depends on starting from the correct mail-sourced file.\n- If `the task names a Drive folder or asks to create one`, choose `Verify the uploaded Drive result`. The upload target in Drive is the actual endpoint.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `thunder_drive_result`: Uploaded Thunderbird file is visible in Drive. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `thunder_drive_save_action`: Message export save action is exposed. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `thunder_drive_source_attachment`: Thunderbird attachment save surface is visible. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `thunder_drive_target_folder`: Target Drive folder is open. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Save Thunderbird content and confirm the uploaded file in Drive\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Thunderbird attachment save surface is visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird already shows the attachment that should begin the Drive upload chain.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_drive_source_attachment.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The relevant email is open in Thunderbird.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the Thunderbird source file before starting the upload workflow.\n\n##### State 2: Message export save action is exposed\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird already exposes the save action for exporting the chosen message or attachment.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_drive_save_action.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct Thunderbird source item has been identified.\n\nAction:\n- Use the explicit save action that creates the local file for upload.\n\n##### State 3: Target Drive folder is open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Google Drive is already open inside the folder that should receive the uploaded Thunderbird file.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_drive_target_folder.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The local Thunderbird-sourced file is ready for cloud upload.\n\nAction:\n- Upload into the named Drive folder rather than leaving the file in a generic Drive view.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Drive folder visibly contains the uploaded file that came from Thunderbird.\n- Image reference: `Images/thunder_drive_result.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The upload has already completed in the requested folder.",
