      "skillMarkdown": "# Use Document Text As A GIMP Watermark And Export PNGs\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill when document text must be carried into GIMP as the visible watermark and the task only ends after the exported PNG shows the text applied on the image.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Apply Document Text As A GIMP Watermark\n- Export Edited GIMP Assets As PNGs\n\n## When to Use\n\n- A Writer document provides the text that should become a GIMP watermark or overlay.\n- The requested output is a PNG image with the transferred text already visible.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The source document with the required text can be opened.\n- GIMP can open the target image and export the final PNG.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **Capture the requested source text**: Stay anchored on the exact document text that should move into the image edit.\n- Derived from: Apply Document Text As A GIMP Watermark, Export Edited GIMP Assets As PNGs\n- **Apply and export the watermarked image**: Use GIMP to place the text and finish only after the exported PNG shows it.\n- Derived from: Apply Document Text As A GIMP Watermark, Export Edited GIMP Assets As PNGs\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the document already shows the exact phrase to reuse`, choose `Capture the requested source text`. Copying the visible source text avoids inventing the watermark content.\n- If `the task names a PNG output and image corner placement`, choose `Apply and export the watermarked image`. The visual GIMP result is the true endpoint.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill uses multiview state bundles in `state_cards.json` and the compact runtime surface in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load a state only when the current screen matches its `when_to_use` conditions.\n- Start with `full_frame` to confirm the app surface, then use `focus_crop` to inspect the local working region.\n- Treat red and green boxes as visual cues, not reusable coordinates.\n- Use verification states to confirm the cross-app handoff or saved result before marking completion.\n\n## State Card Index\n\n- `gimp_watermark_export_target`: PNG export target is named. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `gimp_watermark_result`: Exported image shows the watermark text. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `gimp_watermark_source_text`: Source text is selected in the document. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n- `gimp_watermark_text_tool`: GIMP text tool is active. Views: `full_frame`, `focus_crop`.\n\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Move document text into GIMP and verify the exported PNG result\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: Source text is selected in the document\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The exact document text that should become the watermark is already selected.\n- Image reference: `Images/gimp_watermark_source_text.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The source Writer document is open at the requested text.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the exact phrase before switching into GIMP.\n\n##### State 2: GIMP text tool is active\n\nVisual grounding:\n- GIMP is open with the text tool ready for placing the watermark.\n- Image reference: `Images/gimp_watermark_text_tool.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The source text has already been chosen.\n\nAction:\n- Use the text tool so the copied document text is placed as an image overlay.\n\n##### State 3: PNG export target is named\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The GIMP export dialog already shows the PNG filename for the edited image.\n- Image reference: `Images/gimp_watermark_export_target.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The text has been placed onto the image and the export step is active.\n\nAction:\n- Confirm the PNG export target before finishing the image edit.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The final image visibly contains the document text as the applied watermark.\n- Image reference: `Images/gimp_watermark_result.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The PNG export has completed.",
