      "skillMarkdown": "# Adjust Terminal Window and Preferences\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill for Ubuntu Terminal preference tasks: opening Terminal Preferences, selecting the requested profile, changing profile options such as initial size, cursor behavior, font, colors, or login-shell behavior, and verifying that the requested value is visibly saved.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use when the task asks for a Terminal profile or Terminal window preference change.\n- Use when the task can be completed through Terminal Preferences, a task-approved settings command, or a visible query of the saved Terminal profile value.\n- Use when completion depends on seeing the changed value, not merely on reaching a menu.\n\nDo not use this skill for arbitrary shell-command tasks, GNOME Users/account management, avatar changes, or general Ubuntu Settings navigation unless those actions are explicitly part of the current task.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Terminal is open or can be opened directly.\n- The requested profile, setting name, and target value are known from the current task.\n- If a command-line method is used, it must target the same Terminal profile setting requested by the task.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- `state_cards.json` is the detailed version with full image-level notes and transfer limits.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` is the compact version for runtime branch loading.\n- Runtime should load only the image cards that plausibly match the current screenshot and current task state.\n- Red boxes are interaction cues. Green boxes are verification/state cues. Neither should be reused as coordinates.\n- The example images include source-task residue, including a foreground Ubuntu Settings Users page in later frames. Treat that content as non-transferable unless the current task explicitly asks for Users settings.\n\nRelevant image cards:\n\n- `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_prepare_terminal_context.png`: ready Terminal prompt before the preference workflow.\n- `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_run_requested_command.png`: intermediate desktop settings context with Terminal partly behind it; use cautiously and only when it matches the active task state.\n- `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_verify_terminal_result.png`: terminal output/result evidence marked as the verification cue.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### Prepare Terminal Context\n\nVisual grounding:\n- A Terminal window is visible and the shell prompt is ready.\n- Image reference: `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_prepare_terminal_context.png`\n\nActions:\n- Focus Terminal if needed.\n- Confirm the task's requested profile and setting before acting.\n- If the task requires the GUI, open Terminal Preferences and select the requested profile. If the task permits a command-line edit, use the exact setting key/value required by the task.\n\n### Change The Requested Preference\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The active window should be the Terminal preference surface or another task-required settings surface.\n- Image reference, only when visually relevant: `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_run_requested_command.png`\n\nActions:\n- Apply only the requested Terminal preference change.\n- Do not copy example values from the image set. Use the current task's profile name, dimensions, checkbox state, cursor value, or other requested value.\n- If another settings window is foregrounded, confirm it is part of the current task before interacting with it; otherwise return to Terminal Preferences or Terminal.\n\n### Verify The Result\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The saved Terminal preference value is visible in the UI or in terminal output from a task-appropriate query.\n- Image reference: `Images/os_adjust_terminal_window_and_preferences_verify_terminal_result.png`\n\nActions:\n- Read the final value on screen.\n- Compare it against the current task's requested value.\n- Finish only after the visible UI or terminal output confirms the requested Terminal preference state.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not reuse image coordinates, crop positions, window placement, desktop icons, wallpaper, username, host name, file paths, or prior shell commands.\n- Do not transfer the example's profile name, terminal dimensions, account details, or avatar content unless the current task explicitly names the same values.\n- Do not treat the Ubuntu Settings Users page as proof that a Terminal preference task is complete.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- A selected Terminal profile shows the requested setting value in Preferences.\n- A terminal query prints the requested saved profile value and returns to the prompt.\n- A green image cue in the card set means \"verify this state signal,\" not \"click here.\"\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Changing a nearby Terminal preference but not the exact requested profile setting.\n- Copying the example screenshot's values instead of the current task's values.\n- Getting distracted by an unrelated foreground Ubuntu Settings page.\n- Stopping after opening Preferences without verifying the saved value.",
