      "skillMarkdown": "# Change Wallpaper and Appearance Theme\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- Use this skill for Ubuntu Settings tasks that explicitly target `Appearance`, wallpaper selection, accent color, style, or light/dark theme mode.\n- Use it when success must be confirmed by a persistent visual state such as a selected wallpaper thumbnail, active style chip, highlighted accent swatch, or retained theme toggle.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Open Ubuntu Settings.\n2. Reach `Appearance` from the sidebar or Settings search.\n3. Locate the exact requested control on the Appearance page.\n4. Apply the requested wallpaper, style, accent, or theme value.\n5. Verify the requested state remains visibly selected before leaving Settings.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- detailed cards live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime cards for the Agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Runtime should load only the image cards whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- If no image card matches, keep using the text procedure instead of forcing an image match.\n- Red boxes are interaction hints. Green boxes are verification hints. Neither is a reusable coordinate.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy example wallpaper content, desktop filenames, usernames, device names, or any other incidental screenshot detail.\n- Several saved screenshots are weak or mismatched examples for the intended Appearance workflow.\n- If a saved image shows the desktop, `Users`, or `About` rather than `Appearance`, treat it as a wrong-surface cue and continue navigating.\n- Ignore full-screen borders and oversized annotations. Use live row labels and visible Appearance controls instead.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- Verify on the `Appearance` page itself.\n- Confirm that the requested wallpaper thumbnail, style mode, accent selection, or theme control is still visibly active after the change.\n- Do not treat a click, temporary highlight, or navigation away from `Appearance` as sufficient proof.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Acting on the wrong Settings page, especially `Users` or `About`.\n- Changing a nearby row because the label was not checked against the task.\n- Treating a legacy red or green annotation as a coordinate instead of a cue.\n- Marking success while the requested Appearance state is off-screen or no longer selected.\n\n## Image References\n\n- `Images/os_change_wallpaper_and_appearance_theme_open_settings_surface.png`\n- `Images/os_change_wallpaper_and_appearance_theme_locate_target_control.png`\n- `Images/os_change_wallpaper_and_appearance_theme_apply_requested_setting.png`\n- `Images/os_change_wallpaper_and_appearance_theme_verify_result_state.png`\n\nLoad only the matching card for the current screenshot. The image set is for audit and conditional grounding support; the reusable procedure remains the text-first Appearance workflow above.",
