      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Remote Sharing\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task explicitly targets Ubuntu Sharing, Remote Desktop, Remote Login, Legacy VNC, password-required remote control, or turning remote access on or off.\n- The requested result can be verified from the Sharing page or from the matching Remote Desktop or Remote Login dialog before it is dismissed.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Reach sharing page.\n2. Configure remote desktop dialog.\n3. Configure remote login.\n4. Verify sharing row state.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the live screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_open_settings_surface.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_locate_target_control.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_configure_legacy_vnc.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_verify_legacy_vnc_enabled.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_choose_require_password_option.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_verify_password_requirement.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_verify_remote_desktop_disabled.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_locate_remote_login_row.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_remote_sharing_verify_remote_login_enabled.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, row, dialog, and visible state relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, usernames, machine names, timestamps, desktop contents, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant Search or Sharing surface must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI rather than inferred from the last click.\n- Do not finish from a pre-action page, a wrong settings family, or a dismissed dialog that hid the only reliable verification cue.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Mistaking another Sharing row such as Media Sharing for the requested Remote Desktop or Remote Login row.\n- Leaving the Remote Desktop dialog before verifying that the checkbox, password mode, or on/off toggle really changed.\n- Treating the Sharing page alone as proof that password-required remote control is set, even though that requirement is only visible inside the Remote Desktop dialog.\n- Ignoring the authentication step for Remote Login and assuming that the row turned on before the auth dialog completed.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
