      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Search Results\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The live task explicitly mentions Ubuntu Search settings, Search Locations, Activities Overview results, or the order of search providers.\n- The requested result can be verified from the Search page itself or from the Search Locations dialog before it is dismissed.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Reach search page.\n2. Edit search locations.\n3. Toggle or reorder search rows.\n4. Verify search result state.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the live screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_open_settings_surface.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_locate_target_control.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_verify_search_locations_result.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_apply_requested_setting.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_verify_result_state.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_reorder_provider_row.png`\n- `Images/os_configure_search_results_verify_reordered_provider_row.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, row, dialog, and visible state relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, usernames, machine names, timestamps, desktop contents, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant Search or Sharing surface must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI rather than inferred from the last click.\n- Do not finish from a pre-action page, a wrong settings family, or a dismissed dialog that hid the only reliable verification cue.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Treating another Settings panel as a valid Search match without confirming the Search sidebar row and the Search page title.\n- Closing the Search Locations dialog before verifying that the requested folder toggle changed to the requested state.\n- Changing a nearby provider row because the agent followed the example box instead of the live row label.\n- Forgetting that some tasks change row order rather than toggle state, so the drag handle and final row position must be re-read before finishing.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
