      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Time and Date Preferences\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\nUse this skill when the task explicitly asks for a change inside Ubuntu `Settings > Date & Time`, including time format, timezone, automatic date and time, automatic timezone, manual date, or manual time.\n\nThis skill is appropriate when success depends on a visible control state that must still be shown on the Date & Time page after the change, or when a timezone task can be verified more directly from `timedatectl` in Terminal.\n\nDo not use this skill for other Settings areas just because a search term overlaps with time-related wording.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Open Ubuntu Settings if it is not already open.\n2. Reach `Date & Time` through the sidebar or Settings search when the GUI route is clear and the page is actually loading.\n3. Identify the exact row named in the task before changing anything.\n4. For timezone tasks, especially when the verification uses `timedatectl`, a Terminal fallback such as `timedatectl set-timezone UTC` or `timedatectl set-timezone Etc/UTC` is acceptable if GUI entry keeps drifting or the page search is unreliable.\n5. Change only the requested toggle, selector, date field, time field, or timezone control.\n6. Verify on the `Date & Time` page or with `timedatectl status` that the requested state remains visible before leaving.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` is the compact set for the Agent branch. Load only the cards whose screenshot content plausibly matches the current screen.\n- `state_cards.json` is the audit set with fuller transfer notes and evidence lineage.\n- Image filenames are not enough. Match on the actual visible UI state first.\n- Red boxes indicate interaction cues. Green cues indicate visible state signals. Neither is a reusable coordinate.\n- If the current screen does not plausibly match a card's `when_to_use`, skip that image and continue with the text procedure.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Treat literal example values, app names, desktop files, wallpaper details, and window placement as non-transferable.\n- One image in this package is a duplicated desktop frame, and one image is an off-topic `Default Applications` screenshot. Those cards exist so the runtime can reject bad matches, not so the agent can imitate the example literally.\n- Do not infer that a change succeeded from a search result, a neighboring Settings page, or a control on another panel.\n- If the current screen keeps matching the desktop or an off-topic Settings page instead of `Date & Time`, use that mismatch as a cue to re-open the right surface or switch to a shell-based timezone fallback.\n- Use image cues to recognize the current state, then act on the live UI labels in front of you.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The Settings window is on `Date & Time`, not another Settings category.\n- The exact requested control row is still visible after the action.\n- The requested value, toggle state, or selected format remains shown on that row.\n- Verification should happen on the final Date & Time surface or on the exact shell status output that the task or verification reads, not on search results or another page.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Staying on the desktop and assuming the task has already reached Settings.\n- Opening the wrong Settings category because the sidebar row label was not checked.\n- Changing a nearby control with a similar switch or dropdown shape.\n- Drifting into another page, such as `Default Applications`, and verifying the wrong state.\n- Staying in a GUI navigation loop for a timezone task even though `timedatectl` would provide a more direct and verifiable path.\n- Copying literal example values from the screenshots instead of using the task's requested value.\n\n## Visual References\n\n- `Images/os_configure_time_and_date_preferences_open_settings_surface.png`: desktop entry cue before Settings is open.\n- `Images/os_configure_time_and_date_preferences_locate_target_control.png`: duplicate desktop frame; use only as a mismatch or failure cue.\n- `Images/os_configure_time_and_date_preferences_apply_requested_setting.png`: Settings sidebar cue for entering `Date & Time` from another category.\n- `Images/os_configure_time_and_date_preferences_verify_result_state.png`: off-topic drift example; use only when the live screen also matches that wrong page.\n\nThe runtime should normally load only the matching card or cards for the current screen, not the whole image set at once.",
