      "skillMarkdown": "# Copy Matching Files In Terminal\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task asks for copying files that match a pattern into one destination folder.\n- The destination should contain the matching files themselves rather than a replicated directory hierarchy.\n- Success must be confirmed by a destination listing, file manager view, or an explicit follow-up terminal check.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Confirm the source path, the file pattern, and whether the destination folder already exists.\n2. Use a flat copy recipe such as `mkdir -p DEST` followed by `find SRC -type f -iname 'PATTERN' -exec cp -t DEST -- {} +` when the task explicitly wants a flat destination.\n3. Verify with `find DEST -maxdepth 1 -type f`, `ls -1 DEST`, or a file manager view that shows the copied files in the destination itself.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_copy_matching_files_or_directory_hierarchy_in_terminal_identify_source_pattern_and_destination.png`\n- `Images/os_copy_matching_files_or_directory_hierarchy_in_terminal_run_flat_copy_command.png`\n- `Images/os_copy_matching_files_or_directory_hierarchy_in_terminal_verify_destination_contents.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, prompt, or modal relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, package names, usernames, desktop contents, timestamps, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant page, shell prompt, or modal must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI or shell output.\n- Do not finish from command entry, pre-action page state, or a guessed outcome.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Accidentally preserving the source hierarchy when the task wants only the matching files in one folder.\n- Forgetting to create the destination first or copying to the wrong target path.\n- Marking success before reading the destination listing that proves the copied files are present.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
