      "skillMarkdown": "# Edit and Save Text in Text Editor\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task explicitly requires Ubuntu Text Editor or another GUI text-editing flow that depends on typing exact content into the editor surface and confirming the saved filename afterward.\n\nUse a different skill when the task is primarily about terminal editors, package installation, filesystem cleanup, or settings changes that do not depend on the Text Editor document surface.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- The requested text content is known.\n- The target filename or save path is known when the task requires saving.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill stays text-first. The procedure below is the default execution path. Visual cards are support evidence for state matching and verification:\n\n- `state_cards.json` is the full audit file with image-specific rationale.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json` is the compact file intended for runtime branch loading.\n- Load only the image card whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- Treat red boxes as interaction cues and green boxes as verification cues. They are not reusable coordinates.\n\nImage references remain attached to the relevant steps:\n\n- `Images/os_edit_and_save_text_in_text_editor_focus_editor_surface.png`\n- `Images/os_edit_and_save_text_in_text_editor_enter_requested_content.png`\n- `Images/os_edit_and_save_text_in_text_editor_verify_saved_filename.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy literal example text, filenames, folder names, or formatting values from the reference screenshots unless the current task explicitly asks for them.\n- Do not treat any boxed region as a fixed click point.\n- Use the images to answer two narrow questions: where the editable surface is, and what on-screen signal confirms the saved filename.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Focus the Text Editor document surface so keyboard input will land in the document body.\n2. Enter or revise the exact requested content in the editor.\n3. Save the document to the requested location and with the requested filename.\n4. Confirm that Text Editor visibly shows the saved filename before leaving the app.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nThe task is complete only when the current Text Editor window shows the requested filename as a stable post-save signal. Use the verification image card only after saving has already happened.\n\nUseful result cues:\n\n- The document name is visible in the editor chrome, header, or related save surface.\n- The filename shown on screen matches the current task, not the example screenshot.\n- The editor is still displaying the saved document rather than an unsaved draft.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Typing correct content into the wrong window because the editor canvas was never focused.\n- Saving the document with the wrong filename or in the wrong location.\n- Treating the example screenshot's filename or text as reusable content.",
