      "skillMarkdown": "# Install App Via Snap Flatpak And App Center\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task names an end-user app and the live environment routes installation through Ubuntu Software, Snap Store, or another app-center style surface.\n- The workflow needs visual confirmation that the correct app page or install state is visible before the install is considered in progress.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Search the app store for the requested application and confirm the correct result row or detail page.\n2. Open the app detail page, confirm the package source if it matters, and only then click Install.\n3. Verify that the button changes to a progress state such as `Preparing...` or handle the authentication dialog if the store requires credentials.\n4. For explicit `snap` or `flatpak` tasks that stay in Terminal, use the text-first shell path, but keep the visual claims in this package limited to the store workflow actually shown in the evidence.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_install_app_via_snap_flatpak_and_appcenter_search_store_results.png`\n- `Images/os_install_app_via_snap_flatpak_and_appcenter_open_app_detail_ready_to_install.png`\n- `Images/os_install_app_via_snap_flatpak_and_appcenter_verify_install_has_started.png`\n- `Images/os_install_app_via_snap_flatpak_and_appcenter_handle_store_auth_dialog.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, prompt, or modal relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, package names, usernames, desktop contents, timestamps, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant page, shell prompt, or modal must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI or shell output.\n- Do not finish from command entry, pre-action page state, or a guessed outcome.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Clicking the wrong search result because only the app name fragment was checked.\n- Assuming an install succeeded before the button changed or the store actually began preparing the install.\n- Ignoring an authentication dialog that blocks the install from proceeding.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
