      "skillMarkdown": "# Install Remove And Verify Packages In Terminal\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The package task is meant to be completed in Terminal with `apt`, `dpkg`, `apt-cache`, `apt search`, or a package command check.\n- Success or failure must be proved by visible shell output rather than by a later desktop cleanup view.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Open Terminal or bring it back into focus before running package commands.\n2. Confirm the exact package path first: `apt`, `dpkg`, `snap`, `apt-cache`, `apt search`, `which`, or another direct package check should match the task and verification.\n3. Run the package command and read the live shell, especially for `Unable to locate package`, `command not found`, repository errors, or a blocking sudo prompt.\n4. Treat authentication as a separate state from package success. A password prompt or store auth dialog is not evidence that the package changed state, and repeated blank submissions are a failure loop.\n5. Verify the outcome from the same shell with decisive commands such as `which`, `dpkg -l`, `snap list`, or the exact verification command. A finished desktop view is never the primary proof signal for this package family.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_install_remove_and_verify_packages_in_terminal_prepare_terminal_context.png`\n- `Images/os_install_remove_and_verify_packages_in_terminal_run_package_command.png`\n- `Images/os_install_remove_and_verify_packages_in_terminal_verify_package_not_found_or_absence.png`\n- `Images/os_install_remove_and_verify_packages_in_terminal_recognize_auth_or_command_failure.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, prompt, or modal relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, package names, usernames, desktop contents, timestamps, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant page, shell prompt, or modal must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI or shell output.\n- Do not finish from command entry, pre-action page state, or a guessed outcome.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Treating a typed package command as success before reading the shell output.\n- Treating a sudo or auth prompt as if it already proved the package install or removal happened.\n- Reusing the wrong credential, or repeatedly submitting an empty password, when the shell is clearly still blocked on authentication.\n- Ignoring `Unable to locate package`, `command not found`, or repeated bad password output and continuing as if the package changed state.\n- Closing Terminal before the package result is proven.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
