      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Notifications\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task is specifically about Ubuntu Settings `Notifications`: turning `Do Not Disturb` on or off, changing lock-screen notification visibility, or enabling or disabling notifications for a named app. It also applies when the verification expects the final notification state to remain visible on the `Notifications` page after the action.\n\nDo not use this skill for unrelated Settings panels such as `Power`, `Sound`, or `Privacy`, even if those panels also contain switches or dropdowns.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Ubuntu Settings is open or can be opened from the current workspace.\n- The task names a notification setting that can be checked directly on the `Notifications` page.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis skill keeps two image-card files:\n\n- `state_cards.json`: full detailed version with image-specific review rationale.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json`: compact version for the Agent branch.\n\nLoad only the image cards whose `when_to_use` cues genuinely match the live screenshot. If the live screen does not match, skip the card and continue with the text procedure. The current image set contains several grounding artifacts, so the runtime should treat the cards as match-or-reject evidence rather than as a source of coordinates.\n\nImage references remain attached to the relevant steps below, but runtime loading should stay selective: only bring in the card for a screenshot that actually resembles the current screen.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes are interaction cues, not reusable click coordinates.\n- Green boxes are verification cues, not proof that the live task is complete unless the current screen matches the requested setting.\n- A red box around the whole desktop or around an unrelated UI element means the grounding failed; ignore its position and rely on the text procedure.\n- Do not transfer example-only details such as wallpaper, desktop files, clock values, app names from the screenshot, or controls from the wrong Settings panel.\n\n## Procedure\n\n### 1. Open The Notifications Surface\n\nOpen Ubuntu Settings if it is not already visible. Use the sidebar or Settings search to reach `Notifications`.\n\nImage reference:\n- `Images/os_manage_notifications_open_settings_surface.png`\n\n### 2. Locate The Exact Notification Control\n\nFind the exact row named in the task. Match the row label first, then the control type. This avoids changing a neighboring app or a nearby global setting by mistake.\n\nImage reference:\n- `Images/os_manage_notifications_locate_target_control.png`\n\n### 3. Apply The Requested Setting\n\nChange only the requested control:\n\n- toggle `Do Not Disturb` to the requested state\n- change lock-screen notification visibility to the requested setting\n- enable or disable notifications for the named app\n\nKeep the relevant row in view while acting so you can verify the same row immediately afterward.\n\nImage reference:\n- `Images/os_manage_notifications_apply_requested_setting.png`\n\n### 4. Verify The Persisted Result\n\nBefore leaving Settings, confirm on the live `Notifications` page that the same row still shows the requested state. Verification must come from the live row label and its visible control state, not from the fact that a click already happened.\n\nImage reference:\n- `Images/os_manage_notifications_verify_result_state.png`\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\nTreat the task as complete only when the live `Notifications` page shows all of the following:\n\n- the correct `Notifications` panel is still open\n- the exact row named in the task is visible\n- that row's toggle, selector, or per-app switch shows the requested state\n- no neighboring row was changed instead\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Staying on the desktop or another panel because a grounded image highlighted the wrong region.\n- Changing the wrong app row because multiple notification toggles look similar.\n- Verifying on the wrong Settings page, especially a different panel that also has switches.\n- Leaving the page immediately after clicking, without checking that the requested notification state persisted.",
