      "skillMarkdown": "# Recursive Pattern Copy And Directory Replication\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task asks for copying an entire folder hierarchy or preserving parent directories for matching files.\n- The destination may need `mkdir -p`, `cp -a`, `cp --parents`, or `rsync -a` style behavior.\n- The success proof is a directory tree, recursive listing, or explicit terminal output that shows the copied structure.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Inspect the source tree first with `find`, `tree`, or `ls -R` so the live hierarchy is explicit before copying.\n2. Use a hierarchy-preserving command such as `cp -a SRC/. DEST/`, `rsync -a SRC/ DEST/`, or `find SRC -type f -iname 'PATTERN' -exec cp --parents -t DEST -- {} +` depending on whether the task wants whole-tree replication or preserved parents for matching files.\n3. Verify with a recursive listing from the destination and stop immediately if the shell only shows unset `sourceDir` or `targetDir` probes instead of the real paths.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\n- Audit state bundles live in `state_cards.json`.\n- Compact runtime state bundles for the agent branch live in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n- Load only the states whose `when_to_use` conditions match the current screenshot.\n- Treat the stored images as state evidence only. They are never coordinate templates.\n\nImage references used by this skill:\n\n- `Images/os_recursive_pattern_copy_and_directory_replication_prepare_terminal_context.png`\n- `Images/os_recursive_pattern_copy_and_directory_replication_run_recursive_copy_command.png`\n- `Images/os_recursive_pattern_copy_and_directory_replication_verify_replicated_tree.png`\n- `Images/os_recursive_pattern_copy_and_directory_replication_reject_unset_variable_loop.png`\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Reuse the page, prompt, or modal relationship that the image demonstrates, not the literal example values.\n- Red cues mark the local work region. Green cues mark the verification region.\n- Do not transfer example filenames, package names, usernames, desktop contents, timestamps, or wallpaper details unless the live task calls for those exact values.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- The relevant page, shell prompt, or modal must still be visible at the end of the workflow.\n- The requested final state must be readable directly from the live UI or shell output.\n- Do not finish from command entry, pre-action page state, or a guessed outcome.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Copying files flat into one folder when the task asked for the directory hierarchy to remain intact.\n- Looping on empty `sourceDir` or `targetDir` guesses instead of reading the real source and destination from the live task state.\n- Skipping the final recursive verification and assuming the hierarchy exists because a copy command was typed.\n\n## References\n\n- Audit card set: `state_cards.json`\n- Compact runtime card set: `runtime_state_cards.json`\n- Planning source: `plan.json`",
