      "skillMarkdown": "# Set Default Applications\n\n## Overview\n\nUse this skill to open Ubuntu Settings, reach `Default Applications`, change the requested default-app row, and verify that the chosen app remains visible on the settled panel.\n\n## When This Skill Applies\n\n- The task asks to change a default app such as the web browser, mail app, calendar, music player, video app, or photo app.\n- Success depends on the final selected value staying visible in the `Default Applications` panel.\n- Ubuntu Settings is available from the current desktop or can be brought into focus.\n\n## When This Skill Does Not Apply\n\n- The task targets a different Settings category and does not require `Default Applications`.\n- The requested result cannot be verified from the visible row label and selected value in Settings.\n- The task is about launching an app once, not changing the system default.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\ndetailed cards live in `state_cards.json`. The compact runtime set for the Agent branch lives in `runtime_state_cards.json`.\n\n- Load only the image cards whose `when_to_use` and `visible_cues` match the live screenshot.\n- Treat red boxes as action cues and green boxes as verification cues. They are never reusable coordinates.\n- The runtime should prefer the Settings-panel cards when the panel is visible and should ignore desktop-only cards once `Default Applications` is on screen.\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_open_settings_surface.png` and `Images/os_set_default_applications_locate_target_control.png` are weak desktop-context images, not row-level evidence.\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_apply_requested_setting.png` is the main action card for changing a dropdown row.\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_verify_result_state.png` is the main verification card for confirming the persisted value.\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Do not copy literal app names from the reference screenshots unless the live task asks for that exact value.\n- Do not transfer desktop file names, wallpaper details, sidebar scroll position, or window geometry.\n- Do not infer the target row from annotation placement alone; identify the row by its live label.\n- If a saved image and the current screen differ in panel, row visibility, or settled result text, fall back to the text procedure instead of forcing the match.\n\n## Result Verification Cues\n\n- `Default Applications` is selected in the Settings sidebar.\n- The requested row label is visible in the main panel.\n- The dropdown field on that row visibly shows the requested application after the change.\n- The final value is shown on the settled panel, not only in a transient open menu.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening Settings but stopping on the wrong category.\n- Changing the wrong row because nearby dropdowns look similar.\n- Assuming the click succeeded without checking the final visible selected value.\n- Trusting a desktop-only reference image as if it already proved the panel or target row was present.\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Open or focus Ubuntu Settings.\n2. Navigate to `Default Applications`.\n3. Find the row named by the task.\n4. Change that row to the requested application.\n5. Verify the same row still shows the requested selection before finishing.\n\n## Image References\n\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_open_settings_surface.png`\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_locate_target_control.png`\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_apply_requested_setting.png`\n- `Images/os_set_default_applications_verify_result_state.png`",
