      "id": "THUNDERBIRD_Add_or_Remove_Thunderbird_Chat_Accounts",
      "name": "Add or Remove Thunderbird Chat Accounts",
      "description": "Use Thunderbird Account Settings and the chat account wizard to remove existing chat accounts or add a new IRC, XMPP, Matrix, or similar entry.",
      "domain": "thunderbird",
      "domainLabel": "Thunderbird",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/thunderbird/THUNDERBIRD_Add_or_Remove_Thunderbird_Chat_Accounts",
      "imageCount": 9,
      "stateCardCount": 4,
      "runtimeCardCount": 4,
      "planStepCount": 7,
      "tags": [
        "thunderbird"
      ],
      "overview": "Handle Thunderbird chat-account lifecycle work by removing an existing chat account from Account Settings or creating a new chat account from the built-in wizard.",
      "applicability": [
        "Use this skill when the task explicitly names IRC, XMPP, Matrix, Odonklasniki, or another chat account type inside Thunderbird.",
        "Do not use this skill for ordinary mail-account setup."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Removing the wrong account because the selected row was not verified before opening Account Actions.",
        "Picking the wrong chat protocol when the wizard shows multiple account types at once."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Add or Remove Thunderbird Chat Accounts\n\n## Overview\n\nHandle Thunderbird chat-account lifecycle work by removing an existing chat account from Account Settings or creating a new chat account from the built-in wizard.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task explicitly names IRC, XMPP, Matrix, Odonklasniki, or another chat account type inside Thunderbird.\n- Do not use this skill for ordinary mail-account setup.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **remove_chat_account**: Remove an existing chat account from Thunderbird Account Settings.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Chat Accounts\n- **create_chat_account**: Create a new chat account from the Add Chat Account wizard.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Chat Accounts\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task starts from an existing chat account that must disappear`, choose `remove_chat_account`. Prefer Account Settings and verify the selected chat account row before opening Account Actions.\n- If `the task asks for a new IRC or XMPP style account`, choose `create_chat_account`. Use the chat-account wizard and verify the protocol selection page before filling credentials.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `chat_account_selected.png`\n- `chat_remove_confirm_ready.png`\n- `chat_protocol_picker_ready.png`\n- `chat_finish_ready.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Remove the selected chat account from Account Settings\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: chat_account_selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target chat account row is selected in Thunderbird Account Settings and Account Actions is available.\n- Image reference: `Images/chat_account_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task names a chat account that already exists.\n\nAction:\n- Open Account Actions and choose the remove flow for the selected chat account.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Remove Account and Data confirmation dialog is open with the removal action available.\n- Image reference: `Images/chat_remove_confirm_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The remove flow has already been opened from Account Actions.\n\n### Create a new chat account with the wizard\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: chat_protocol_picker_ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Add Chat Account wizard is open and the requested protocol can be selected.\n- Image reference: `Images/chat_protocol_picker_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- No matching chat account exists yet and the wizard has reached the protocol selection step.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested protocol, such as XMPP, before continuing to the credential form.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The chat account wizard has collected the requested values and shows the final completion button.\n- Image reference: `Images/chat_finish_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested protocol, account name, and password have already been entered.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Removing the wrong account because the selected row was not verified before opening Account Actions.\n- Picking the wrong chat protocol when the wizard shows multiple account types at once.",
      "runtimeSchema": "2026-04-17.runtime_state_bundles.v4",
      "stateSchema": "2026-04-17.state_bundles.v4",
