      "id": "THUNDERBIRD_Apply_Tags_Stars_and_Junk_Status_to_Messages",
      "name": "Apply Tags Stars and Junk Status to Messages",
      "description": "Create or edit tags and change visible Thunderbird message status markers such as star state or junk classification.",
      "domain": "thunderbird",
      "domainLabel": "Thunderbird",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/thunderbird/THUNDERBIRD_Apply_Tags_Stars_and_Junk_Status_to_Messages",
      "imageCount": 11,
      "stateCardCount": 4,
      "runtimeCardCount": 4,
      "planStepCount": 7,
      "tags": [
        "email"
      ],
      "overview": "Handle mailbox-state edits that stay on existing messages: manage Thunderbird tags, then change visible message markers such as star or junk status and verify the result.",
      "applicability": [
        "Use this skill when the task changes tags, stars, junk state, or similar visible message status markers.",
        "Do not use this skill for moving messages into folders unless status change is the main goal."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Editing the wrong tag because the target tag row was not verified in Manage Tags.",
        "Marking the wrong message because the selected mailbox row changed before the state action was opened."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Apply Tags Stars and Junk Status to Messages\n\n## Overview\n\nHandle mailbox-state edits that stay on existing messages: manage Thunderbird tags, then change visible message markers such as star or junk status and verify the result.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task changes tags, stars, junk state, or similar visible message status markers.\n- Do not use this skill for moving messages into folders unless status change is the main goal.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open on the Mail surface or can be returned to from the current window.\n- The requested mailbox, account, sender, recipient, or folder name from the task is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **manage_tags**: Create, recolor, or remove Thunderbird tags.\n- Derived from: Apply or Edit Message Tags\n- **change_message_status**: Toggle star or junk state on selected Thunderbird messages.\n- Derived from: Toggle Message Star Read or Junk Status\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task changes a tag definition or assigns a named label`, choose `manage_tags`. Open Manage Tags first and verify the target tag row before editing its color or label.\n- If `the task changes a visible message marker such as star or junk`, choose `change_message_status`. Work from the selected message row and verify the resulting status or destination folder before continuing.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `tag_management_open.png`\n- `tag_color_ready_to_confirm.png`\n- `message_state_menu_open.png`\n- `message_status_result_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Create or edit a Thunderbird tag\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: tag_management_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Manage Tags dialog is open with the target tag row visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/tag_management_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task needs a tag definition change rather than a message move.\n\nAction:\n- Select the target tag row and open the edit flow for that tag.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Edit Tag dialog is open and ready to confirm the updated tag values.\n- Image reference: `Images/tag_color_ready_to_confirm.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The tag name or color has already been adjusted in the tag editor.\n\n### Apply or remove the visible message state\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: message_state_menu_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- A selected message row is visible and its context menu exposes the state-changing actions.\n- Image reference: `Images/message_state_menu_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The target message has already been isolated in the mailbox list.\n\nAction:\n- Open the state-changing submenu for the selected message and choose the requested star or junk action.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The result of the status change is visible in the mailbox, such as the Junk folder being selected after marking mail as junk.\n- Image reference: `Images/message_status_result_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested status change has already been applied.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Editing the wrong tag because the target tag row was not verified in Manage Tags.\n- Marking the wrong message because the selected mailbox row changed before the state action was opened.",
