      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Send Only SMTP Accounts\n\n## Overview\n\nReach Thunderbird’s outgoing-only mail-account path, expose manual outgoing settings when needed, and verify that the intended SMTP profile is the active default without broad incoming-mail guidance.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task is about send-only mail setup, manual outgoing server exposure, or choosing the default SMTP profile.\n- Do not use this skill for general identity text edits once the account already exists.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **reach_manual_send_only_setup**: Expose the manual outgoing settings path from Thunderbird account setup.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts, Configure Outgoing SMTP Servers and Defaults\n- **set_default_smtp_profile**: Choose and verify the active outgoing SMTP default.\n- Derived from: Configure Outgoing SMTP Servers and Defaults\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task starts from account setup and must avoid broad incoming-mail configuration`, choose `reach_manual_send_only_setup`. Stay on the manual account-setup branch that clearly shows the outgoing server controls.\n- If `the task only changes which SMTP profile is used for sending`, choose `set_default_smtp_profile`. Work directly from the Outgoing Server (SMTP) list and verify the default marker after the change.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `906eb418-f684-45c5-9d1c-33fb8c335fbf.png`\n- `2c899028-5d91-4e20-ae7d-fbb90375dabc.png`\n- `f6349e5b-7ba9-4510-a043-5835ebf81e88.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Reach the manual account configuration branch that exposes outgoing server details\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: manual_account_configuration_available\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The account setup dialog exposes the manual configuration link alongside the outgoing SMTP server row.\n- Image reference: `Images/906eb418-f684-45c5-9d1c-33fb8c335fbf.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The mail-account wizard is open and the outgoing settings must be inspected manually.\n\nAction:\n- Open the manual configuration path only after confirming that the outgoing server row is visible on the setup dialog.\n\n### Confirm the desired outgoing server remains the active SMTP default\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 2: smtp_settings_list_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Outgoing Server (SMTP) list shows the target server row and the Set Default control.\n- Image reference: `Images/2c899028-5d91-4e20-ae7d-fbb90375dabc.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The SMTP settings page is already open.\n\nAction:\n- Select the intended SMTP profile and use Set Default only after the target row is clearly highlighted.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The SMTP settings list marks the intended outgoing profile as Default.\n- Image reference: `Images/f6349e5b-7ba9-4510-a043-5835ebf81e88.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The desired SMTP profile has already been promoted to the active default.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Falling into ordinary incoming-mail configuration instead of staying on the outgoing-only path.\n- Choosing the wrong SMTP row when multiple similarly named profiles exist.",
