      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Server Retrieval Retention and Cache Settings\n\n## Overview\n\nAdjust Thunderbird server retrieval cadence, deletion policy, per-account Synchronization & Storage retention, General > Disk Space cache limits, or closely related persisted account prefs such as incoming-filter auto-apply behavior, then verify the value from the same scoped surface.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task changes startup retrieval, deletion semantics, retention, cache sizing, or advanced persisted account prefs such as incoming-filter auto-apply behavior.\n- Do not use this skill for composition defaults or reply formatting.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_account_server_settings**: Reach the Server Settings page for retrieval, deletion, or advanced account buffer controls.\n- Derived from: Configure Server Retrieval Retention and Cache\n- **open_account_sync_storage**: Reach Synchronization & Storage for retained local-message controls on a specific account.\n- Derived from: Configure Server Retrieval Retention and Cache\n- **open_global_disk_space**: Reach General > Disk Space for global cache-size and cache-clearing behavior.\n- Derived from: Configure Server Retrieval Retention and Cache\n- **verify_persisted_storage_values**: Verify the visible numeric, checkbox, or retention value after editing.\n- Derived from: Configure Server Retrieval Retention and Cache\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task changes retrieval, deletion semantics, startup message checks, or advanced persisted account prefs such as automatic incoming filters or biff status for one account`, choose `open_account_server_settings`. Prefer the account-level Server Settings page or a closely related advanced-preference path when the change is scoped to one account or one persisted Thunderbird profile pref.\n- If `the task changes kept-local-message limits or Synchronization & Storage retention for one account`, choose `open_account_sync_storage`. Use the account-level Synchronization & Storage page and verify the visible retention controls there.\n- If `the task changes application cache size or clears cache on exit for Thunderbird overall`, choose `open_global_disk_space`. Use General > Disk Space for global cache behavior instead of account-specific storage pages.\n- If `the value has already been changed and the task needs confirmation`, choose `verify_persisted_storage_values`. Verify the visible numeric or checkbox state on the same scoped page before leaving.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `server_settings_open.png`\n- `storage_value_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the correct account or global storage surface and verify the saved values\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: server_settings_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target Thunderbird account is already on Server Settings or Synchronization & Storage, or Thunderbird General settings are open on Disk Space, so the requested scoped control is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/server_settings_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task is about account retrieval, deletion, auto-apply filter prefs, or other persisted server-side behavior rather than compose defaults.\n\nAction:\n- Stay on the correctly scoped server, storage, or advanced-preference surface and adjust only the requested persisted account-level values, such as incoming-filter auto-apply or biff status.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Synchronization & Storage or General > Disk Space page shows the cache or retention control that proves the requested value is persisted.\n- Image reference: `Images/storage_value_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested storage-related value has already been entered.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Editing global preferences instead of the target account’s server or storage page.\n- Editing account storage settings when the task actually targets global General > Disk Space cache controls.\n- Leaving the page before verifying the final numeric or checkbox value that proves the setting persisted.",
