      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Thunderbird Calendar Views and Workweek\n\n## Overview\n\nChange Thunderbird Calendar display defaults such as week span, previous-week display, working days, and short-date presentation from Calendar preferences.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task is about Calendar view spans, workweek days, or date-format display values.\n- Do not use this skill for creating or editing calendar events.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and Calendar can be reached from the current window.\n- The requested event details, dates, or calendar file are already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_calendar_preferences**: Reach Thunderbird Calendar preferences for display configuration.\n- Derived from: Configure Calendar Layout and Workweek\n- **set_calendar_span_and_workweek**: Apply the requested date format, week span, or workweek values.\n- Derived from: Configure Calendar Layout and Workweek\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task changes multi-week display, previous weeks, or date format`, choose `set_calendar_span_and_workweek`. Work from Calendar preferences and confirm the visible selected values before leaving.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `calendar_preferences_open.png`\n- `date_format_or_span_set.png`\n- `workweek_values_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open Calendar preferences and set the requested display values\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: calendar_preferences_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird Settings is already on the Calendar category where display values are configured.\n- Image reference: `Images/calendar_preferences_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task is editing Calendar preferences rather than event entries.\n\nAction:\n- Stay on the Calendar settings category before changing date format, week span, or workweek values.\n\n##### State 2: date_format_or_span_set\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Calendar display controls show the date-format and week-span settings needed for the task.\n- Image reference: `Images/date_format_or_span_set.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- Calendar preferences are already open and the relevant display controls are visible.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested date format or week-span value from the currently visible Calendar controls.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Calendar preferences page shows the workweek controls that confirm the requested day selection.\n- Image reference: `Images/workweek_values_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The date-format and span values have already been changed and the task also cares about working days.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Editing event content instead of Calendar display preferences.\n- Changing one display control but not confirming the rest of the requested workweek or span values.",
