      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Thunderbird Layout And Visible Chrome\n\n## Overview\n\nChange Thunderbird pane layout and visible chrome such as the status bar, space toolbar, or related bars from the View path, then confirm the visible shell state.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Configure Thunderbird Appearance Layout and Advanced UI\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for pane layout, visible bars, toolbar visibility, straight-view style changes, and similar shell-level Thunderbird chrome adjustments.\n- Do not use this skill for theme, font-color, or display-color changes that belong to the theme and display skill.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the task-specific account, folder, or module is already visible or reachable from the current profile.\n- The requested destination value, message target, or setting value is known before the change is made.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_view_layout_surface**: Reach the View menu path that controls Thunderbird layout and visible chrome.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n- **toggle_visible_bars**: Toggle status-bar or toolbar visibility while verifying the correct chrome element.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task mentions layout, panes, straight view, or a visible bar such as the status bar or space toolbar`, choose `open_view_layout_surface`. Use the View path first so the correct visible-chrome submenu is confirmed before toggling anything.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `view_layout_menu_open.png`\n- `visible_chrome_toggle_ready.png`\n- `layout_or_chrome_result_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the View layout path and apply the requested visible-chrome change\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: view_layout_menu_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird View menu is open and the layout branch is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/view_layout_menu_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task changes visible layout or chrome from the View path.\n\nAction:\n- Navigate within the View menu only after confirming the layout-related branch is visible.\n\n##### State 2: visible_chrome_toggle_ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird visible-chrome toggle for the requested bar or shell element is exposed and ready to change.\n- Image reference: `Images/visible_chrome_toggle_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct View or toolbar submenu is already open and the task is about changing visibility.\n\nAction:\n- Toggle the requested bar or toolbar item only after confirming the exact entry matches the task.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird shell now shows the requested final layout or visible-bar state.\n- Image reference: `Images/layout_or_chrome_result_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The layout or visible-chrome change has already been applied.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Toggling the wrong bar because the submenu entry was not verified first.\n- Stopping at the menu without confirming the visible shell state on the actual Thunderbird surface.",
