      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Thunderbird Mail Composition Preferences\n\n## Overview\n\nChange Thunderbird’s global composition defaults such as autosave, spellcheck, link previews, sending format, and address handling from the Composition settings page.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task changes general authoring defaults that apply to new compose windows.\n- Do not use this skill for reply quote behavior, which now lives in the dedicated quote-formatting skill.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **edit_composition_defaults**: Change autosave, link preview, spellcheck, or shortcut-confirmation controls.\n- Derived from: Configure Thunderbird Composition Defaults and Sending Format\n- **edit_sending_format_defaults**: Change sending format, forwarding style, or address-handling defaults.\n- Derived from: Configure Thunderbird Composition Defaults and Sending Format\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task changes autosave, spellcheck, link previews, or shortcut confirmation`, choose `edit_composition_defaults`. Stay on the global Composition page and verify the visible checkbox or numeric value before leaving.\n- If `the task changes sending format or automatic address collection`, choose `edit_sending_format_defaults`. Use the sending-format section of the same Composition page and verify the final selected option.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `c3db558e-6797-4877-a44d-ab5cc3ce62e7.png`\n- `1fba3dca-8f0c-4e34-9bb2-c994fe290ffe.png`\n- `f4d518af-346f-42e6-b9b1-921fb6737286.png`\n- `f513d649-6bab-43ea-b8e6-82c01a16cdc0.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the global Composition settings page and change message-authoring defaults\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: composition_settings_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird Settings is open on the Composition category and the authoring defaults are visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/c3db558e-6797-4877-a44d-ab5cc3ce62e7.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task changes compose defaults such as autosave, link previews, spellcheck, or shortcut confirmation.\n\nAction:\n- Stay on the Composition page and edit only the requested authoring defaults.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Composition page visibly shows the updated autosave and spellcheck defaults after the change.\n- Image reference: `Images/1fba3dca-8f0c-4e34-9bb2-c994fe290ffe.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested composition defaults have already been changed.\n\n### Set the sending format and related address-handling defaults on the Composition page\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: sending_format_controls_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The sending-format section of Thunderbird Composition settings shows the format options and address-collection controls.\n- Image reference: `Images/f4d518af-346f-42e6-b9b1-921fb6737286.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task changes sending format or automatic address handling rather than autosave or spellcheck.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested sending-format or address-handling option from the visible Composition controls.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The sending-format section shows the requested final selection after the change.\n- Image reference: `Images/f513d649-6bab-43ea-b8e6-82c01a16cdc0.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The sending-format and address-handling values have already been updated.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Using the account-level reply-formatting page instead of the global Composition defaults page.\n- Changing autosave or spellcheck values without verifying the final visible setting state.",
