      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Thunderbird Themes And Display Colors\n\n## Overview\n\nChange Thunderbird theme and display colors from Add-ons Manager or the Fonts & Colors settings path, and verify the visible reading surface after the change.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Configure Thunderbird Appearance Layout and Advanced UI\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for dark or light theme changes, custom text or background colors, high-contrast behavior, and font-size or visible display-color adjustments.\n- Do not use this skill for layout or bar visibility changes that belong to the visible-chrome skill.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the task-specific account, folder, or module is already visible or reachable from the current profile.\n- The requested destination value, message target, or setting value is known before the change is made.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_theme_surface**: Reach Add-ons Manager or the General settings page that exposes theme choices.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n- **adjust_custom_colors**: Open the Colors dialog and set the requested text, background, or high-contrast behavior.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task explicitly changes Dark, Light, or another named Thunderbird theme`, choose `open_theme_surface`. Work from Add-ons Manager or the relevant settings page where the named theme can be seen before it is enabled.\n- If `the task changes text or background colors, when-to-use rules, or similar display overrides`, choose `adjust_custom_colors`. Verify the Colors dialog and the requested color rule before closing back to the mail view.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `theme_manager_visible.png`\n- `colors_dialog_ready.png`\n- `display_result_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the theme or custom-color surface and verify the visible display result\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: theme_manager_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird Add-ons Manager is open on the Themes surface and the requested theme row is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/theme_manager_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task explicitly changes the active theme before any color-dialog adjustments happen.\n\nAction:\n- Enable or disable the requested theme only after confirming the correct theme row is visible.\n\n##### State 2: colors_dialog_ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird Colors dialog is open and the custom-color rule is visible for editing.\n- Image reference: `Images/colors_dialog_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task changes text or background colors or the rule for when Thunderbird should use those custom colors.\n\nAction:\n- Adjust the color fields or the use-colors rule from the dialog before saving back to Settings.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird has returned to the main mail surface and the requested theme or display change is visibly active.\n- Image reference: `Images/display_result_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested theme or display-color change has already been saved.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Changing only the theme row or only the color dialog when the task explicitly asked for both.\n- Leaving auxiliary settings tabs open without checking the actual mail surface that the user will see afterward.",
