      "skillMarkdown": "# Create Calendar Events and Send Invitations\n\n## Overview\n\nCreate Thunderbird calendar events, fill their core details, and add attendees or invitation behaviors when the task explicitly requires meeting invites.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for event creation, editing core event fields, or adding attendees inside Thunderbird Calendar.\n- Do not use this skill for calendar subscriptions or display preferences.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and Calendar can be reached from the current window.\n- The requested event details, dates, or calendar file are already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **create_event**: Open Thunderbird event editor and fill the requested event details.\n- Derived from: Create or Edit Calendar Events\n- **add_attendees**: Add attendees and invitation settings from the event editor.\n- Derived from: Add Event Attendees and Invitation Options\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task only sets title, time, privacy, or note fields`, choose `create_event`. Stay in the event editor and verify the requested event fields before saving.\n- If `the task explicitly mentions attendees, sharing, notifications, or invitation comments`, choose `add_attendees`. Use the invitation controls from the same event editor and verify the attendee list before sending.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `new_event_entry.png`\n- `event_editor_ready.png`\n- `invite_attendees_entry.png`\n- `invitation_send_ready.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Create the event and populate its core details\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: new_event_entry\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird Calendar is open and the toolbar exposes the New Event action.\n- Image reference: `Images/new_event_entry.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- No event editor is open yet and a new event must be created.\n\nAction:\n- Open the event editor from the Calendar toolbar before filling the requested details.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The event editor is open and visibly contains the requested event fields.\n- Image reference: `Images/event_editor_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The event editor has already been opened for the target event.\n\n### Add attendees and finalize invitation options\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: invite_attendees_entry\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The event editor toolbar exposes the Invite Attendees control for the active event.\n- Image reference: `Images/invite_attendees_entry.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The event body is already filled and the task now requires attendees or invitation behavior.\n\nAction:\n- Open the attendee flow from the event editor before changing invitation-specific settings.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The attendee list and invitation controls are configured and the event editor can send or close the invitation workflow.\n- Image reference: `Images/invitation_send_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The attendee list and invitation settings have already been configured.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening a task editor instead of the calendar event editor.\n- Editing core event fields but forgetting to verify invitation settings or attendee list state.",
