      "skillMarkdown": "# Create and Maintain Thunderbird Message Filters\n\n## Overview\n\nCreate, edit, reorder, delete, and run Thunderbird message filters while keeping the standard filter-management workflow separate from specialized subfolder automation.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for standard rule creation, deletion, reordering, enabling, disabling, or manual runs in Message Filters.\n- Prefer the dedicated subfolder-automation skill when the task explicitly depends on automatic runs into a mailbox subfolder.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **create_standard_filter**: Create or edit a normal Thunderbird message rule from the Message Filters dialog.\n- Derived from: Create or Edit Thunderbird Message Filters\n- **maintain_filter_list**: Reorder, delete, enable, disable, or run rules from the filter list.\n- Derived from: Create or Edit Thunderbird Message Filters\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task defines conditions and actions for a new or edited rule`, choose `create_standard_filter`. Open the Filter Rules dialog and verify the condition and action rows before saving.\n- If `the task changes list order, enabled state, deletion, or manual execution`, choose `maintain_filter_list`. Stay in the Message Filters list and verify the correct row before applying maintenance actions.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `fe458859-ebd6-41df-ae27-2fdb8e2beed2.png`\n- `9f934850-b680-4b7a-804e-73dd2a84a04d.png`\n- `a41d9743-0a28-4710-8fcc-7fef33a80cc7.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open Message Filters and define a standard rule\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: message_filters_dialog_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Message Filters dialog is open for the target account and exposes the New control.\n- Image reference: `Images/fe458859-ebd6-41df-ae27-2fdb8e2beed2.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The filter list is already open and the task is about creating or editing a rule.\n\nAction:\n- Open the rule editor only after verifying that the Message Filters dialog is scoped to the correct account.\n\n##### State 2: filter_rule_editor_ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Filter Rules dialog shows the condition and action rows needed for the requested rule.\n- Image reference: `Images/9f934850-b680-4b7a-804e-73dd2a84a04d.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The rule editor is already open for the target account.\n\nAction:\n- Set the condition and action rows from the Filter Rules dialog and verify both before saving.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Message Filters list shows the saved enabled rule after the editor is confirmed.\n- Image reference: `Images/a41d9743-0a28-4710-8fcc-7fef33a80cc7.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The rule editor has already been saved and focus has returned to the filter list.\n\n### Maintain existing filter order or membership from the filter list\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Message Filters list is open with the relevant rule rows visible for reorder, deletion, enablement, or manual execution.\n- *(No screenshot available — text description below)*\n- **Detailed layout**: Keep focus on the Message Filters list and verify the selected rule name before any destructive action.\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task is maintaining existing rules rather than defining a new condition-and-action pair.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Creating a standard rule in the wrong account because the Message Filters dialog scope was not checked.\n- Deleting or reordering the wrong rule from the filter list because the selected row changed.",
