      "skillMarkdown": "# Export Messages To Individual EML Files\n\n## Overview\n\nUse Thunderbird’s message export surface to save selected messages into local files, with an emphasis on the result-facing path that produces separate `.eml` files in a chosen directory.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task backs up or exports selected messages to local files.\n- Prefer this skill over compose or folder-management guidance when the goal is the exported file output itself.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open on the Mail surface or can be returned to from the current window.\n- The requested mailbox, account, sender, recipient, or folder name from the task is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_export_menu**: Open the Thunderbird export surface and choose an EML-compatible message export format.\n- Derived from: Export Selected Thunderbird Messages as Individual EML Files\n- **choose_destination_directory**: Confirm the local directory used for the exported message files.\n- Derived from: Export Selected Thunderbird Messages as Individual EML Files\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the export flow is already open on the message context menu or add-on export submenu`, choose `open_export_menu`. Stay on the export surface and choose the format that matches the task instead of drifting into compose or attachment flows.\n- If `the export flow already reached the local file chooser`, choose `choose_destination_directory`. Verify the target directory and the save action because successful completion depends on the resulting local files.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `425baee1-f0bf-4b1d-adc9-85e5c44a6f5f.png`\n- `02fd5771-2e94-4dfe-9a6b-5c8b983419aa.png`\n- `0a626f79-e1a4-43f8-8b89-0a771d4ad794.png`\n- `93122f96-de0d-45ce-a6ac-59b3c35e4e93.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Use the Thunderbird export surface to choose an EML-based message export path\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: export_format_menu_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The export submenu is open and the EML-based message export option is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/425baee1-f0bf-4b1d-adc9-85e5c44a6f5f.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task has already reached the export surface from selected messages.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the export format that writes messages as separate files and verify the export submenu before confirming.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird shows an export-complete status after a message-export run.\n- Image reference: `Images/02fd5771-2e94-4dfe-9a6b-5c8b983419aa.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The export action has already been executed from the export surface.\n\n### Save selected messages into a local folder as separate files\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: save_dialog_targeting_destination\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The file chooser is open on the intended destination directory for the exported messages.\n- Image reference: `Images/0a626f79-e1a4-43f8-8b89-0a771d4ad794.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The export flow has already reached the local save dialog.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested destination directory and verify it before confirming the export save action.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The destination directory is visible in the file chooser and shows the exported message files or destination path.\n- Image reference: `Images/93122f96-de0d-45ce-a6ac-59b3c35e4e93.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The destination folder has already been chosen for the export output.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Using a compose or attachment-save path instead of the message-export surface.\n- Choosing the wrong destination directory and losing the result-facing local output.",
