      "skillMarkdown": "# Find Target Messages in Thunderbird Mailboxes\n\n## Overview\n\nOpen the correct mailbox or folder and isolate the intended Thunderbird message row before a downstream action changes it.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the main challenge is locating the right existing message by sender, subject, folder, or recency.\n- Pair it with another skill when the task only starts after the correct message row is selected.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open on the Mail surface or can be returned to from the current window.\n- The requested mailbox, account, sender, recipient, or folder name from the task is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_requested_folder**: Open the correct mailbox or folder for the task.\n- Derived from: Search Mailbox Messages\n- **select_target_message**: Select the intended message row from the current list.\n- Derived from: Search Mailbox Messages, Select Messages by Sender Subject or Status\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the target message lives in a different folder than the currently visible list`, choose `open_requested_folder`. Change folders first so later selection and status changes apply to the correct mailbox.\n- If `the correct folder is already open but the target row must still be isolated`, choose `select_target_message`. Select the message row using visible sender, subject, or recency cues before taking another action.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `open_requested_folder.png`\n- `target_message_selected.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the right folder and select the requested message\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: requested_folder_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird folder tree shows the mailbox branch that contains the target message.\n- Image reference: `Images/open_requested_folder.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct mailbox or folder is not yet open for selection.\n\nAction:\n- Open the requested mailbox or folder from the Thunderbird folder tree before selecting the message row.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target message row is visible and can be selected from the currently open message list.\n- Image reference: `Images/target_message_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct folder is already open and the target row is visible.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Opening the wrong mailbox branch when multiple accounts expose similar folder names.\n- Acting on a visually similar message row without checking sender, subject, or recency.",
