      "skillMarkdown": "# Install and Configure Thunderbird Add-ons\n\n## Overview\n\nOpen Thunderbird Add-ons Manager, install the requested extension or theme, and verify any post-install option changes from the add-on’s own settings surface.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for extension or theme installation plus immediate add-on-specific settings changes.\n- Do not use this skill for built-in appearance settings that do not require Add-ons Manager.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **install_addon**: Install the requested add-on or theme from Add-ons Manager.\n- Derived from: Install or Configure Add ons\n- **change_addon_option**: Open the installed add-on’s own settings and change the requested option.\n- Derived from: Install or Configure Add ons\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task first needs the extension or theme installed`, choose `install_addon`. Verify the correct add-on card before confirming the installation.\n- If `the extension is already installed and the task changes an add-on-specific option`, choose `change_addon_option`. Stay on the installed add-on row and open its settings from the same card.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `addon_card_ready.png`\n- `addon_install_confirm_ready.png`\n- `addon_settings_entry.png`\n- `addon_option_ready.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Install the requested add-on from Add-ons Manager\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: addon_card_ready\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The requested add-on card is visible in Add-ons Manager with the install action available.\n- Image reference: `Images/addon_card_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The add-on search or recommendation list already shows the requested extension.\n\nAction:\n- Install the requested add-on only after verifying the correct add-on card.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The install confirmation dialog is open and the add-on can be added to Thunderbird.\n- Image reference: `Images/addon_install_confirm_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The add-on install action has already been requested.\n\n### Open add-on settings and change the requested option\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: addon_settings_entry\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The installed add-on row is visible in Add-ons Manager with its settings affordance.\n- Image reference: `Images/addon_settings_entry.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The target add-on is already installed.\n\nAction:\n- Open the add-on’s settings or tools menu from the correct installed extension row.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The add-on’s own settings surface shows the option that the task must change.\n- Image reference: `Images/addon_option_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The add-on’s settings page or dialog is already open.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Installing the wrong add-on because the card title was not verified.\n- Changing a built-in Thunderbird setting when the task explicitly targets an add-on’s own options.",
