      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Email Attachments in Thunderbird\n\n## Overview\n\nHandle Thunderbird attachment work from two entry points: save attachments from existing messages, or rename and manage attachments inside the compose window before sending.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task is about attachments rather than the full email body workflow.\n- Choose the existing-message branch for downloads and the compose branch for renaming or adding attachments before send.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open on the Mail surface or can be returned to from the current window.\n- The requested mailbox, account, sender, recipient, or folder name from the task is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **save_existing_attachment**: Save an attachment or inline image from an already received message.\n- Derived from: Download Attachments from Messages\n- **rename_compose_attachment**: Rename a compose-window attachment before the message is sent.\n- Derived from: Add or Rename Attachments in Compose Window\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the attachment already exists inside a received message`, choose `save_existing_attachment`. Work from the message-view attachment surface and verify the save dialog before confirming.\n- If `the attachment is part of an outgoing compose window`, choose `rename_compose_attachment`. Use the compose attachment list and verify the renamed attachment state before sending.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `attachment_save_action_open.png`\n- `save_dialog_ready.png`\n- `attachment_rename_action_open.png`\n- `attachment_rename_confirm_ready.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Save an existing attachment from a message\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: attachment_save_action_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The message view shows the attachment surface with the save action exposed.\n- Image reference: `Images/attachment_save_action_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task is acting on an attachment from an existing message rather than a draft.\n\nAction:\n- Open the save action from the attachment surface and verify the attachment before saving it.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The local file save dialog is open and ready to write the attachment to disk.\n- Image reference: `Images/save_dialog_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The save action has already been selected from the message attachment surface.\n\n### Rename an attachment in the compose window\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: attachment_rename_action_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The compose attachment list is visible and exposes the rename action for the selected attachment.\n- Image reference: `Images/attachment_rename_action_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task is working inside an outgoing compose window.\n\nAction:\n- Open the rename action from the selected attachment in the compose window.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The attachment rename dialog is open and ready to confirm the new attachment name.\n- Image reference: `Images/attachment_rename_confirm_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The new attachment name has already been typed into the rename dialog.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Using the compose attachment workflow for a received-message download task.\n- Renaming the wrong attachment because the selected attachment chip was not verified first.",
