      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Thunderbird Address Book Contacts\n\n## Overview\n\nOpen Thunderbird Address Book or account-linked card editing surfaces, select the intended person, change the requested fields, and verify the saved contact values.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for address-book contacts and personal card edits.\n- Do not use this skill for mail-account identity text that lives in Account Settings rather than a contact card.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the current profile already contains the account or feature named in the task.\n- The requested value or destination is known before editing settings.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **edit_address_book_contact**: Edit a saved Thunderbird Address Book contact.\n- Derived from: Edit Address Book Contacts and Cards\n- **edit_personal_card**: Edit the account-linked personal card from Account Settings.\n- Derived from: Edit Address Book Contacts and Cards\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task names a normal contact in Address Book`, choose `edit_address_book_contact`. Work from the Address Book list and verify the selected contact row before editing.\n- If `the task explicitly references the personal card or an account-linked card`, choose `edit_personal_card`. Use Edit Card from Account Settings so the right account-linked card is opened.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `contact_selected.png`\n- `contact_save_ready.png`\n- `personal_card_entry.png`\n- `personal_card_save_ready.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Select the target contact and open its editor\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: contact_selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The target contact row is selected in Thunderbird Address Book and the edit control is available.\n- Image reference: `Images/contact_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task edits a regular Address Book contact.\n\nAction:\n- Verify the selected contact row before opening the contact editor.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The contact editor is open and ready to save the requested field changes.\n- Image reference: `Images/contact_save_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested contact fields have already been edited.\n\n### Edit the account-linked personal card\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: personal_card_entry\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Account Settings is open and exposes the Edit Card action for the account-linked personal card.\n- Image reference: `Images/personal_card_entry.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task targets a personal card or account-linked contact.\n\nAction:\n- Open the personal card editor from Account Settings and verify the right account window first.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The personal card editor is ready to save the requested card changes.\n- Image reference: `Images/personal_card_save_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested personal-card fields have already been entered.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Editing the wrong contact because the selected Address Book row was not verified.\n- Opening a personal-card editor when the task only targets a normal contact, or vice versa.",
