      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Thunderbird Home Surfaces Profiles And Unified Inbox\n\n## Overview\n\nReturn Thunderbird from auxiliary tabs back to the main mail home surface, and route profile-related internal-page requests through the in-app Troubleshooting Information surface instead of guessing at startup dialogs. Unified-folder guidance is retained only as low-confidence supplemental advice until stronger visual evidence is available.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Configure Thunderbird Appearance Layout and Advanced UI\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task says to return to Thunderbird's initial or home surface, clean up extra tabs, or open a profile-related internal page from inside Thunderbird.\n- Use unified-folder guidance only when the folder-mode control or combined Inbox entry is already visible on screen; otherwise treat that branch as low-confidence.\n- Do not use this skill for ordinary theme or layout changes once the user is already on the correct surface.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the task-specific account, folder, or module is already visible or reachable from the current profile.\n- The requested destination value, message target, or setting value is known before the change is made.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **return_to_mail_home_surface**: Close auxiliary Thunderbird tabs and verify the main mail view is back on screen.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n- **route_internal_page_tasks**: Handle profile-related internal-page requests through Troubleshooting Information and the Profile Directory entry point; treat unified-folder requests as low-confidence supplemental guidance only when the folder-mode control is already visible.\n- Derived from: Configure Appearance Layout and Reading Theme\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task explicitly asks to go back to the homepage, initial page, or a normal mail surface after closing tabs`, choose `return_to_mail_home_surface`. Finish the cleanup by verifying the main mail surface, not just by clicking tab-close buttons.\n- If `the task names profile management, about:profiles-style content, Troubleshooting Information, or another internal page tied to the active Thunderbird profile`, choose `route_internal_page_tasks`. Anchor profile-related navigation on the in-app Troubleshooting Information surface and do not confuse it with the startup profile chooser dialog.\n- If `the task mentions Smart Folders, Unified Folders, or Unified Inbox but the folder-mode control is not yet visible`, still choose `route_internal_page_tasks`. Recover a visible folder-mode control or combined Inbox cue before relying on this skill for unified-folder work.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `auxiliary_tab_ready_to_close.png`\n- `mail_home_surface_visible.png`\n- `troubleshooting_information_profile_entry_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Close auxiliary tabs and return Thunderbird to the main mail home surface\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: auxiliary_tab_ready_to_close\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird still shows an auxiliary tab such as Settings or Add-ons Manager and the close control is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/auxiliary_tab_ready_to_close.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task asks to return to the initial or homepage surface after changes made in another tab.\n\nAction:\n- Close only the auxiliary Thunderbird tab that blocks the main mail surface.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Thunderbird has returned to the main mail surface with the normal folder tree and message list visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/mail_home_surface_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The auxiliary tabs have already been closed and the task needs the normal home surface again.\n\n### Route profile-related internal-page tasks through Troubleshooting Information before attempting profile actions\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: troubleshooting_information_profile_entry_visible\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird Troubleshooting Information page is open and the Profile Directory row with its Open Directory button is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/troubleshooting_information_profile_entry_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The instruction asks for profile management or another internal page tied to the current Thunderbird profile.\n\nAction:\n- Use the in-app Troubleshooting Information page to anchor profile-related navigation, and only follow the Profile Directory or related profile entry once the row is visible.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The folder pane is in a unified-folder mode and a combined Inbox or Unified Inbox entry is visible after the folder-mode control has already been exposed.\n- *(No screenshot available — text description below)*\n- **Detailed layout**: The folder pane is in a unified-folder mode and a combined Inbox or Unified Inbox entry is visible after the folder-mode control has already been exposed.\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The instruction asks for Smart Folders, Unified Folders, or a unified Inbox surface.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Closing the whole Thunderbird window instead of only closing the blocking tab.\n- Opening the startup profile chooser dialog when the task explicitly needs an in-app profile-related page.\n- Treating unified-folder work as menu-guessing when the folder-mode control is not yet visible on screen.",
