      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Thunderbird Identity Fields\n\n## Overview\n\nEdit saved Thunderbird identity fields such as reply-to, signature text, account display name, organization, and business-card details without treating normal account onboarding as the same workflow.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Manage Thunderbird Mail Accounts and Identities\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task edits saved identity values on an existing Thunderbird mail account.\n- Do not use this skill for send-only SMTP defaults or for account-creation work that primarily belongs to the onboarding flow.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the task-specific account, folder, or module is already visible or reachable from the current profile.\n- The requested destination value, message target, or setting value is known before the change is made.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **edit_default_identity_fields**: Edit reply-to, signature text, account display name, or organization values inside Account Settings.\n- Derived from: Configure Mail Account Identity Fields\n- **edit_business_card_fields**: Open the business-card editor and change nickname or related personal-card values.\n- Derived from: Configure Mail Account Identity Fields\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task changes reply-to, signature text, account name, or organization for an existing account`, choose `edit_default_identity_fields`. Stay on the target account identity page and verify the saved field values before leaving Account Settings.\n- If `the task explicitly edits nickname or business-card information from the same account settings flow`, choose `edit_business_card_fields`. Open the card editor only after confirming the correct account identity page is already selected.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `e06630dd-304a-41a1-8e0a-642b797e60e2.png`\n- `business_card_editor_open.png`\n- `20ad9337-8a73-43f2-9691-11fbd0cab6a9.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Edit saved identity values and related business-card fields\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: default_identity_page_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Account Settings is open on the target account’s identity page and the requested fields are visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/e06630dd-304a-41a1-8e0a-642b797e60e2.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The account already exists and only persisted identity values must change.\n\nAction:\n- Edit the requested fields from the current Account Settings page after verifying the target account section.\n\n##### State 2: business_card_editor_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird business card editor is open from Account Settings and the identity card fields are editable.\n- Image reference: `Images/business_card_editor_open.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task also changes nickname or personal-card values after the core identity fields are edited.\n\nAction:\n- Use the visible business-card dialog to edit nickname or related personal-card fields before saving back to Account Settings.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 3)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Account Settings page visibly shows the updated identity values after editing.\n- Image reference: `Images/20ad9337-8a73-43f2-9691-11fbd0cab6a9.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The requested identity values have already been entered.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Editing the wrong account because the identity page was not verified before typing.\n- Changing signature or reply-to values but leaving the business-card edit unsaved in the modal dialog.",
