      "skillMarkdown": "# Manage Thunderbird Tasks and Task Conversions\n\n## Overview\n\nCreate Thunderbird tasks, convert emails into tasks, and adjust reminders, recurrence, postpone actions, progress, or deletion flows from the task editor and task list.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for task creation, email-to-task conversion, and task-list maintenance actions.\n- Do not use this skill for calendar events unless the task explicitly targets Thunderbird Tasks.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the Tasks view or source email can be reached from the current window.\n- The requested reminder, recurrence, or task text is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **create_or_convert_task**: Create a task or convert an email into a task.\n- Derived from: Create or Convert Thunderbird Tasks\n- **adjust_task_list_state**: Postpone, complete, or filter existing tasks from the task list.\n- Derived from: Adjust Task Reminders Recurrence and Progress\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task starts from an email or requires a new task entry`, choose `create_or_convert_task`. Open the task editor first and verify the save flow before leaving.\n- If `the task modifies already existing tasks from a list or filtered view`, choose `adjust_task_list_state`. Use the task list filters and verify the requested action option before applying it.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `convert_to_task_path.png`\n- `task_editor_save_ready.png`\n- `task_filter_selected.png`\n- `task_action_option_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Create a task or convert a message into one\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: convert_to_task_path\n\nVisual grounding:\n- A selected email row is visible and its context menu exposes the Convert To path.\n- Image reference: `Images/convert_to_task_path.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task converts an email into a task.\n\nAction:\n- Open the conversion path from the selected email only after verifying the correct source message row.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird task editor is open and ready to save the requested task details.\n- Image reference: `Images/task_editor_save_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task editor has already been opened for a new or converted task.\n\n### Filter the task list and apply a task action\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: task_filter_selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Tasks view is open and the requested task-list filter is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/task_filter_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task needs a list-based action such as postpone, delete, or bulk maintenance.\n\nAction:\n- Choose the requested task filter before applying the list action.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The requested task action option is visible from the selected task row or task action menu.\n- Image reference: `Images/task_action_option_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The relevant tasks have already been filtered in the list.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Creating a calendar event when the task explicitly needs a Thunderbird task.\n- Applying a task-list action without first verifying the filter or selected task row.",
