      "id": "THUNDERBIRD_Onboard_And_Remove_Thunderbird_Mail_Accounts",
      "name": "Onboard And Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts",
      "description": "Open Thunderbird's existing-mail onboarding flow, keep the filled setup page visible for manual review, and use the matching removal path when the task is about account membership.",
      "domain": "thunderbird",
      "domainLabel": "Thunderbird",
      "platform": "Ubuntu",
      "category": "GUI Tasks",
      "sourcePath": "ubuntu/thunderbird/THUNDERBIRD_Onboard_And_Remove_Thunderbird_Mail_Accounts",
      "imageCount": 9,
      "stateCardCount": 4,
      "runtimeCardCount": 4,
      "planStepCount": 7,
      "tags": [
        "thunderbird"
      ],
      "overview": "Use Thunderbird's regular mail-account onboarding path for existing-mail accounts, stop on the filled setup page when the task is only to prepare access for manual review, surface the manual-configuration branch when IMAP or server details must remain visible, and verify the Remove Account and Data dialog before confirming deletion.",
      "applicability": [
        "Use this skill for regular Thunderbird mail-account membership changes such as opening the existing-mail wizard, filling account credentials, stopping on the review page for manual checking, or removing a normal mail acc",
        "Do not use this skill for chat-account lifecycle tasks or for outgoing-only SMTP-default tasks that belong to the dedicated send-only skill."
      ],
      "failureModes": [
        "Stopping at the generic new-account chooser without opening the actual existing-mail setup form.",
        "Using chat-account removal cues when the task is about a normal mail account.",
        "Confirming deletion without checking that the Remove Account and Data dialog names the intended mail account."
      ],
      "skillMarkdown": "# Onboard And Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts\n\n## Overview\n\nUse Thunderbird's regular mail-account onboarding path for existing-mail accounts, stop on the filled setup page when the task is only to prepare access for manual review, surface the manual-configuration branch when IMAP or server details must remain visible, and verify the Remove Account and Data dialog before confirming deletion.\n\n## Source Atomic Skills\n\n- Manage Thunderbird Mail Accounts and Identities\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill for regular Thunderbird mail-account membership changes such as opening the existing-mail wizard, filling account credentials, stopping on the review page for manual checking, or removing a normal mail account.\n- Do not use this skill for chat-account lifecycle tasks or for outgoing-only SMTP-default tasks that belong to the dedicated send-only skill.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and the task-specific account, folder, or module is already visible or reachable from the current profile.\n- The requested destination value, message target, or setting value is known before the change is made.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **open_mail_account_wizard**: Open Thunderbird's regular mail-account onboarding flow from the application menu.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts\n- **inspect_manual_configuration_branch**: Reach the manual-configuration branch when the setup dialog needs closer inspection before completion.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts, Configure Outgoing SMTP Servers and Defaults\n- **remove_mail_account_from_settings**: Remove a normal mail account from Account Settings using the Account Actions menu.\n- Derived from: Add or Remove Thunderbird Mail Accounts\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task is adding a regular mail account and Thunderbird still shows the main window or application menu`, choose `open_mail_account_wizard`. Start from Thunderbird's New Account entry instead of treating the account as a chat or feed setup.\n- If `the task asks you to fill the form and stay on the setup page for manual checking, or it requires IMAP or server details to remain visible before finishing`, choose `inspect_manual_configuration_branch`. Stay on the wizard until the filled name, email, and password fields plus the IMAP or manual-configuration cues are visible; do not finish the setup prematurely.\n- If `the task explicitly removes an existing normal mail account`, choose `remove_mail_account_from_settings`. Use Account Settings and Account Actions so the account identity can be verified before deletion.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `new_mail_account_entry.png`\n- `mail_account_form_ready.png`\n- `906eb418-f684-45c5-9d1c-33fb8c335fbf.png`\n- `mail_account_removal_confirmation_visible.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Open the regular mail-account onboarding flow and inspect setup details\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: new_mail_account_entry\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird application menu is open and exposes the New Account entry point.\n- Image reference: `Images/new_mail_account_entry.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task needs the regular mail-account membership flow.\n\nAction:\n- Open the regular New Account flow from the Thunderbird application menu.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The mail-account setup form is visible with the account name, email address, and password fields ready or already filled so the task can pause here for manual review.\n- Image reference: `Images/mail_account_form_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The regular mail-account setup wizard is already open and the task is about filling or verifying the form.\n\nAction:\n- Fill the requested account name, email, and password, then keep the wizard open and verify the visible fields before continuing.\n\n##### State 3: manual_account_configuration_available\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The account setup dialog exposes the manual configuration branch or protocol summary so IMAP or other server details can stay visible for manual review.\n- Image reference: `Images/906eb418-f684-45c5-9d1c-33fb8c335fbf.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The mail-account wizard is open and the task needs visible IMAP or server details before completion.\n\nAction:\n- Open or stay on the manual-configuration branch only after confirming that the IMAP or server summary is visible on the setup dialog.\n\n### Remove a normal mail account from Account Settings\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 4: mail_account_selected_for_removal\n\nVisual grounding:\n- Account Settings is open on a normal mail-account entry rather than a chat, feed, or newsgroup account.\n- *(No screenshot available — text description below)*\n- **Detailed layout**: Account Settings is open on a normal mail-account entry rather than a chat, feed, or newsgroup account.\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The task explicitly removes a regular mail account from Thunderbird.\n\nAction:\n- Select the requested mail-account row in Account Settings, then open Account Actions and choose Remove Account.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 5)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Remove Account and Data confirmation dialog is open for the selected Thunderbird mail account, and the Remove button is visible.\n- Image reference: `Images/mail_account_removal_confirmation_visible.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The removal flow has already been opened from Account Actions for the requested mail account.\n\nAction:\n- Verify the dialog title, selected account label, and Remove button before confirming removal.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Stopping at the generic new-account chooser without opening the actual existing-mail setup form.\n- Using chat-account removal cues when the task is about a normal mail account.\n- Confirming deletion without checking that the Remove Account and Data dialog names the intended mail account.\n- Clicking through or finishing the wizard before the filled name, email, password, and IMAP cues are visible for manual review.",
