      "skillMarkdown": "# Organize Mail Folders and Move Messages\n\n## Overview\n\nCreate or rename Thunderbird folders, then move or copy selected messages into the requested destination folder once the folder tree is ready.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task changes folder structure or routes messages into a named Thunderbird folder.\n- Do not use this skill for filesystem export of messages, which belongs to the dedicated export skill.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open on the Mail surface or can be returned to from the current window.\n- The requested mailbox, account, sender, recipient, or folder name from the task is already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **prepare_destination_folder**: Create or rename the destination folder in Thunderbird.\n- Derived from: Create or Rename Mail Folders\n- **route_selected_message**: Move or copy the selected message into the destination folder.\n- Derived from: Move or Copy Messages to Folders\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the destination folder does not already exist`, choose `prepare_destination_folder`. Create or verify the destination folder first so later move or copy actions target a real mailbox path.\n- If `the folder exists and the task now routes a message into it`, choose `route_selected_message`. Use the message row context menu and verify the destination folder path before confirming the move or copy.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `folder_context_new_folder.png`\n- `folder_created_under_parent.png`\n- `message_move_to_submenu.png`\n- `destination_folder_chosen.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Create the destination folder when it does not exist yet\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: new_folder_action_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The Thunderbird folder context menu is open and exposes the New Folder action.\n- Image reference: `Images/folder_context_new_folder.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The destination folder does not exist yet.\n\nAction:\n- Open the folder-creation flow from the correct parent folder in the Thunderbird tree.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The new-folder dialog shows the requested destination name under the correct parent path.\n- Image reference: `Images/folder_created_under_parent.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The folder-creation flow has already been opened from the correct parent folder.\n\n### Route the selected message into the destination folder\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: move_to_submenu_open\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The selected message row is visible and its context menu exposes the Move To path.\n- Image reference: `Images/message_move_to_submenu.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct message row has already been selected in the mailbox list.\n\nAction:\n- Open the Move To or Copy To path from the selected message row.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The destination folder option is visible in the Thunderbird move or copy submenu.\n- Image reference: `Images/destination_folder_chosen.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The move or copy submenu is already open for the selected message.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Creating the folder under the wrong parent mailbox.\n- Moving or copying the wrong message because the selected row was not rechecked before opening Move To.",
