      "skillMarkdown": "# Subscribe and View Holiday Calendars in Thunderbird\n\n## Overview\n\nImport a holiday calendar file into Thunderbird Calendar and confirm that the subscribed holiday calendar appears in the visible calendar list.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Use this skill when the task imports a holiday calendar file or verifies a holiday calendar entry in the sidebar.\n- Do not use this skill for ordinary event creation or calendar display preferences.\n\n## Preconditions\n\n- Thunderbird is open and Calendar can be reached from the current window.\n- The requested event details, dates, or calendar file are already known.\n\n## Atomic Capabilities\n\n- **import_holiday_calendar**: Import the holiday calendar file from a local chooser.\n- Derived from: Import or Inspect Holiday Calendars\n- **verify_holiday_calendar**: Confirm that the imported holiday calendar is visible in Thunderbird.\n- Derived from: Import or Inspect Holiday Calendars\n\n## Decision Guide\n\n- If `the task starts from a local `.ics` or holiday calendar file`, choose `import_holiday_calendar`. Verify the selected file in the chooser before opening it into Thunderbird Calendar.\n- If `the file is already imported and the task only needs the subscribed calendar confirmed`, choose `verify_holiday_calendar`. Stay on the Calendar sidebar and verify the named holiday calendar row directly.\n\n## Visual Annotation Conventions\n\n- Red boxes mark the interactive target that should be clicked, typed into, or otherwise manipulated.\n- Green boxes mark the state signal or result change that the agent should verify before continuing.\n\n## Image References To Create\n\n- `holiday_file_selected.png`\n- `holiday_import_ready.png`\n- `holiday_calendar_selected.png`\n- `holiday_calendar_available.png`\n\n## Procedures\n\n### Import a holiday calendar file\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 1: holiday_file_selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The local file chooser is open with the intended holiday calendar file selected.\n- Image reference: `Images/holiday_file_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The import flow has already reached the file chooser.\n\nAction:\n- Verify the chosen holiday calendar file before opening it into Thunderbird Calendar.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 2)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The file chooser is ready to import the selected holiday calendar file.\n- Image reference: `Images/holiday_import_ready.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The correct file has already been selected for import.\n\n### Inspect the imported holiday calendar\n\n#### State-Action Mapping\n\n##### State 3: holiday_calendar_selected\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The holiday calendar row is visible in Thunderbird Calendar sidebar.\n- Image reference: `Images/holiday_calendar_selected.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The calendar import has already completed and the task now verifies the subscription.\n\nAction:\n- Select or inspect the holiday calendar row from the Thunderbird sidebar.\n\n##### Expected Result (State 4)\n\nVisual grounding:\n- The holiday calendar remains visible in the Thunderbird calendar list after import.\n- Image reference: `Images/holiday_calendar_available.png`\n\nTrigger condition:\n- The holiday calendar row is already visible in Thunderbird Calendar.\n\n## Common Failure Modes\n\n- Importing the wrong file from the chooser because the selected calendar file was not verified.\n- Assuming the calendar was subscribed without checking the visible calendar row in the sidebar.",
