      "skillMarkdown": "# Configure Preferences Hotkeys Paths And Persisted Defaults\n\n## When This Skill Is Applicable\n\nUse this skill when the task stays inside VLC and matches one of these flows:\n\n- Change a saved screenshot or recording destination in VLC Preferences.\n- Edit a persistent hotkey assignment in the Hotkeys table.\n- Verify that the visible saved path or hotkey row matches the request before leaving Preferences.\n\nDo not use this skill for one-off playback, snapshot, wallpaper, fullscreen, or convert flows that can finish directly from the active VLC surface or a one-time dialog.\n\n## Text-First Procedure\n\n1. Enter Preferences only when the task explicitly asks for a persistent saved value.\n2. Go directly to the relevant tab or row instead of browsing unrelated settings.\n3. Save and verify the exact path or hotkey row value before leaving Preferences.\n4. If the task can already be finished from the live playback or capture surface, back out of Preferences instead of continuing deeper.\n\n## Visual State Card Usage\n\nThis package keeps two image-card files:\n\n- `state_cards.json`: full detailed cards with detailed rationale.\n- `runtime_state_cards.json`: compact cards for runtime loading.\n\nLoad only the card whose `when_to_use` matches the live screenshot.\n\n- `Images/preferences_menu_entry.png`: preferences_menu_entry\n- `Images/snapshot_path_saved.png`: snapshot_path_saved\n- `Images/hotkeys_table_entry.png`: hotkeys_table_entry\n- `Images/hotkey_value_saved.png`: hotkey_value_saved\n\n## Visual Transfer Limits\n\n- Red boxes mark action regions. Green boxes mark result or verification regions.\n- Use stored screenshots as state evidence only. Do not transfer literal coordinates, example filenames, URLs, or example slider values into a different run.",
